<CHANGES>
## 2026.05.24.01
- Force-publish to re-verify all 163 smoke assertions on factory v2026.05.23.26 with the v.24-v.25 audit-fix batch + new tests baked in: WP #1082 SHA256 runtime, WP #1083 HTTPS validation, WP #1084 loop-mount cleanup, WP #1085 restore-snapshot guard, smoke safety net, concurrency A162-A163.
## 2026.05.23.25
- Audit fixes + new tests: WP #1082 SHA256 verify in runtime.sh; WP #1083 UrlValidator::requireHttps in CurlInstallSource/GithubReleaseSource/TarballSource; WP #1084 mount_stack.sh loop-mount cleanup on overlay failure; WP #1085 regression guard pinning restoreAgentVersion-snapshots-current; smoke safety net (tests/smoke/_safety.sh) snapshots production home_*.sqsh and restores on EXIT; new smoke A162-A163 (concurrency.sh) tests per-entity bake flock + WP#1080/#1081 busy defer.
## 2026.05.23.24
- WP #1081 follow-up: remove WORK_DIR wipe from both commit_stack.sh + consolidate_layers.sh. Under the new refresh-then-cleanup order (WP #1081), the overlay holds a live kernel fd on WORK_DIR/work after the refresh; wiping the subdir from userspace mid-mount broke overlayfs copy-up (smoke A10 reproduced: fopen on a new file in the merged view returned ENOENT until next mount cycle). The wipe was pure cosmetic kernel-scratch reclamation - overlayfs clears workdir contents on its OWN mount, so leftover bytes don't accumulate. Removing the wipe is correctness-preserving.
## 2026.05.23.23
- WP #1081 - close the residual cleanup-vanish race in commit_stack.sh + consolidate_layers.sh. WP #1080 added a second fuser check before the refresh but left selective_upper_cleanup BETWEEN the two checks; an agent that launched mid-cleanup could see a file vanish if cleanup removed it from upper while the mount hadn't yet been refreshed to expose the new lower. Restructure: single fuser check immediately before destructive ops, refresh-then-cleanup (instead of cleanup-then-refresh). Removing files from upper AFTER refresh is safe because the new lower is exposed. Same restructure in consolidate_layers.sh - compute UPPER_CHANGED before umount (find -newer reads UPPER_DIR directly, no mount needed), then refresh, then conditionally wipe upper. Net result: the only remaining race is the microsecond-scale umount window inside mount_stack.sh - down from 10+ second selective_upper_cleanup window. testWp1080RefreshRaceHardened updated to lock the new contract (single fuser+exit 2, refresh-before-cleanup, UPPER_CHANGED-before-refresh in consolidate).
## 2026.05.23.22
- Fix WP #1080 post-bake refresh race: agent launches mid-bake died with ENOENT during mount_stack.sh umount/remount window. Antigravity CLI clean-install on Tower showed: 'mkdir /tmp/.../home/.gemini/antigravity-cli: no such file or directory' exactly as commit_stack.sh logged 'Refreshing mount stack...'. Root cause: fuser -sm busy check ran BEFORE selective_upper_cleanup (which can take 10+ seconds on busy hosts walking /proc/*/fdinfo), but the unconditional mount refresh at the end raced against agents launched during that 10-second window. Fix: re-check fuser immediately before the umount in both commit_stack.sh and consolidate_layers.sh. If busy, skip the refresh and exit 0 - the new layer is on disk + manifest is updated; next mount cycle (next bake/agent launch/plugin restart/supervisor reconcile) picks it up. Two new lifecycle events for observability: bash_bake_ok_refresh_deferred + bash_consolidate_ok_refresh_deferred. Bake/consolidate itself succeeded; refresh is an optimization not a correctness requirement. PHPUnit guard testWp1080RefreshRecheckBeforeUmount uses strrpos slicing to lock the new check placement (must precede mount_stack.sh / umount -l respectively) without brittle byte-count regexes.
## 2026.05.23.21
- Polish WP #1078 follow-up: SQLITE_DB_COUNT counter no longer trips '[: integer expected' shell warning on empty input. Was using 'echo | grep -c -v ... || echo 0' which produced '0\n0' when SQLITE_DBS was empty (grep -c outputs 0 AND returns exit 1 on no matches). Replaced with 'printf | awk NF{c++}END{print c+0}' in both commit_stack.sh + consolidate_layers.sh. Pre-existing benign warning; only became visible when running PHP CLI persist for a no-SQLite home.
## 2026.05.23.20
- Fix WP #1078 critical SQLite data loss: mksquashfs append mode renames colliding top-level dirs with _N suffix (.copilot/ -&gt; .copilot_1/), stranding SQLite backups at unreachable paths. The append_zero_bytes_added check (8b4c397) caught only the 4KB-block-alignment subset. Three coupled fixes: (1) Replace mksquashfs append with overlay-merge single-pass bake via new bake_via_overlay_merge helper (common.sh). Lower=UPPER_DIR/MNT_POINT, upper=sqlite_stage; SQLite backups shadow live DBs at canonical paths; WAL/SHM/journal excluded via new build_mksquashfs_sqlite_sidecar_excludes. Removes APPEND_ARGS/APPENDING_TMP/_append_fail/append_zero_bytes_added entirely from commit_stack.sh + consolidate_layers.sh. (2) Disambiguate misleading session-active message via write_defer_reason marker (/tmp/unraid-aicliagents/.bake_defer_reason_&lt;type&gt;_&lt;id&gt;) + TaskService::deferReasonMessage switch on mount_busy/sqlite_backup_deferred/bake_lock_held/bake_landed_during_consolidate. Stale markers cleared at each script start; StorageMountService logs the reason. (3) One-shot orphan-_N cleanup: consolidate_layers.sh scans MNT_POINT/.*_[0-9]* and folds matches into MKSQUASHFS_ARGS as -e excludes. Spec at docs/specs/SQLITE_APPEND_DATALOSS_BUG.md. 5 existing WP#935+V08C2 tests updated; 6 new testWp1078* guards; new smoke A159-A161 (wp1078_overlay_merge.sh) verifies DBs at canonical paths, backup content shadowing, no WAL/SHM, live UPPER unmutated.
## 2026.05.23.19
- Fix: non-root audit - all 12 remaining tmux call-sites refactored to iterate per-uid sockets. PHP/root tmux client sees only its own server, so non-root agent sessions (e.g. aicliagent) were invisible to: TerminalHandler::agentSignalReload (Apply-now-args broken), AgentHandler::_closeSessionsForUpgrade (resume ids lost across upgrade), ProcessManager::stopTerminal (tmux orphan on hard stop), InstallerService kill (sessions survive agent install), InitService boot kill, plus 8 shell scripts (events/disks_mounted, events/stopping, events/stopping_array, stop-plugin.sh, repair-plugin.sh, installer/cleanup.sh, uninstaller/uninstall-engine.sh, uninstaller/cleanup.sh). Consolidated under ProcessManager::findTmuxSessionForId (single session lookup) and ProcessManager::killAllAgentSessions (bulk kill). Smoke A158 + PHPUnit testNonRootAuditAllTmuxCallSitesMultiUser guard every site.
## 2026.05.23.18
- Fix: non-root audit - all 12 remaining tmux call-sites refactored to iterate per-uid sockets. PHP/root tmux client sees only its own server, so non-root agent sessions (e.g. aicliagent) were invisible to: TerminalHandler::agentSignalReload (Apply-now-args broken), AgentHandler::_closeSessionsForUpgrade (resume ids lost across upgrade), ProcessManager::stopTerminal (tmux orphan on hard stop), InstallerService kill (sessions survive agent install), InitService boot kill, plus 8 shell scripts (events/disks_mounted, events/stopping, events/stopping_array, stop-plugin.sh, repair-plugin.sh, installer/cleanup.sh, uninstaller/uninstall-engine.sh, uninstaller/cleanup.sh). Consolidated under ProcessManager::findTmuxSessionForId (single session lookup) and ProcessManager::killAllAgentSessions (bulk kill). Smoke A158 + PHPUnit testNonRootAuditAllTmuxCallSitesMultiUser guard every site.
## 2026.05.23.17
- Fix: cross-workspace contamination in claude resume id discovery. discoverLatestSessionId('claude-code') was scanning ALL .claude/projects/&lt;dasherised-cwd&gt;/*.jsonl globally and returning the newest, which could be a session from a DIFFERENT workspace. Closing workspace B would then save workspace A's session id; clicking Resume on B later launched claude with cwd=B and --resume A-session-id, and claude rejected it with 'No conversation found with session ID: &lt;A-id&gt;' because the .jsonl lives under projects/-A-path/, not projects/-B-path/. Fix: thread the workspace path into discoverLatestSessionId and dasherise it the same way claude does (lead slash dropped, slashes replaced with dashes) to restrict the scan to the closing workspace's project subdir. Legacy fallback (whole .claude/projects/ tree) kept for callers that don't supply a path.
## 2026.05.23.16
- Fix: Bug #1071 follow-up - gracefulClose under non-root configured user. PHP runs as root; when cfg.user=aicliagent, the agent tmux server lives at /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/tmux/tmux-1003/default, but gracefulClose was running plain 'tmux ls' which targets root's tmux-0/default and missed aicliagent's sessions. With no session resolved the pane-scrape branch was skipped AND the disk fallback (discoverLatestSessionId) was gated inside the same sessName-empty check, so claude's existing .claude/projects/.../{uuid}.jsonl never got read either. Net effect: no Resume button after closing+re-adding a claude workspace under any non-root user. Two-part fix: (1) iterate every per-uid tmux socket under /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/tmux/tmux-*/default; thread the resolved socket into a tmuxBin prefix used by every tmux send-keys/resize/capture/has-session call in gracefulClose. (2) Pull discoverLatestSessionId out of the sessName-empty branch so it always runs when no resume id was captured from the pane. Smoke A157 + extended PHPUnit testBug1071 guard.
## 2026.05.23.15
- Fix: Bug #1071 - Antigravity CLI resume capture. Closing + re-adding an agy workspace never surfaced a Resume button because gracefulClose: (1) the pane regex matched only --resume/-s, but agy prints --conversation on exit, (2) only sent Ctrl-C, but agy ignores Ctrl-C and exits on Ctrl-D, (3) discoverLatestSessionId disk fallback had no antigravity-cli case. Fix wires all three: regex now accepts --conversation, Ctrl-D x2 is sent after the Ctrl-C x2, and antigravity-cli falls back to the newest &lt;uuid&gt;.pb basename in ~/.gemini/antigravity-cli/conversations/. PHPUnit testBug1071 + smoke A156 guard. Issue B (agy intrinsic double-Ctrl-D-to-quit) is upstream behavior, documented in the WP, no plugin fix.
## 2026.05.23.14
- Fix: Bug #1071 - Antigravity CLI resume capture. Closing + re-adding an agy workspace never surfaced a Resume button because gracefulClose: (1) the pane regex matched only --resume/-s, but agy prints --conversation on exit, (2) only sent Ctrl-C, but agy ignores Ctrl-C and exits on Ctrl-D, (3) discoverLatestSessionId disk fallback had no antigravity-cli case. Fix wires all three: regex now accepts --conversation, Ctrl-D x2 is sent after the Ctrl-C x2, and antigravity-cli falls back to the newest &lt;uuid&gt;.pb basename in ~/.gemini/antigravity-cli/conversations/. PHPUnit testBug1071 + smoke A156 guard. Issue B (agy intrinsic double-Ctrl-D-to-quit) is upstream behavior, documented in the WP, no plugin fix.
## 2026.05.23.13
- Fix: Bug #1067 - orphan ttyd sweep. Failed launches and unclean exits left ttyd processes alive forever along with their /var/run sock+pid+metadata, inflating the agent-upgrade dialog open-sessions count. New ProcessManager::sweepOrphanSessions enumerates aicliterm-*.sock, checks each ttyd's child-process count via pgrep -P, and reaps any ttyd alive &gt;30s with zero children. Wired into TerminalService::listActiveSessionsForAgent so the upgrade dialog gets the correct count, and into events/disks_mounted so array-start reconciles stale state. PHPUnit testBug1067OrphanTtydSweep + smoke A155 guard the wiring. Existing 6 live orphans on the test server will serve as the post-deploy live-fire test.
## 2026.05.23.12
- Fix: Bug #1067 - orphan ttyd sweep. Failed launches and unclean exits left ttyd processes alive forever along with their /var/run sock+pid+metadata, inflating the agent-upgrade dialog open-sessions count. New ProcessManager::sweepOrphanSessions enumerates aicliterm-*.sock, checks each ttyd's child-process count via pgrep -P, and reaps any ttyd alive &gt;30s with zero children. Wired into TerminalService::listActiveSessionsForAgent so the upgrade dialog gets the correct count, and into events/disks_mounted so array-start reconciles stale state. PHPUnit testBug1067OrphanTtydSweep + smoke A155 guard the wiring. Existing 6 live orphans on the test server will serve as the post-deploy live-fire test.
## 2026.05.23.11
- Fix: smoke A153 (Bug #1054 behavioral) bypasses boot_integrity strict mode. The test's synthetic persist dir has no layer manifest so the classifier flags legacy_unmanaged and strict-mode HALTS the mount before the OWNER chown can be exercised. A153 now toggles boot_integrity_strict=0 in cfg before invoking mount_stack.sh and restores the original value in teardown -- mirrors A56's warn-mode pattern. With strict disabled the mount completes and the runuser-as-smk1054 touch actually exercises the OWNER auto-default end-to-end.
## 2026.05.23.10
- Fix: smoke A153 (Bug #1054 behavioral) bypasses boot_integrity strict mode. The test's synthetic persist dir has no layer manifest so the classifier flags legacy_unmanaged and strict-mode HALTS the mount before the OWNER chown can be exercised. A153 now toggles boot_integrity_strict=0 in cfg before invoking mount_stack.sh and restores the original value in teardown -- mirrors A56's warn-mode pattern. With strict disabled the mount completes and the runuser-as-smk1054 touch actually exercises the OWNER auto-default end-to-end.
## 2026.05.23.09
- Fix: Bug #1054 follow-up - auto-reload Settings page on Terminal User switch + regress.sh tooling fallback. ManagerConfigTab stamps hidden aicli-original-user input; saveAICliAgentsManager forces safeReload on user change regardless of silent mode, so per-user UI state (Args panel, workspaces, etc.) re-renders from the new home overlay. PHPUnit testBug1054UserSwitchAutoReload guards the wiring. tests/regress.sh PHPSTAN_PHAR also falls back to .gemini path during the in-flight skill migration.
## 2026.05.23.08
- Fix: Bug #1054 root cause + audit fixes for ui-visual-reviewer compliance. Root cause: tmux uses the user's login SHELL from /etc/passwd (or SHELL env if set) to run session commands. System users like aicliagent (created via useradd -r) have /bin/false as their shell, so tmux invoked RUN_SCRIPT via /bin/false which exits immediately, killing the session and the server before the has-session check fires. DIAG-1054-PRE/POST-TMUX logs from v.07 captured this: new-session rc=0 but has-session-now=no server running. Fix: export SHELL=/bin/bash in aicli-shell.sh before any tmux call. Works for any sandbox user the admin picks (no install-time dependency). Audit fixes per ui-visual-reviewer skill: new tests/ui_playbook.json (Docker-runner format), removed anthropic SDK gate from run-l4.sh (visual review is the agent's job, no SDK calls allowed), updated stale Gemini wording in visual_review.sh / regress.sh / ui_e2e_playbook.md to Claude visual review per the new pipeline.
## 2026.05.23.07
- Fix: Bug #1065 + Bug #1054 v.07 diagnostic. Bug #1065 (Joly0 forum): adds StorageMountService::mountAllInstalledAgents() and wires it into events/disks_mounted so agent overlays are mounted at array-start. Without this, agent binaries appeared missing from the host shell after reboot because overlays were lazy-mounted only from TerminalService::startTerminal. PHPUnit testBug1065BootMountSweep + smoke A154 guard. Bug #1054 v.07: adds DIAG-1054 instrumentation to capture exactly where RUN_SCRIPT dies in the non-root plugin flow -- the v.06 fix should make it work per isolation tests but live launches still fail with no SHELL-CHILD logs, so we need on-the-wire data to pin down the actual death point.
## 2026.05.23.06
- Fix: Bug #1054 v.06 — mount_stack.sh now defaults OWNER to ID for TYPE=home, so every caller (commit_stack.sh remount-after-bake, consolidate_layers.sh's mid-launch remount) automatically applies the user chown without each one having to thread the arg through. v.05's self-heal alone was insufficient because commit_stack/consolidate re-mount mid-launch and the merged-view perms reverted to root-only, breaking aicli-shell.sh's tmux session start. New behavioral smoke A152b creates a throwaway system user, mounts a fresh home overlay via mount_stack.sh WITHOUT passing OWNER, and uses runuser to verify the merged view is actually writable end-to-end (the static A152 checks were the gap that let v.02-v.05 ship without catching this regression class).
## 2026.05.23.05
- Fix: Bug #1054 v.05 — chown+force-unmount self-heal. OverlayFS caches upperdir metadata at mount time, so the v.04 chown-only self-heal had no effect on the merged view (chown propagated to the underlying inode but not to the kernel's mounted-overlay perm-cache). Now when ensureHomeUpperOwnership detects a wrong-owner upper, it chown -Rs the underlying upper and work (catches root-owned subdirs from copy_up such as .aicli/), forces a lazy unmount, and signals the caller via a bool return. ensureHomeMounted skips the fast-path on forced unmount so the mount step below rebuilds via mount_stack.sh — which applies the OWNER chown at the correct moment for OverlayFS to honour the new owner on the merged view. Verified live on test server: post-remount, runuser -u aicliagent mkdir succeeds on the merged view.
## 2026.05.23.04
- Fix: Bug #1054 v.04 self-heal helper. Adds ensureHomeUpperOwnership() called from the top of ensureHomeMounted so already-mounted overlays with root-owned upperdirs chown the upper to the agent user without an unmount + remount. The v.03 OWNER chown only fired on fresh mounts via mount_stack.sh, but live upgrades hit the ensureHomeMounted fast-path and skipped the script entirely. The new helper computes the upperdir path (mirroring mount_stack.sh fstype logic) and recursively chowns it when the uid mismatches. Idempotent and cheap. PHPUnit + smoke A152 guard the new layer.
## 2026.05.23.03
- Fix: Bug #1054 non-root Terminal User support (v.03 follow-up — drop saveConfig validation that broke smoke A100/UC #623). TerminalService and mount_stack.sh carry the real fix. The ConfigService write-time guard was belt-and-braces but blocked the synthetic test user used to exercise getUserStatePath. TerminalService posix_getpwnam fallback from Bug #1053 already prevents bad on-disk values from reaching runuser.
## 2026.05.23.02
- Fix: Bug #1054 non-root Terminal User support. TerminalService sticky-1777s the shared tmp tree and chowns the per-user work dir before runuser. mount_stack.sh takes an OWNER 4th arg and chowns UPPER_DIR + WORK_DIR + MNT_POINT so OverlayFS writes inherit the user's ownership (previously the home overlay mounted but was effectively read-only for non-root agents). ConfigService::saveConfig now coerces any user value missing from posix_getpwnam back to root before write, mirroring TerminalService's launch-time fallback. PHPUnit testBug1054NonRootHomeOverlayWritable plus smoke A152 guard all four layers.
## 2026.05.23.01
- Fix: Bug #1053 - Terminal User dropdown saved the option index instead of the username. getUnraidUsers returns a numeric-indexed list of usernames, but ManagerConfigTab iterated it associatively, treating the list index as the key. Picking the 5th user wrote user=4 to the cfg and runuser -u 4 failed with user 4 does not exist - every terminal then showed Terminal session not found. ManagerConfigTab now iterates the list correctly. TerminalService now validates the configured user via posix_getpwnam and falls back to root with a logged warning if it does not exist, so any stale or numeric cfg value no longer bricks terminals. PHPUnit testBug1053UserDropdownSavesUsername guards both fixes.
## 2026.05.22.11
- Fix: Bug #1043 one-off migration — gracefully close pre-upgrade terminal sessions left in the old shared tmux socket. The switch to a private TMUX_TMPDIR would otherwise silently orphan any tmux session created by an earlier version in the shared per-uid socket. installer/cleanup.sh now, once only and gated by a sentinel file, finds those sessions on the old default socket, sends Ctrl-C twice so each agent flushes its state into the home overlay, then kills the session — the same safe close the UI uses. Runs before the hot-swap and full-teardown split so it covers both paths. Tests: smoke A151 plus PHPUnit testBug1043 guard the wiring.
## 2026.05.22.10
- Fix: Bug #1043 follow-up — switch to a plugin-private tmux socket directory instead of healing the shared one. The earlier fix chowned and chmod-700d the shared per-uid tmux directory before each launch, which mutates a directory the plugin does not own and could disturb another tmux user in narrow cases. Now every tmux caller — aicli-shell.sh, stop-plugin.sh, repair-plugin.sh, ssh-attach.sh, the uninstaller and installer cleanup scripts, the three event hooks, and the PHP bootstrap via putenv — points TMUX_TMPDIR at /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/tmux, a directory the plugin owns. tmux never touches the shared socket directory, so it cannot be corrupted from outside and there is zero blast radius. Tests: smoke A151 rewritten, PHPUnit testBug1043 guards every caller.
## 2026.05.22.09
- Fix: Bug #1043 — heal the tmux socket directory before launching terminals. tmux refuses its per-uid socket directory with an unsafe-permissions error, and every terminal then fails as Terminal session not found, when that directory is not owned by the user with mode 0700 — it is shared with anything else on the box that runs tmux. aicli-shell.sh now chowns and chmod-700s it before any tmux call. Triage confirmed on tmux 3.6a: a mode-0777 or wrong-owner socket dir is rejected and the heal restores it. Tests: smoke A151, PHPUnit testBug1043 guard.
## 2026.05.22.08
- Feat: Bug #1042 Secret Service — bundle an org.freedesktop.secrets daemon so keyring-using agents persist auth on headless Unraid. New Go static daemon implementing the Secret Service API plain transport, file-backed 0600 keyring in the agent home overlay. Per-user bring-up via secret-service-up.sh — a private dbus session bus plus the daemon, reused across sessions, works for root and non-root. aicli-shell.sh exports DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS into the agent env, finalize.sh makes it executable, stop-plugin.sh tears it down at shutdown. Tests: smoke A147-A150 with a live daemon self-test round-trip, PHPUnit testBug1042 guard. Spec docs/specs/SECRET_SERVICE.md. Fixes Antigravity CLI re-authenticating every session.
## 2026.05.22.07
- Fix: WP #964 rollback — de-duplicate the version-restore list. Two backups of the same version are equivalent because agent layers ARE the version, so backupAgentVersion now skips capturing a version it already retains, listRetainedBackups de-dups by version, and the restore optgroup omits the currently-installed version. Smoke A142 asserts version-uniqueness, two new PHPUnit assertions, VERSION_ROLLBACK.md updated.
## 2026.05.22.06
- Fix: WP #964 sort toggle — match the agent-sort button to the filter chips. The button element picked up the browser default font and line-height and rendered taller than the ALL INSTALLED UPDATES filter chips, so font-family and line-height are reset to inherit and the padding plus hover now match the filter chip styling. It reads as a fourth chip in the row.
## 2026.05.22.05
- Feat: WP #964 version rollback — restore a locally-kept agent version backup. InstallerService listRetainedBackups + restoreAgentVersion (realpath traversal guard, WP #966 per-entity lock, snapshot-first reversibility, PHP-native ZRAM-upper wipe), restore_agent_backup AJAX, Store version-picker Restore-a-kept-backup optgroup, companion A-Z/Z-A card sort toggle, LayerManifestService classifyLayerKind helper. Tests: smoke A142-A146 (version_rollback.sh), PHPUnit testWp964Rollback guards. Spec: docs/specs/VERSION_ROLLBACK.md.
