## 2026.05.22.03
- Fix: WP #964 rollback — move layer-kind classification into LayerManifestService::classifyLayerKind() so InstallerService no longer contains a consolidation-marker string (smoke A67 false positive). No behavioural change.
## 2026.05.22.02
- Feat: WP #964 version rollback — restore a locally-kept agent version backup. InstallerService::listRetainedBackups + restoreAgentVersion (realpath-anchored traversal guard, WP #966 non-blocking per-entity storage lock, snapshots the current version first so the restore is reversible, PHP-native ZRAM-upper wipe), restore_agent_backup AJAX action, a 'Restore a kept backup' optgroup in the Store version picker, and a companion A-Z/Z-A agent-card sort toggle. Tests: smoke A142-A146 (new tests/smoke/version_rollback.sh), PHPUnit testWp964Rollback* guards. Spec: docs/specs/VERSION_ROLLBACK.md.
## 2026.05.22.01
- Feat: WP #964 version rollback — restore a locally-kept agent version backup. Surfaces the copies the WP #965 keep-a-copy overlay captures: InstallerService::listRetainedBackups + restoreAgentVersion (realpath-anchored traversal guard, WP #966 non-blocking per-entity storage lock, snapshots the current version first so the restore is reversible, PHP-native ZRAM-upper wipe), restore_agent_backup AJAX action, a 'Restore a kept backup' optgroup in the Store version picker, and a companion A-Z/Z-A agent-card sort toggle. Tests: smoke A142-A146 (new tests/smoke/version_rollback.sh), PHPUnit testWp964Rollback* guards. Spec: docs/specs/VERSION_ROLLBACK.md.
## 2026.05.21.03
- Chore: clean pipeline run for the bake-only/home-only shutdown fix (v2026.05.21.02 deployed correctly but its smoke gate aborted on a stale assertion since rewritten). Bake-only home-only shutdown: supervisor flush removed (no consolidate cascade), home-only bake, budget from Unraid shutdownTimeout (var.ini/disk.cfg, default 90, minus 15s headroom), graceful agent SIGTERM before SIGKILL. Smoke A83 rewritten + A139-A141 added (141 total); 3 PHPUnit testShutdown* guards. Spec docs/specs/SHUTDOWN_BAKE.md.
## 2026.05.21.02
- Fix: bake-only, home-only shutdown. The shutdown path now does exactly one thing - bake the home overlays. (1) Bake-only: the supervisor flush is removed from event/stopping (it could cascade into an auto-consolidate via the post-bake layer-count trigger); the supervisor is stopped first so nothing can consolidate; the home bake is done directly by stop-plugin.sh via atomic_write_layer (delta, append-only - never touches an existing layer). (2) Home-only: stop-plugin.sh Step 6 drops the agent-bake loop - agent overlays are re-installable software, not worth shutdown budget; only home (irreplaceable user data) is baked. (3) Budget from Unraid's own Shutdown time-out: event/stopping reads shutdownTimeout from /var/local/emhttp/var.ini (live) -&gt; /boot/config/disk.cfg -&gt; default 90; run_full_stop is bounded by max(30, shutdownTimeout-15) instead of a hardcoded 30s - the 15s headroom keeps our bake+unmount inside Unraid's overall shutdown wall, and the budget tracks the user's setting. (4) Graceful agent shutdown: stop-plugin.sh hard-kills the aicli-run retry loops first (stops respawn), then SIGTERMs the agents and polls up to 5s so they flush their SQLite/state into the home overlay before the bake, then SIGKILLs stragglers. Residual risk is now unbaked-home-ZRAM only (bounded by periodic-bake cadence) - zero baked-layer loss, append-only by construction. Coverage: smoke A139-A141 (new tests/smoke/shutdown_bake.sh, total 141); 3 PHPUnit testShutdown* guards. Spec docs/specs/SHUTDOWN_BAKE.md.
## 2026.05.21.01
- Fix WP #966 (home data loss): per-entity storage lock — bake/consolidate/reconcile mutual exclusion. Root cause diagnosed from the live server lifecycle.log: the supervisor's reconcile runs every ~7s, scans persistence/, and quarantines any .sqsh not in the manifest to .untracked/. consolidate_layers.sh and commit_stack.sh mutate persistence/ + the manifest with no lock reconcile respected — and 'on disk but not in manifest' is exactly the normal mid-flight state of a consolidate (manifest swapped, old layers still deleting) or a bake. Evidence: a 12s home/root consolidate had a reconcile tick land in its delete loop and quarantine 4 home layers (incl. a fresh 13MB delta of the user's work) + re-add a 0-byte mid-deletion layer to the manifest (-&gt; mount failure -&gt; whole home stack dark). Fix: one shared per-entity lock /var/run/aicli-bake-&lt;type&gt;-&lt;id&gt;.lock honoured by all three. consolidate_layers.sh runs its long mksquashfs UNLOCKED (never blocks a bake), then takes the lock for the manifest-swap+delete critical section, re-validates the layer set first, and discards its stale consolidated layer (non-destructive) + defers if a bake landed during mksquashfs — baking is the priority. supervisor _op_reconcile holds the same per-entity lock per entity and skips (reconcile_skipped_locked) any entity whose lock is held. commit_stack.sh already holds the lock. Coverage: smoke A136-A138 (new tests/smoke/storage_lock.sh, total 138); 3 PHPUnit testWp966 guards. Spec docs/specs/STORAGE_LOCKING.md. Part 2 (non-destructive consolidation / .superseded retention) deferred to WP #964.
## 2026.05.20.04
- Feat WP #965 (first slice of WP #964 rollback): pre-upgrade keep-a-copy overlay. Clicking Upgrade on a Store card now shows an overlay offering to back up the current version before it's replaced. InstallerService::estimateUpgradeBackup (sums current agent_&lt;id&gt;_*.sqsh layers; required = ceil((current + estimated_new) * 1.10) with estimated_new guesstimated as ~current; disk_free_space of the destination, walking up to the nearest existing ancestor) + backupAgentVersion (copies layers to &lt;dest&gt;/aicli-rollback/&lt;agent&gt;/&lt;version&gt;_&lt;dt&gt;/ + meta.json sidecar, absolute-path guard, partial-copy rollback on failure). New AJAX action get_upgrade_backup_estimate. The backup runs as install-bg.php's first step before the binary swap; AgentHandler::install forwards backup=1+backup_dest positionally. A failed backup ABORTS the upgrade (current version left intact). Frontend: _showUpgradeBackupOverlay replaces the plain confirm for upgrades - keep-a-copy toggle (default on), editable destination defaulting to persistence, live size/free readout, debounced re-estimate; insufficient space or non-absolute path disables the backup but still allows upgrade-without-backup or cancel. Coverage: smoke A132-A135 (new tests/smoke/upgrade_backup.sh, total 135); 4 PHPUnit testWp964 guards. Spec docs/specs/UPGRADE_BACKUP_OVERLAY.md.
## 2026.05.20.03
- Feat: backfill changelog_url onto every default agent. WP #963's optional changelog_url field is now set for all 11 other agents (gemini-cli, claude-code, opencode, kilocode, pi-coder, gh-copilot, codex-cli, factory-cli, nanocoder, goose, qwen-code) so each Store card carries a Release-notes link. URLs verified via npm-view repository metadata + gh-api release/CHANGELOG existence checks: GitHub releases page where the vendor uses them, npm ?activeTab=versions fallback for opencode-ai and @factory/cli (no public release history). New testAllDefaultAgentsHaveChangelogUrl regression guard makes the field de-facto mandatory for default agents so a new agent can't ship without one. Relatedly filed WP #964 (local version rollback by retaining pre-upgrade agent SquashFS layers - the only possible rollback path for no-archive self-updating vendors like Antigravity).
## 2026.05.20.02
- Feat WP #963: Antigravity CLI version tracking. Antigravity ships via a self-updater with no GitHub releases/tags - its auto-updater manifest is the only latest-version source, CHANGELOG.md the human-readable history. (1) CurlInstallSource gains a manifest version probe: populateCache() (feeds the Store-tab version dropdown via a single 'latest'-tagged cache entry) and a manifest branch in checkUpdates() (feeds the update badge), both via probeManifestVersion() which fetches source.manifest_url and reads manifest_version_key (default 'version'). No downgrade/pin - the vendor publishes no archived builds, so latest-only is the honest representation. (2) New optional changelog_url registry field rendered by ManagerStoreTab as a 'Release notes' Store-card link (gated on a valid http(s) URL). antigravity-cli registry entry gains manifest_url (linux_amd64 manifest) + changelog_url (repo CHANGELOG.md). Coverage: smoke A129-A131 added to tests/smoke/antigravity.sh (now A122-A131, smoke.sh total 131); 2 new PHPUnit guards (testWp963ManifestVersionProbe, testWp963ChangelogLink). Both general - any curl_install agent whose vendor publishes a manifest/changelog benefits.
## 2026.05.20.01
- Feat WP #963: Add Antigravity CLI (agy) as a supported agent. Google folded Gemini CLI into Antigravity CLI at I/O 2026; Gemini CLI sunsets 2026-06-18 for AI Pro/Ultra. New AgentRegistry entry antigravity-cli using the curl_install source (vendor install.sh, captive HOME -&gt; binary at agents/antigravity-cli/home/.local/bin/agy). Resume via --conversation {chatId} / --continue. CurlInstallSource hardened: clean-reinstall (rrmdir captive bin/+home/ before re-run, PHP-native recursive delete - so the vendor script's idempotency check cannot no-op a plugin-driven upgrade) + timeout 300 guard on the script run. Antigravity .ico Store-card icon. Coverage: new smoke feature script tests/smoke/antigravity.sh (A122-A128, registered in smoke.sh); standalone tests/smoke_antigravity_agent.sh for the live install/upgrade/uninstall cycle; 4 PHPUnit RegressionGuards (Wp963). Spec docs/specs/ANTIGRAVITY_CLI_AGENT.md.
## 2026.05.18.08
- Fix data-loss review (seven hardening fixes on top of WP #935 + WP #941): C1 selective_upper_cleanup SQLite-aware excludes; C2 atomic append via tempfile + byte-growth verify in both commit_stack.sh and consolidate_layers.sh - hard fail/defer rather than proceeding to wipe; C3 cleanup.sh hot-swap synchronous pre-bake to flush ZRAM before potential power loss; M1 detect_sqlite_dbs sniffs every file (no extension pre-filter); M2 50ms marker gap; M3 distinguish sqlite_backup_all hard-error vs defer return codes; M4 layout-version sanitization in PLG INLINE + cleanup.sh. Seven new PHPUnit regression guards.
## 2026.05.18.07
- Fix WP #935 same-day data-loss: SQLite append pass was carrying the wide bake's -e &lt;db&gt; excludes forward into APPEND_ARGS. Since the SQLite staging dir mirrors the same relative tree as UPPER, the -e flags excluded the .backup files we'd just produced - silent no-op append, then selective_upper_cleanup wiped the live DBs from UPPER (old mtime, no open write fd between SQLite transactions). Net: opencode/goose/kilocode session DBs were permanently lost on bake. Caught from the very first deploy: home_root_delta_20260518T091609Z.sqsh was 4 KB despite bash_bake_sqlite_appended logging db_count:4 - unsquashfs -ll showed only empty dirs and a 518-byte workspaces.json, no SQLite files anywhere. Fix: APPEND_ARGS rebuilt from  (base only) with -noappend stripped, NOT from MKSQUASHFS_ARGS. Applied to both commit_stack.sh and consolidate_layers.sh. PHPUnit guard testWp935AppendArgsDoesNotCarryWideBakeExcludes added to lock the contract.
## 2026.05.18.06
- Feat WP #935 + #936 + #941: SQLite live-backup bake (consolidate + commit-stack three-pass: detect SQLite DBs -&gt; sqlite3 .backup to staging -&gt; mksquashfs -e excludes for *.db/*-wal/*-shm -&gt; mksquashfs -append staging; replaces all-or-nothing UPPER wipe with selective_upper_cleanup that protects files with open write fds via /proc/*/fdinfo flags inspection). qwen-code surfaces DASHSCOPE_API_KEY as a labelled password field on the Store card. Plugin upgrade flow goes hot-swap by default: cleanup.sh checks MIGRATION_NEEDED (defaults 0) via .migration_required sentinel or src/.layout-version change, exits early before bake/kill/umount when no migration needed - sessions, overlays, and agent processes survive routine upgrades. PLG INLINE snapshots OLD_LAYOUT_VERSION before src.tar.gz extract. PHPUnit regression guards added for all three WPs.
## 2026.05.18.05
- Fix: WP #932 post-test correction. After live --help probing on the test box for each of the 5 fixed agents, two regressions in v.18.04 needed reverting: (1) kilocode resume_cmd was changed from -s {chatId} to --continue, but kilo --help confirms BOTH -s/--session AND -c/--continue exist (sub-agent's research was wrong about -s being absent) — kilocode now uses --session {chatId} for per-ID resume (canonical form of -s) and --continue for resume_latest. (2) gh-copilot was treated as stateless and lost both resume flags, but copilot --help confirms BOTH --continue (resume most recent) AND --resume[=value] (per-ID resume) exist — gh-copilot now uses --resume={chatId} for resume_cmd and --continue for resume_latest. goose, pi-coder, opencode fixes verified against actual --help output and are unchanged. PHPUnit regression guards updated to assert the post-test-correct flags. This also adds proof for the WP #931 .gemini/tmp fix: synthetic chat probe survived a full consolidate_layers.sh run on test box with content intact.
## 2026.05.18.04
- Fix: AgentRegistry drift against upstream docs for 5 agents (WP #932). Findings from a Sonnet agent review against current upstream npm/GitHub state: (1) kilocode resume_cmd used a non-existent -s flag and resume_latest didn't actually resume — both now use --continue (Kilo Code has no per-session-ID resume). (2) pi-coder resume_latest used --resume which opens an interactive picker that hangs the SSH-attach flow; now --continue. resume_cmd uses --session for direct-ID. (3) gh-copilot binary now points at npm-loader.js (the real entry that tries the native SEA binary first) with index.js fallback; resume_cmd dropped the bogus --resume= flag (agent is stateless). (4) goose resume_cmd was creating a new named session instead of resuming — now uses session --resume -n {chatId}. (5) opencode binary now points at bin/opencode.exe with bin/opencode (npm bin symlink) as fallback — the package actually ships .exe-suffixed binaries cross-platform like claude-code. PHPUnit regression guard (testWp932AgentRegistryResumeFlagsMatchUpstream) locks in all 6 invariants. Deferred follow-ups (separate WP): GEMINI_CLI_HOME/CODEX_HOME/PI_CODING_AGENT_DIR/NANOCODER_DATA_DIR/OPENCODE_CONFIG data-dir-override env vars not surfaced; SQLite WAL corruption risk on opencode+goose mid-consolidate; qwen-code DASHSCOPE_API_KEY not in default_secrets.
## 2026.05.18.03
- Fix (data loss): pre-bake prune no longer deletes .gemini/tmp (WP #931). commit_stack.sh and consolidate_layers.sh used to rm -rf .gemini/tmp in the pre-bake prune block on the assumption it's regenerable cache. gemini-cli actually stores per-project session chat logs at .gemini/tmp/&lt;projectId&gt;/chats/session-*.jsonl there. Every consolidate was silently wiping users' chat history and then crashing the next gemini launch with ChatRecordingService.appendRecord ENOENT. Reported on Tower today after the v.18.02 upgrade triggered an auto-consolidate. PHPUnit regression guard added (testWp931PreBakePruneDoesNotDeleteGeminiTmp) to prevent reintroduction. Other prune entries kept (.npm, .cache, .bun/install, .claude/cache, .claude/shell-snapshots, .claude/telemetry are genuinely regenerable).
## 2026.05.18.02
- WP #703 + #700 (complete). React component tests: 4 new files (DrawerPanel/AgentCard/InstallProgress/ManagerStore) under ui-build/src/__tests__/, 24 new tests, 39 total green via vitest jsdom. Smoke decomposition: tests/smoke.sh became thin orchestrator with --list and --feature=&lt;name&gt; flags; 6 feature scripts under tests/smoke/ (_common.sh + infra/storage/lifecycle/agents/envs/bugs.sh) collectively cover all 121 assertions in the same numbering as the previous monolith. tests/regress.sh gains --smoke-filter=&lt;domain&gt;. publish-and-deploy.php scp step updated to scp both smoke.sh AND the new tests/smoke/ directory tree (legacy single-file shape still supported as a fallback). Sub-agents server-side verified 121/121 SMOKE PASS on 192.168.1.4 during decomposition.
## 2026.05.18.01
- Multi-WP batch: (#150) Semgrep gate L1.7 in regress.sh + .semgrep/aicliagents.yml ruleset (4 ERROR rules + 1 WARNING; skips locally if semgrep not on PATH or wrapper is broken). (#770) AtomicWriteService now uses fopen + stream_set_write_buffer(0) + fwrite + fflush + fsync to close the cross-process cfg-visibility lag that made L4 Step 7 channel-persist flake; L4 spec's cfg-write-lag soft-pass branch hard-fails now. (#703) React component test infrastructure scaffolded: @testing-library/react + user-event + jest-dom + jsdom added, vitest config switched to jsdom env, setup.ts stubs ResizeObserver/PointerEvent, smoke test verifies the stack. Full component tests for DrawerPanel/AgentCard/InstallProgress/ManagerStore remain TBD per spec but the runway is in place.
## 2026.05.17.03
- Fix: Consolidate-failure resilience overhaul (WP #922). Five-part hardening based on Tower lifecycle log evidence (2026-05-17T22:07:10Z home/root consolidate failed exit 1, self-recovered 2 minutes later, but the failure cause was lost to /tmp/debug.log rotation before investigation). (1) consolidate_layers.sh now does fuser -sm pre-bake; if any session has open files on the merged mount it exits 2 (deferred) rather than charging into the aggressive prune step and tripping set -euo pipefail. Same safety pattern as commit_stack.sh already uses. (2) Supervisor _op_consolidate now branches on exit 2 -&gt; consolidate_deferred lifecycle event, no failure counter increment, no halt escalation. (3) StorageHandler::getSupervisorStatus exposes a new consolidate_fails field; ManagerStorageScripts renders a non-blocking theme-friendly banner on the Storage tab when count &gt; 0 - surfaces the issue at fail 1 rather than waiting for the auto-halt at fail 2. (4) common.sh adds snapshot_failure + install_failure_trap helpers; consolidate_layers.sh and commit_stack.sh install the trap so on any non-zero exit the last 50 lines of /tmp/debug.log are snapshotted to /boot/config/plugins/unraid-aicliagents/failures/ AND a stderr_tail.txt is written for the supervisor to splice into its lifecycle event. (5) Supervisor's consolidate_failed AND bake_failed events now include stderr_tail in their JSON. PHPUnit regression guards added (7 new).
## 2026.05.17.02
- Fix: Storage halt UX overhaul (WP #916). (1) Agent total_loss now auto-heals — silently npm-reinstalls the agent instead of nagging with a destructive 'abandon data' prompt. New StorageHandler endpoint auto_heal_agent_install; UI in ManagerStorageScripts splits halts at render time and routes agent total_loss to the heal path. (2) InstallerService::uninstallAgent now calls LayerManifestService::removeEntity + HaltService::clearHalt — without these, an uninstalled agent's manifest entry survives and the next boot-integrity sweep creates a ghost total_loss halt (the gh-copilot 'Storage Unavailable' on Tower). (3) WIPE confirm dialog now has a real input field (SweetAlert type:input + WIPE-string validation + showInputError) — previously the dialog rendered no input box, making CONFIRM a decorative gate and CANCEL a loop-back-to-halt trap. Only home/total_loss shows the destructive option now. (4) Halt overlay re-themed: .unapi root + var(--background-color)/var(--text-color)/var(--border-color)/var(--orange) so light + dark + auto themes render correctly. (5) Every halt card gains Retry + Dismiss-for-24h buttons; Dismiss uses localStorage so refresh doesn't re-block. PHPUnit regression guards added: uninstall calls removeEntity+clearHalt; StorageHandler exposes auto_heal_agent_install; overlay uses .unapi+theme vars; WIPE dialog has real input; halt overlay provides non-destructive options.
## 2026.05.17.01
- Feat+Chore: e2e a11y + touch-target sweeps across 3 viewports (WP #903) + drop Beta flag from CA template. New ui-build/tests/e2e/specs/global-a11y.spec.ts runs axe-core (WCAG2 A/AA) + 44x44 touch-target sweep on Manager Store + Config tabs, tagged @responsive so they execute on every Playwright project. playwright.config.ts now has 3 projects: chromium (all specs, primary regression target), ipad-portrait (810x1080, @responsive only), iphone-14 (390x844, @responsive only). 4 viewports of the skill's 7-matrix intentionally skipped — Unraid admin tooling is desktop-first; 7x serial runtime against shared test box would have negligible coverage gain. New fixtures/matchers.ts adds toHaveTouchTarget custom matcher. @axe-core/playwright dev dep added + new npm scripts (test:e2e:desktop, test:e2e:responsive). unraid-aicliagents.xml: removed Beta=True — plugin is exiting CA-store beta with this release.
## 2026.05.16.01
- Feat: Synchronous home bake before agent binary swap on upgrade (WP #859). install-bg.php now calls SupervisorService::waitForOpsToDrain('home', user, 30s) before InstallerService::installAgent. Closes the timing window where install-bg.php could begin the agent binary swap before the supervisor had picked up the queued pre-install home bake. Existing safety nets (commit_stack.sh marker-timestamp + fuser busy check) still protect under the old async behavior; this hardening removes the race so the no-loss guarantee no longer depends on a chain of conditional defenses firing in the right order. Returns one of completed | no_pending_work | timeout; on timeout the install proceeds anyway (data still protected by the marker mechanism). Outcome logged via aicli_log + LifecycleLogService. Spec: docs/specs/AGENT_UPGRADE_HOME_BAKE_SYNC.md. PHPUnit regression guards in RegressionGuardsTest verify (a) SupervisorService exposes waitForOpsToDrain with the three documented return statuses, and (b) install-bg.php calls it BEFORE InstallerService::installAgent.
## 2026.05.15.16
- Fix: SSH Help modal button rendering on Unraid 7.2.x — defensive !important guards on .aicli-help-x, .aicli-help-tab (+ active/hover), .aicli-cmd-cp (+ hover) rules in ManagerConfigTab.php. Unraid 7.2 lacks the .unapi escape hatch (added in 7.3), so the modal's &lt;button&gt; elements were inheriting Unraid's global button styling (orange borders around X close, tab buttons, and copy buttons). 'all: unset' alone wasn't winning on Tower (7.2.6) — !important on every reset declaration short-circuits the specificity hunt. 7.3.0 test box still renders correctly; this only changes appearance on 7.2.x.
## 2026.05.15.15
- Storefront release notes — tighten public changelog and drop the inadvertent auto-promoted Docs: meta-entry. The v2026.05.15.14 publish auto-promoted the factory pre-flight commit message into CHANGES.public.xml; cleaned that up and folded the v.13 + v.14 content into a single concise v.15 entry. No code changes.
## 2026.05.15.14
- Docs: pre-storefront pre-flight — README.public.md fleshed out from a 10-line stub to a proper feature description (11 supported agents named, key features listed, support thread linked); CHANGES.public.xml gains a 2026.05.15.13 entry covering the SSH-attach feature (carefully worded — clipboard-only, no ssh:// browser-launch claim, no security-lockdown claim given the known Unraid root authorized_keys options-stripping behaviour), the marketplace empty-state fix, the Flash→persistent-storage wording cleanup, and the supervisor convergence test poll fix.
## 2026.05.15.13
- Polish: full green-color sweep on SSH chip — the outer 'Command copied' header tick + text, AND the small fallback chip's tick + text (used when SSH isn't ready, just copying tmux session name) are all now green (#6ee86e). Previously only the inner re-copy confirmation was green, leaving an inconsistent orange/green mix.
## 2026.05.15.12
- Polish: (1) SSH chip — Copied to clipboard tick + text now green (#6ee86e) instead of orange to match the success-state palette used elsewhere; (2) two remaining 'Flash drive' / 'on Flash' references in dashboard copy (Saving session overlay, Secrets card) replaced with 'persistent storage' for consistency with the Settings persistence wording; (3) Agent Marketplace empty-state banner — fixed false-positive 'No agents match the current filter' that appeared even when matching cards were visible. The counter relied on jQuery's :visible which polls computed visibility and returns 0 during initial render before CSS grid layout assigns offsetWidth/Height to the cards. Switched to an explicit counter incremented inside the show/hide loop — layout-agnostic, no race.
## 2026.05.15.11
- Fix: chip-generated SSH command now includes LC_ALL=en_US.utf8 prefix so tmux renders UTF-8 glyphs correctly even when ssh-attach.sh isn't engaged (Unraid strips command= options from root's authorized_keys).
## 2026.05.15.10
- Fix: UTF-8 glyph rendering over SSH — ssh-attach.sh now exports LANG=en_US.utf8 and LC_ALL=en_US.utf8 before invoking tmux. Unraid's /etc/profile doesn't export LANG, so SSH sessions arrive with LC_CTYPE=POSIX, which causes tmux to downgrade multi-byte UTF-8 glyphs (snowflake, sparkle, e-acute, box-drawing chars) to ASCII fallbacks. Fix is server-side so it applies to every SSH-attach path: chip-copied command, manual ssh, interactive picker. Regression test added.
## 2026.05.15.09
- Polish: SSH 'Command copied' chip — close button is now a 22x22 hit area with fa-times icon and a subtle hover background (was a bare × glyph with thin click target); chip background switches from --content-background-color (pure white in light theme) to --background-color (matches the drawer card surface); command box gets a hover border highlight to reinforce its clickability.
## 2026.05.15.08
- Simplify: SSH key icon now copies the full connect command to clipboard and shows a chip with a preview ('Command copied — Paste it into your local terminal to connect'). Drops the ssh:// browser-launch path entirely (too fragile across browser/OS combos — Chrome on Windows refuses embedded user@ credentials, Edge opens a blank tab) and the full SSH Client Setup modal that went with it. Chip auto-dismisses after 12 s. Spec updated to reflect clipboard-only v1; ssh:// launch deferred.
## 2026.05.15.07
- Fix: SSH 'has key' check is now server-scoped, not per-browser — every browser pointed at the same Unraid box sees the SSH launch button as soon as ANY key is registered. Also fixes two latent bugs in the same feature: (a) addKey's duplicate check searched authorized_keys for the SHA256 fingerprint string (which lives only in the sidecar) and silently allowed duplicate lines; (b) removeKey did the same and left removed keys valid on the server. Both now use the sidecar's pubkey content correctly. Drops the now-unused aicli_ssh_key_fp cookie. Adds three regression-guard tests.
## 2026.05.15.06
- Fix: SSH chip + setup modal button styling — wrap both containers in className=unapi (Unraid's button selectors use :where(:not(.unapi *)) — an official escape hatch); drop the heavy !important reset, keep only a minimal UA-defaults reset and the per-element styling. Close/tab/copy/launch buttons now render flat as designed instead of inheriting Unraid's orange uppercase pill style.
## 2026.05.15.05
- Fix: SSH launch uses programmatic anchor click instead of hidden iframe — bypasses Chrome's embedded-credentials block on subresource URLs containing 'user@' userinfo. Top-level navigation to ssh:// hands off to the OS handler without navigating the page or leaving a blank tab.
## 2026.05.15.04
- Fix: SSH launch uses hidden iframe (no blank tab); button CSS uses !important to defeat Unraid global button overrides
## 2026.05.15.03
- Fix: resume GUID sync on Ctrl-C exit -- shell post-exit scan updates frozen_chat_id and durable resume file; PHP discoverLatestSessionId gains claude-code filesystem implementation
## 2026.05.15.02
