## 2026.05.15.01
- Fix: SSH modal iframe navigation — add link.target=_blank so ssh:// click stays in new context (previous page never navigates/unmounts React); scoped CSS all:unset resets Unraid global button overrides inside .aicli-ssh-setup so close/tab/copy buttons render correctly
## 2026.05.14.18
- Fix: SSH chip + setup modal — use Unraid CSS variables (var(--background-color), var(--orange), var(--border-color) etc.) instead of hardcoded dark green; chip adapts to light/dark theme; modal matches settings-page card style (gray header bar, orange underline tabs, white panel, dark command blocks); remove setSshSetupOpen from 8s timer so modal survives chip auto-close
## 2026.05.14.17
- Feat: SSH setup overlay on terminal tab — 'Set up SSH client' link in launch chip opens modal with OS-specific handler registration steps (Windows Terminal / iTerm2 / xdg); copy command now includes full tmux attach-session command
## 2026.05.14.16
- Fix: SSH chip username normalization + overflow + card size consistency. checkSshEnabled returns normalized user (empty/'0'-&gt;root via PHP empty()); AICliAgentsTerminal uses dedicated sshUser state. Card is fixed 248px width; copy row uses flex ellipsis truncation so long myunraid.net hostnames clip cleanly.
## 2026.05.14.15
- Feat: SSH fallback chip + global client error handler. SSH chip now shows an 8s informational card with a copy-command fallback when no SSH client is registered (browser cannot throw a catchable error for unregistered protocols). Global window.onerror + unhandledrejection handlers log to new log_client_error AJAX endpoint (server-side LogService) and swal-toast genuine rejections while suppressing network noise.
## 2026.05.14.14
- Fix: home mount race conditions and fringe cases. (1) ensureHomeMounted serializes concurrent callers with per-user flock. (2) isHomeMountHealthy verifies genuine overlay entry, stale mounts rebuilt. (3) getUserStatePath logs WARN when mount unavailable. (4) mount_stack.sh loop-device failure hard-fails instead of continue.
