## 2026.05.14.03
- Feat: SSH session copy icon in drawer toggle tab (fa-key when SSH enabled), SSH key setup help overlay with OS-specific key-gen instructions, fix xterm resize-timing dots on tab switch
## 2026.05.14.02
- Feat: SSH launch links (#747) — SshKeyService + SshHandler + ssh-attach.sh + session chip in DrawerPanel + SSH Keys card in Settings. Fix: StorageHandler pipe deadlock (#341 findmnt). Fix: consolidate guard ordering (#342). Tests: SshKeyServiceTest.php.
## 2026.05.14.01
- Feat: static-analysis gating — PHPStan (L1.5) + ESLint (L1.6) wired into regress.sh (#148 #149). Fix 9 PHPStan findings (treat treatPhpDocTypesAsCertain:false + 6 dead-code / redundant checks); fix 4 ESLint errors (3 unused vars in test specs, DrawerPanel useState order). Zero findings on both gates. (v2026.05.14.01)
## 2026.05.13.11
- Fix mobile card overhang -- root cause was the grid not the card. av2-grid defaults to repeat auto-fill minmax 460px 1fr and aicli-config-grid to minmax 400px 1fr -- at any sub-460px or sub-400px viewport the grid track is wider than the viewport and cards bleed off the right edge, which is exactly what the 2026-05-14 screenshot showed -- ARGS chip and version badge both clipped. Mobile override collapses both grids to a single minmax 0 1fr column so each card fills the viewport width minus container padding. Plus max-width 100% min-width 0 box-sizing border-box on av2-card and aicli-card belt-and-braces so an oversized child can never re-introduce the overhang, and the state-stripe before bar narrows from 4px to 3px on mobile to reclaim a sliver of head-row width. Cards now fit cleanly with badge anchored top-right and all 5 chips visible in a single row. Spec MOBILE_RESPONSIVE.md updated to call out the grid as the root cause, regression guard testMobileResponsiveAssertions extended to assert the av2-grid + aicli-config-grid mobile collapse.
## 2026.05.13.10
- Fix v? badge UX glitch during in-flight installs/upgrades. InstallerService::installAgent was eager-clearing the saved agent version at the top of the install -- the old D-328 behaviour -- so any concurrent page render during the install window fell back to the 0.0.0 sentinel and showed v? on the Store card badge. Repro the user hit -- two agents upgrading in parallel, the faster one completes and the page refreshes while the slower is still baking, the slower badge renders v?. Fix -- drop the eager removeVersion call. saveVersion at the end of the success path atomically replaces the old version with the new one. Bonus -- a failed install now preserves the prior saved version so the user keeps a working previous install while the install-status panel surfaces the failure separately, instead of being left with v? next to a perfectly-fine agent. New regression guard testInstallerServicePreservesSavedVersionDuringInstall asserts no AgentRegistry::removeVersion call in the installAgent body up to the success-path saveVersion.
## 2026.05.13.09
- Mobile card layout revision -- keep desktop 3-column head grid icon then title-desc then badge top-right, just shrink it into the mobile viewport instead of restacking the badge onto its own full-width row. Earlier v...08 attempt stretched the badge across the card which looked bad per user feedback. New mobile head -- grid-template-columns 40px minmax 0 1fr auto so the middle column compresses while the badge stays anchored in column 3. Title shrinks to 15px nowrap-ellipsis at one line, desc to 11px 2-line clamp, icon to 40 by 40, badge font and dot smaller. Chips also tightened -- av2-strip now flex-wrap nowrap with av2-chip flex 1 1 0 so all 5 share a single row instead of ARGS wrapping alone to a third row. Chip label 9.5px tight letter-spacing. Health pill stays compact 8px so the badge stack does not grow. Regression guard testMobileResponsiveAssertions updated -- now asserts grid-template-columns 40px minmax 0 1fr auto plus av2-strip flex-wrap nowrap instead of the reverted full-width badge layout. Spec MOBILE_RESPONSIVE.md updated to record the revision and the reason.
## 2026.05.13.08
- Mobile responsive UX plus Unraid 7.3.0 log-noise filter. Three reports against v...06 on iPhone Safari -- Settings sub-tab strip overflows right and clips Debug Console, Agent Store cards too big in portrait so version badge and TERMINAL chip and UNINSTALL button are clipped, drawer toggle off-screen in mobile landscape and not touch-draggable. Plus the debug log was flooding with Unraid 7.3.0 ReferenceError Can not find variable codeAZ at webGui dynamix.js -- upstream Lime Tech regression in the minified bundle. ManagerStyles.php gains a single 600px max-width media query block -- tab strip becomes overflow-x auto, av2-head re-stacks as icon-title row plus badge full-width row so the badge cannot be clipped, av2-chip wraps to ~3 per row with full labels visible, av2-foot stacks meta over a 50-50 button row. DrawerPanel.tsx -- the toggle drag handler switches from MouseEvent to PointerEvent so mouse and touch and pen all drive the same code path, touchAction none on the handle suppresses iOS scroll-gesture interception, removed preventDefault so a non-drag tap still fires the synthetic click, added orientationchange listener and a setTabY clamp on every measure plus on initial useState construction so a portrait-saved tabY cannot leave the toggle off-screen in landscape. CommonLogging.php window.onerror now skips errors sourced from webGui plus cross-origin opaque url empty -- full detail still goes to the browser console so DevTools-armed devs see everything, only the upstream log POST is suppressed. New spec docs MOBILE_RESPONSIVE.md plus regression guard testMobileResponsiveAssertions covers all four wirings. 7.3.0 broader audit -- smoke 119 plus L4 playbook pass clean on 7.3.0 kernel 6.18.29, codeAZ in dynamix.js is the only 7.3.0 anomaly observed and is filtered.
## 2026.05.13.07
- WP #748 J migration audit + halt-aware Re-install fix. Audited the two upgrade paths to J -- current SquashFS users multi-layer and pre-SquashFS Btrfs/raw-folder users via migrate-btrfs-to-squashfs.sh that the PLG INLINE has been firing for many releases. Both land in working states on plugin upgrade with zero administrator action -- multi-layer mounts unchanged, boot-integrity sweep correctly classifies multi-layer-but-manifest-matching as healthy so no false-positive pill, and the J consolidate collapse kicks in lazily on the first per-agent install/upgrade post-upgrade. No PLG INLINE change. Documented both paths plus the deliberate no-forced-collapse choice (Fix #1 hazard) in STORAGE_DURABILITY_SUPERVISOR.md. Real gap found and fixed: Re-install on a halted+corrupt agent failed because InstallerService::installAgent calls ensureAgentMounted which runs mount_stack.sh in strict mode which exits 1 for any non-healthy classification, blocking the install. av2RepairAgent reinstall now calls clear_halt as a synchronous idempotent precursor so a single click recovers a halted+corrupt agent end-to-end. Restore path also auto-clears the halt after a successful restore_from_sibling. Both via a new _av2ClearHaltIdempotent helper.
## 2026.05.13.06
- WP #748 J Phase B follow-ups a b c -- storage-health surfaced on the Agent Store card. a Health pill rendered inside the av2-badge stack when an installed agent has a non-healthy boot-integrity state or is halted -- PHP-rendered at page-load, no AJAX round-trip. b Contextual Restore Re-install Clear-halt buttons in the av2-foot. Restore calls restore_from_sibling when SAFE_BACKUP siblings exist. Re-install calls installVersionAgent at latest of current channel for sibling-less corrupt or missing states which under J re-bakes the agent to a single fresh _consolidated_ layer. Clear-halt calls the clear_halt action. New av2-btn.warn amber CSS variant plus JS handlers av2RepairAgent and av2ClearAgentHalt. c Boot-integrity banner becomes navigational for agent entities -- emits Show on Agent Store deep-link buttons that switch tabs, scroll the affected card into view, and pulse an amber outline. Home entities keep the in-banner Restore-from-sibling card. New regression guard testWp748JPhaseBStoreCardHealthSurfacing covers all three. Spec STORAGE_DURABILITY_SUPERVISOR.md updated. Global CLAUDE.md gained a do-not-cut-scope rule.
## 2026.05.13.05
- WP #748 J Phase B -- Storage tab redesign. Under single-layer-per-agent the per-agent storage cards were vestigial: layer count always 1, dirty upper always 0, Persist Now / Consolidate Now meaningless. Phase B strips the 'SquashFS Agent Storage' section from the Storage tab entirely, removes renderAgentStats and its NchanSubscribers feed, and surfaces the per-agent Flash footprint inline in the Store card foot alongside the source label -- PHP-rendered at page-load, e.g. 'npm · @anthropic-ai/claude-code · 50 MB'. No JS poll, no render flicker. Boot-integrity banner stays on the Storage tab and remains the surface for Restore-from-sibling / clear-halt on a halted entity. Deferred to a future polish: health pill near the version badge, contextual Repair/Clear-halt buttons on the Store card foot, and banner -- deep-link to the affected card. Spec updated: Phase A is shipped+verified, Phase B is this release, the three Store-card UI follow-ups are listed as not yet shipped.
## 2026.05.13.04
- WP #748 J Phase A backend -- single-layer-per-agent storage. StorageMountService::commitChanges now early-routes $type === 'agent' to self::consolidate, which bakes the merged mount view -- the post-install package -- as a single fresh _consolidated_ layer, atomically replaces the layer set via Fix #4a manifest-first ordering, and remounts with one lowerdir. Old layers are deleted by consolidate_layers.sh. One layer per agent, no delta accumulation, no later consolidate threshold. The post-bake layer-count threshold consolidate is now gated on $type === 'home' so agents structurally never trip it. Supervisor scheduled-bake and dirty-pressure loops are now home-only -- agent uppers should always be empty outside an install, and if dirt ever appears the supervisor must NOT paper over it by enqueueing a delta-bake. Migration is lazy: existing multi-layer agents collapse on next install/upgrade. New regression guards testWp748JCommitChangesAgentRoutesToConsolidate and testWp748JSupervisorBakeLoopsSkipAgents. Spec updated: docs/specs/STORAGE_DURABILITY_SUPERVISOR.md status table flips J to In progress and the new section J -- implementation 2026-05-13 documents the routing, migration, and Phase B UI redesign that follows.
## 2026.05.13.03
- Port the working-tree classifier into publish-factory.php so the bare publish auto-routes too, not just the publish-and-deploy wrapper. Extracted to a shared lib-classify.php with lc_classifyChanges + lc_commitOnlyFlow, plus a --force-publish override. ui-build/tests and .shellcheckrc are now classified non-functional. Smoke assertion 119 for Bug #761 now mounts the agent overlay first via ensureAgentMounted -- which also exercises the stale-mount detector -- then verifies the /usr/local/bin proxy resolves and runs claude --version without a module-not-found error, instead of skipping when the lazy mount is absent.
## 2026.05.13.02
- Fix Bug #761 — agent proxy wrapper hardcoded a stale cli.js entry point. runtime.sh create_proxy: point claude at the native bin/claude.exe (claude-code 2.1.x dropped cli.js), and make every proxy self-heal — if the baked entry path is gone, re-resolve it from the package json bin field at runtime so in-place agent restructures do not ENOENT the wrapper. New L3 smoke assertion 119: for each mounted agent, the /usr/local/bin proxy resolves and runs without a module-not-found error. Also: testWp748PruneScriptsNeverTouchMigrationOrBackupContent now skips the PLG CHANGES changelog block (it scans prune/consolidate logic, not human prose — the v...01 changelog line tripped a false positive across deterministic ... and ... save-restore).
## 2026.05.13.01
- Fix Bug #706 / Feature #702 — un-block and de-stale the L4 Playwright e2e suite. storageState.json auth captured (one-time codegen). install.spec picker tests now intercept+abort the install_agent request (no server mutation, deterministic) and are un-skipped. uc-coverage UC#617 passes a real csrf_token to list_active_installs (the dispatcher CSRF-gates every action) and is un-skipped. upgrade-ux #29/#63 rewritten for the 2026 redesign where an in-flight upgrade no longer blocks interaction — assert the upgrading tag + the holding overlay via new data-testids. Added data-testid attrs to WorkspaceBrowser / DrawerPanel / AICliAgentsTerminal and a seedWorkspace fixture (workspaces.json backup-restore). Full e2e suite 22/22 green. Docs: AGENT_UPGRADE_UX.md and PLAYWRIGHT_E2E.md updated to current state.
## 2026.05.12.07
- Fix: supervisor single-instance lock (Bug #757). Dedicated /var/run/aicli-supervisor.lock as the mutex (replaces the inode-churning flock-on-pidfile); flock -w 10 at the top of _do_start, losers exit 0; close the lock fd in the heartbeat subshell AND in the spawned commit_stack.sh/consolidate_layers.sh work children (the deadlock the reverted v...04 attempt hit); pidfile written plainly; orphan reaper recast as an orphan-CHILD reaper (PPid==1, path-anchored). Zero change to SupervisorService.php. +5 testBug757* RegressionGuards, smoke A118 (4 concurrent starts converge to one tree), A70/A97/A748-plg test reworded. Cross-checked vs an independent Gemini 2.5 Pro design pass. Docs: SUPERVISOR_SINGLE_INSTANCE.md + STORAGE_DURABILITY_SUPERVISOR.md updated.
## 2026.05.12.06
- Fix Bug #716 — concurrent agent bakes race during upgrade. Two bakes of the same agent entity could run concurrently during an upgrade (the install bake from InstallerService::installAgent -&gt; StorageMountService::commitChanges, plus a redundant SupervisorService::enqueue('agent', ..., 'bake', 'agent_install', 0) in install-bg.php and/or the supervisor's dirty-pressure watchdog), and the second bake's post-bake remount/active-sessions check raced the first remount -&gt; 'Install Failed (Bake Error)' on a normal agent upgrade. Fix: (a) commit_stack.sh now takes a per-entity flock (/var/run/aicli-bake-&lt;type&gt;-&lt;id&gt;.lock, non-blocking) at the top of the bake, held through the bake + remount; a concurrent bake for the same entity logs 'bake_skipped_concurrent' and exits 0 cleanly (its data is already in the ZRAM upper and gets captured by the in-progress bake); a crashed bake's lock auto-releases when the kernel closes the fd, so no deadlock. (b) removed the redundant agent_install bake enqueue from install-bg.php — InstallerService::installAgent already runs commit_stack.sh synchronously via commitChanges. +2 RegressionGuards.
## 2026.05.12.05
- WP #748 — Phase 1 (Flash-wear reduction) + robustness fixes #1 and #4a; #4b deferred. (Phase 1) bake_schedule_minutes 30-&gt;120, dirty thresholds soft/hard/critical 512/1024/2048 -&gt; 1024/2048/4096, consolidate threshold 15-&gt;30 (cfg-migrated on upgrade only if still at the old default); commit_stack.sh + consolidate_layers.sh prune .npm, .bun/install, .gemini/tmp, .claude/cache|shell-snapshots|telemetry from home overlays (caches/temp/telemetry only — never migrated/backup content); skip the bake when the ZRAM upper is empty after pruning; workspace close writes a wants-bake flag instead of an immediate bake. (Fix #1) the upgrade-time wear-cleanup consolidate-enqueue removed from the PLG INLINE — it ran a consolidate during the chaotic post-deploy window and got SIGTERM'd mid-flight, corrupting a test box's manifest; the cache junk is shed at the next natural consolidate instead. (Fix #4a) consolidate_layers.sh now updates the layer manifest BEFORE deleting old layer files, so a mid-flight SIGTERM leaves untracked-but-not-missing layers (reconcile recovers them, no halt) instead of a corrupt_layers halt. (Fix #4b — orphan-supervisor-reaping race / Bug #513) deferred: the naive flock guard deadlocks the supervisor stop/start cycle (forked children inherit the lock fd); needs a dedicated design pass. Smoke #48's supervisor-up timeout bumped 10-&gt;30s as a band-aid for that pre-existing flake. +RegressionGuards.
## 2026.05.12.04
- WP #748 — robustness follow-up to Phase 1. (Fix #1) reverted the upgrade-time wear-cleanup consolidate-enqueue from the PLG INLINE — it ran a consolidate during the chaotic post-deploy window and got SIGTERM'd mid-flight, after deleting the old layer files but before updating the manifest, corrupting a test box's manifest; the cache junk is shed at the next natural consolidate instead (consolidate_layers.sh has the home-overlay prune from Phase 1 F). (Fix #4a) consolidate_layers.sh now updates the layer manifest BEFORE deleting the old layer files, so a mid-flight SIGTERM leaves untracked-but-not-missing layers (reconcile recovers them, no halt) instead of a corrupt_layers halt. (Fix #4b) aicli-supervisor.sh: a flock single-instance guard at the very top of _do_start (losers exit 0 cleanly instead of the orphan-reaping free-for-all that was losing the pidfile and failing smoke #48) plus an EXIT/TERM/INT trap that kills the supervisor's children (heartbeat loop, work child, process group). The Phase-1 cfg-migration block (bumps cadence defaults only if still at the old default) is retained. +3 RegressionGuards.
## 2026.05.12.03
- WP #748 Phase 1 — reduce storage supervisor Flash-write wear. (A/B/C) cadence defaults: bake_schedule_minutes 30-&gt;120, dirty_threshold soft/hard/critical_mb 512/1024/2048 -&gt; 1024/2048/4096, consolidate_layer_threshold_flash 15-&gt;30; the PLG INLINE migrates these in an existing .cfg only if it is still at the old default (user-customised values left alone). (H) skip the bake when the ZRAM upper is empty after pruning. (F) commit_stack.sh + consolidate_layers.sh now prune .npm, .bun/install, .gemini/tmp, .claude/cache|shell-snapshots|telemetry from home overlays (caches/temp/telemetry only — never snap_*, migrated_legacy_data, *backup*, SAFE_BACKUP); the PLG INLINE enqueues a home consolidate on upgrade so existing installs shed the accumulated junk. (E) workspace close writes a wants-bake flag instead of enqueuing an immediate bake; the supervisor bakes it on the next tick. +7 RegressionGuards. J/D/I are Phase 2.
## 2026.05.12.02
- Agent launch resilience + version-check on install. (A) aicli-shell.sh now re-resolves the agent binary (primary then binary_fallback, by existence) on every relaunch iteration instead of using the path frozen at session start — fixes claude-code/qwen-code sessions getting stranded when an in-place agent upgrade swaps the legacy cli.js entry point for a native binary (Claude Code 2.1.x ships bin/claude.exe). TerminalService passes the raw binary + binary_fallback paths through to the shell as BINARY_PRIMARY/BINARY_FALLBACK. (B) PLG INLINE now fires version-check-bg.php in the background on every install/upgrade so Store cards for uninstalled agents show their available version without a manual 'Check for Updates'. New spec docs/specs/AGENT_LAUNCH_RESILIENCE.md; 2 new RegressionGuards.
## 2026.05.12.01
- Flash durability: AtomicWriteService::write now forces a filesystem sync (sync -f) after any write under /boot/ — covers secrets.cfg, the plugin .cfg, versions.json, layer_manifest.json, secrets/ws_*.cfg — so those writes survive an abrupt reboot instead of sitting in the FAT32 page cache. Pairs with publish-and-deploy.php now running 'sync -f /boot' after 'plugin install'. No other behaviour change.
## 2026.05.11.13
- Re-publish to exercise the hardened deploy path (publish-and-deploy now scp's the local .plg to /tmp/plugins/ and verifies the new version landed in both the marker AND /boot/config/plugins/ — was only checking the marker, which let the Flash copy drift stale across releases). No plugin code change.
## 2026.05.11.12
- Harden L4 step 7 (channel-persist): reload up to 3x, poll ~6s/attempt + longer cfg-settle wait. The radio.checked-after-reload check was flaking under heavy load (a long session of back-to-back publishes makes the test box slow to settle the cfg write). Pre-existing L4-drift class (WP #702); unrelated to WP #736. No product code changed.
