- Re-publish (no code change) — smoke A48 supervisor-tick flaked again on the v...08 run (pre-existing Bug #513-class orphan-reaping race; unrelated to the schema-secrets clear fix). Worth hardening A48 separately.
## 2026.05.11.08
- Fix: clearing a schema secret in the ENVS panel now actually clears it (WP #736 follow-up)
- Before: the schema-secrets form's JS skipped any empty (or '••••••••') field
- before POSTing, and save_vault only ever added/updated keys present in the POST
- — no delete path. So clearing the value of e.g. GEMINI_API_KEY and clicking
- Save was a silent no-op; the masked dots reappeared on refresh because the value
- was unchanged.
- Now:
- av2SaveSecrets sends EVERY field except those still showing the masked
- '••••••••' placeholder (= set + untouched → server keeps it). An empty value
- is sent verbatim and means 'the user cleared this field'. Also tightened the
- response handling (checks r.status === 'ok') and added hot-apply
- (av2HotApplyAgent) so a key change restarts the agent's running sessions —
- consistent with the free-form Variables/Secrets saves.
- UtilityHandler::saveVault: a submitted empty value → unset() the key (delete
- from secrets.cfg) instead of writing it. Applies to both the literal-name and
- the {PLACEHOLDER}_API_KEY branches. The merge still preserves sibling agents'
- keys (saving one agent's form only touches that agent's fields).
- Smoke A117: plant a probe key + a sentinel sibling in secrets.cfg, POST
- save_vault with the probe = '' , assert the probe is deleted and the sibling
- survives; snapshots + restores the file.
- Live box: scrubbed the stale GEMINI_API_KEY=e2e-... artifact from secrets.cfg
- (left by the old destructive L4 step) — the field now renders empty so the
- real key can be entered.
- PHPUnit 247, smoke +A117, vitest 13.
