## 2026.05.11.01
- Feat: env vars + secrets — agent + workspace tiers, manifest-seeded defaults, hot-apply (WP #736)
- Backend half of the unified env/secrets surface. UI wiring (Store-card free-form Secrets/Variables sub-sections + workspace-drawer per-key inherit/override) lands in a follow-up; the new EnvHandler endpoints are wired and tested ready for that consumer.
- Adds:
- SecretService (agent + workspace, 600/700 perms, masking-on-read), EnvService (agent + workspace, 5-tier buildEffectiveEnv merge, manifest-seeded defaults with sidecar-tracked user deletions), EnvHandler (9 actions).
- AgentRegistry manifest: rename 'secrets' =&gt; 'default_secrets' (back-compat shim in av2_secrets_schema reads either); add 'default_envs' as a parallel field for general-env seeding; first ship: gemini-cli =&gt; GEMINI_CLI_ENABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=false.
- Seed pipeline: InstallerService::installAgent calls EnvService::seedAgentDefaults after commitChanges; PLG INLINE upgrade block calls seedAllInstalledAgentDefaults (additive only, never overwrites a user value, never auto-removes, honours user deletions via the seeded sidecar).
- Launch-time injection: TerminalService::startTerminal and aicli-shell.sh both merge via EnvService::buildEffectiveEnv (single source of truth). Tier order, later wins per key: source.env &lt; secrets.cfg &lt; workspace secrets &lt; agent envs &lt; workspace envs. Closes the latent dead-write gap where secrets.cfg was written by saveVault but never sourced at launch (verified absent in v2026.05.10.02).
- Hot-apply: new _aicli_load_envs helper in aicli-shell.sh runs per loop iteration — diffs against $AICLI_EXPORTED_KEYS_FILE, unsets removed keys, re-exports the current set. Reuses the existing agent_signal_reload sentinel mechanism (UI piece in the follow-up commit).
- Tests:
- EnvServiceTest (15 cases): validateKey shape + reserved-name + reserved-prefix rejection; sanitiseValue strips control chars + caps length; validateMap drops bad keys but keeps good ones; agent + workspace round-trips; workspace per-key delta save unlinks empty file; effective-merge workspace-beats-agent; seed four outcomes (skip-existing-user, skip-already-seeded, add-new, no-default-envs noop).
- SecretServiceTest (7 cases): workspace round-trip; 600 file perms + 700 dir perms; masking guard (no value leaks through getXForUI — serialised + asserted-not-contains); empty-map unlinks file; free-form-keys sidecar round-trip + dedup + 600 perms.
- RegressionGuardsTest (5 new): EnvHandler::actions() pinned; TerminalService calls buildEffectiveEnv; aicli-shell wires both the startup call AND _aicli_load_envs in the loop; default_secrets rename — no non-comment 'secrets' =&gt; declarations remain; gemini-cli ships GEMINI_CLI_ENABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=false.
- Existing AgentRegistryTest + ConfigTest updated to read default_secrets ?? secrets (back-compat).
- Smoke A109-A116 (8 new): per-tier x per-class round-trips with the masking guard, 5-tier merge precedence, seed honour-user-deletion, vault-injection regression (closes dead-write), validateKey reservation pinning.
- Spec: docs/specs/ENV_AND_SECRETS_TIERS.md (committed dd7e983).
## 2026.05.10.02
- Fix L4 playbook drift (WP #702): step 13 settings-page-renders no longer scans body.textContent for 'Fatal error|Parse error|Uncaught' — that false-positives on the plugin's own #log-content debug-log viewer echoing historical log lines; now positively asserts page chrome rendered (.av2-card count + .aicli-tabs) and detects a real PHP fatal via its &lt;b&gt;Fatal error&lt;/b&gt; markup element. Step 7 channel-persist now polls the beta radio for up to 3s after reload instead of reading once (cfg-write/cache lag flaked it when L4 ran straight after publish/deploy/smoke). tests/ui_e2e_playbook.md steps 7 &amp; 13 updated to match. Test-only change; plugin runtime unchanged.
## 2026.05.10.01
- Fix: ZRAM init robustness — capability probe replaces lsmod/modprobe-fatal (built-in zram kernels now work), XFS fallback when kernel lacks ext4-on-block-device support. Adds RegressionGuardsTest::testZramInitProbesCapabilityNotModprobeSuccess. Docs: ZRAM_INIT_ROBUSTNESS spec; CLAUDE.md custom-field note updated (Bug type now carries canonical_spec). Tracks #719 / GitHub issue #5.
## 2026.05.08.08
- Fix recoverMissingVersions: was checking only binary-path existence (which requires the agent overlay to be MOUNTED), missed every lazy-mounted agent. Now mirrors getRegistry's is_installed gate (binExists OR sqshExists) so unmounted-but-installed agents get mounted+discovered+recovered.
## 2026.05.08.07
- Make recoverMissingVersions synchronous in PLG INLINE for real this time — previous edit got lost in version-bump race.
## 2026.05.08.06
- Make recoverMissingVersions synchronous in PLG INLINE so the post-install state-invariant smoke (A108) doesn't race against the backfill. Per-agent mount+unmount runs in series; takes a few seconds total per upgrade.
## 2026.05.08.05
- Fix version display + bake error visibility. Reverts per-getRegistry mount (memory-exhausting). New AgentRegistry::recoverMissingVersions runs ONCE per upgrade via PLG INLINE: mount-on-demand for sentinel-version installed agents + write real semver to versions.json. Smoke A108 added: post-install state invariant catches both v? and Install-Failed markers.
## 2026.05.08.04
- Fix version display bug: AgentRegistry::getRegistry's lazy version-recovery now calls StorageMountService::ensureAgentMounted before discoverVersion. 10 of 11 installed agents were stuck at 0.0.0 because their .sqsh layers existed but the agent overlay wasn't mounted (lazy-mount only triggers on session open). discoverVersion's npm path reads node_modules/&lt;pkg&gt;/package.json from the unmounted overlay path, returns 'unknown', registry kept 0.0.0 forever. Smoke A108 added: post-install state invariant — every is_installed=1 agent must have a real semver version + no Failed/Error markers in install-status.
## 2026.05.08.03
- Final round: Bug 710 closed (form-nesting fix — outer aicli-settings-form was wrapping store/storage/debug tabs, browsers flatten nested forms so inner Save buttons posted to action=save instead of save_vault). 18 L4 specs pass, 4 skipped with Bug 706 refs. L4 default flipped to strict — pass --warn-l4 to opt out. storageState cookie-freshness probe in run-l4.sh.
## 2026.05.08.02
- Bug 710 fix: close aicli-settings-form at end of ManagerConfigTab.php (was at end of ManagerLogTab, wrapping all tabs). Browsers flatten nested forms — inner secrets/args/tmux forms were posting to action=save not their own handlers. Closing the outer form earlier keeps each tab's inner forms independent. Also adds storageState cookie-freshness probe to run-l4.sh; parks WP 705 vek-sync.
