## 2026.05.06.12
- Fix OP #428: smoke 55/56 leaked work + zram_upper directory trees that StorageMetricsService::getStorageStats fallback rendered as phantom OFFLINE home cards. v10 cleanup-phantoms only scanned the manifest. Three fixes: smoke 55/56 teardown rm -rf's work + zram trees plus a belt-and-braces sweep of smokeuser5[56]* leftovers; _do_cleanup_phantoms extended to scan /tmp/.../work/ and /tmp/.../zram_upper/{homes,agents} for smoke-namespaced entries (strict pattern match, refuses to touch real-looking user names); new smoke 65 seeds one fake and one real entry, runs cleanup-phantoms, asserts only the fake is pruned. Live server work + zram dirs cleaned manually before publish.
## 2026.05.06.11
- Fix upgrade-handoff race: cleanup.sh now stops the old supervisor at the top of pre-eviction work before persistence and process kills (poll 15s for clean exit, SIGKILL fallback). PLG INLINE block adds a defensive stop-and-wait before the setsid launch covering fresh-install and lazy-backstop respawn cases. Without this fix the new supervisor saw the old PID still alive on its first _pidfile_valid call and bailed with 'Another supervisor instance is running' — leaving the box without a supervisor until the next page load. Smoke 63 statically asserts cleanup.sh wiring; smoke 64 asserts the PLG defensive block. Reported by John during today's diagnostics.
## 2026.05.06.10
- Fix cleanup-phantoms exit-vs-return regression. The function used exit 0 causing it to terminate the whole supervisor when called from the start path. Changed to return 0/1 throughout so the inline call from start proceeds to _do_start. The cleanup-phantoms subcommand path adds exit after the return.
## 2026.05.06.09
- Fix OP #419 and OP #420: FD 4 boot hang plus supervisor phantom-smoke reconcile spam. PLG: add 4&gt;&amp;- to both background launchers so PHP installer exits at boot (rc.local). SupervisorService::start: same 4&gt;&amp;- flag for future-proof PHP-FPM path. Supervisor: sanitise rate_key slashes before using as filename so rate-limit files are always written (sub-bug B). Supervisor: warn on failed rate-limit file write instead of swallowing silently. LayerManifestService: add removeEntity and removeEntitiesMatching methods. Supervisor: cleanup-phantoms subcommand prunes smoke-test entity IDs from manifest, also runs on every supervisor start. smoke.sh: _teardown_smoke_state helper registered via trap plus smokes 60-62.
## 2026.05.06.08
- Re-deploy of v2026.05.06.07 (OP #418 classify-path.sh quote-stripping fix). The previous deploy attempt failed at plugin check because /var/log/plugins/unraid-aicliagents.plg symlink was missing post-array-stop; symlink restored manually before this retry.
## 2026.05.06.07
- Fix OP #418: classify-path.sh awk pool-detection. Unraid disks.ini section headers are quoted ([cache], [storage] with literal double-quotes inside the brackets); the awk gsub stripped only [ and ] so pool names were emitted with quotes still attached. Bit-exact bash compare $MNT_NAME = $pool then never matched and pool paths fell through to unknown — broke graceful eviction of pool-resident sessions in stopping_array Scenario 3, caused JS-vs-hook divergence on ArrayStopWarning, and false-negatived Scenario 1 if a persist path was ever set to a pool. One character added to the gsub character class. Smoke 59 added as regression test. Verified end-to-end on the live test server: buggy gsub emits quoted name, fixed gsub emits bare name, classify-path.sh returns pool:cache for /mnt/cache/* under fixed code.
## 2026.05.06.06
- Phase 5 of Storage Durability Supervisor: legacy cleanup. Deletes tryRunPendingConsolidations() from StorageMountService (the synchronous drain method has zero callers since Phase 3.3 stripped them). Deletes manageSyncDaemon() and the per-user sync daemon (replaced by the supervisor; removed call sites in InitService, disks_mounted event, repair-plugin, install/uninstall cleanup, stop-plugin). Routes the three remaining legacy direct-mksquashfs sites through atomic_write_layer.sh: src/event/stopping (scenario 3 home bake), src/scripts/installer/cleanup.sh (pre-upgrade ZRAM bake), src/scripts/user/stop-plugin.sh (both home and agent bakes). These were emitting legacy _delta_&lt;epoch&gt; names and writing non-atomically — closing the residue of findings E/F/I on the shutdown/upgrade paths and the agent_storage_path grep on findings B/C. migrate-btrfs-to-squashfs.sh now sources resolve_paths.sh and uses agent_persist_path/home_persist_path helpers instead of inline cfg greps (closes finding K). No backwards-compat shims, no // removed comments, no empty wrappers. Spec status flipped to Complete with migration history table appended. Audit greps clean: zero tryRunPendingConsolidations refs, zero direct cfg key greps in scripts, zero direct mksquashfs invocations outside atomic_write_layer/migrate-btrfs. Static-analysis smoke 53 still green.
## 2026.05.06.05
- Smoke fixes for Phase 4b: heredoc-rewrite of dirty-pressure test (escaping bug — single-quoted source path was passing literal string to source instead of expanding the variable), guard_path-friendly persist paths in mount_stack halt tests (/tmp/unraid-aicliagents/... not /tmp/...), removal of  ref that was unset without resolve_paths.sh. All 58 assertions verified green against live test server before this publish.
## 2026.05.06.04
- Fix supervisor daemon detachment over SSH-driven plugin install. Previous Phase 4b deploy completed install logic (plugin actually updated to v2026.05.06.03) but the SSH wrapper hung at session-exit because nohup+disown does not sever the controlling-TTY relationship over a remote PTY — the supervisors heartbeat loop kept SSH channel descriptors open and the wrapper SIGTERMed the session. Both launcher sites now wrap with setsid: the PLG post-install bash block (initial install/upgrade) and SupervisorService::start (lazy backstop respawn from PHP AJAX). setsid creates a new session ID for the child so it becomes a session leader with no controlling terminal — the canonical daemonisation pattern. Pattern saved to memory feedback_setsid_for_ssh_daemons.md for future SSH-launched daemons in this workspace.
## 2026.05.06.03
- Phase 4b of Storage Durability Supervisor: strict-mode boot integrity gate. mount_stack.sh now reads boot_integrity_strict (default 1) and exits 1 with a halt marker for any non-healthy state (legacy_unmanaged, path_drift, partial_loss, total_loss, corrupt_layers, host_mismatch). New HaltService owns all halt transitions with lifecycle log entries. Sidecar JSON at /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/supervisor/halts/&lt;type&gt;/&lt;id&gt;.json carries diagnostic context (expected/active/sibling counts, manifest path, recommended action) so the UI can render meaningful copy. New StorageHandler actions list_halts and clear_halt drive a page-level Storage Unavailable overlay (z-index 10002, single non-nested swal flow per memory) that blocks workspace interaction until every halt resolves. Per-state action buttons for restore_from_sibling, emergency mode, start fresh, host confirm. Cross-tab sync via localStorage. Skip mode (boot_integrity_strict=0) preserves Phase 4a warn behaviour as the rollback escape hatch. Smoke 55-58 cover strict-mode halt write, warn-mode passthrough, HaltService round-trip, list_halts shape. Also includes smoke 52 race fix: dirty-pressure test now uses a private mktemp queue dir so the live supervisor cannot consume the test fixture before grep. Closes finding A fully — non-healthy mount can no longer proceed silently.
## 2026.05.06.02
- Phase 4b of Storage Durability Supervisor: strict-mode boot integrity gate. mount_stack.sh now reads boot_integrity_strict (default 1) and exits 1 with a halt marker for any non-healthy state (legacy_unmanaged, path_drift, partial_loss, total_loss, corrupt_layers, host_mismatch). New HaltService owns all halt transitions with lifecycle log entries. Sidecar JSON at /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/supervisor/halts/&lt;type&gt;/&lt;id&gt;.json carries diagnostic context (expected/active/sibling counts, manifest path, recommended action) so the UI can render meaningful copy. New StorageHandler actions list_halts and clear_halt drive a page-level Storage Unavailable overlay (z-index 10002, single non-nested swal flow per memory) that blocks workspace interaction until every halt resolves. Per-state action buttons: legacy_unmanaged or path_drift -&gt; Restore from sibling (delegates to Phase 0 restore_from_sibling, then clear_halt); total_loss -&gt; Enter emergency mode or Start fresh (double-confirm WIPE); host_mismatch -&gt; Confirm this Flash belongs here. Cross-tab sync via localStorage so other open tabs unmount the overlay on resolution. Skip mode (boot_integrity_strict=0) preserves Phase 4a warn behaviour as the rollback escape hatch. Smoke 55-58 cover: strict mode exits 1 with halt sidecar; warn mode exits 0; HaltService round-trip; list_halts AJAX shape. Closes finding A fully — non-healthy mount can no longer proceed silently.
## 2026.05.06.01
- Phase 3 of Storage Durability Supervisor: long-running storage daemon. New aicli-supervisor.sh runs heartbeat (touch tick file every 5s) on a separate background loop from the work loop, so a slow mksquashfs cannot look like a wedge. Atomic JSON writes for both /var/run/aicli-supervisor.work.json and /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/supervisor.status.json. Reconcile op runs every tick (manifest-vs-disk, sha256, untracked recovery, orphan-tmp cleanup, halt+notify on missing/corrupt/drift). Bake and consolidate ops spawn child processes so the watchdog can probe child_pid; per-op-kind ceilings (delta_small 600s, delta_large 1800s, consolidate 3600s, consolidate_slow_usb 7200s); two consecutive consolidate kills auto-disable consolidation per entity until user resumes. Dirty-pressure watchdog (soft 512MB lz4 bake, hard 1GB warn, critical 2GB refuse-new-sessions). Schedule trigger as safety net (default 30 min). Flat-file priority queue at /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/supervisor/queue/ (priority&lt;epoch&lt;type&lt;id&lt;op.req, lex sort = priority order). New SupervisorService.php with isRunning/start/stop/getStatus/getTickAge/getWorkState/enqueue/isHalted/clearHalt/consolidateFailureCount/resetConsolidateFailures (PID validation against /proc/&lt;pid&gt;/cmdline so a recycled PID never gets killed by mistake). 13 new ConfigService settings keys with spec-defined defaults. AJAX handlers stripped of synchronous storage I/O: AICliAjax lazy backstop removed; gracefulClose enqueues priority-10 home bake and returns 'baking' immediately; install-bg enqueues priority-0 agent bake; StorageHandler persistAgent/consolidate/executeMigrate all delegate to supervisor; new get_supervisor_status AJAX action exposes work state + queue depth + dirty pressure. React isSyncing overlay polls get_supervisor_status every 2s and clears on idle+depth=0 or supervisor-gone after 10s — replaces the fixed 1500ms timeout that caused the original spinner-doesnt-clear bug. Plugin install starts supervisor via nohup+disown; lazy backstop in InitService::ensureInit respawns it on next page load if it died. events/stopping and the new events/stopping_array hook call supervisor flush --all --timeout=60 before SIGTERM, writing clean_shutdown_reached or shutdown_timeout_reached to lifecycle log. Static-analysis smoke 53 asserts zero commitChanges/consolidate/tryRunPendingConsolidations leaks in handlers. Smoke 47-54 cover lifecycle, queue, halts, watchdog, fast-spinner-clear. Closes findings G, H, plus the original spinner-doesnt-clear UX bug. Spec scenarios S0/S1/S2 implemented end-to-end.
## 2026.05.05.08
- Phase 0 of Storage Durability Supervisor: sibling-restore UI. New BootIntegrityService::findSiblingLayers and ::restoreFromSibling methods scan plugin-base sibling dirs (matching the same backup/migrated/old patterns the classifier uses), atomic-rename layer files into the active persist path with sha256 re-verify, and register each as kind=recovered in the manifest. New AJAX action restore_from_sibling in StorageHandler invokes the service and invalidates the boot-integrity status cache. The Phase 4a banner IIFE in ManagerStorageScripts is extended to render interactive recovery cards for legacy_unmanaged and path_drift states with a Restore button per entity (single non-nested swal, cross-tab broadcast on completion). discoverSiblings refactored onto a shared buildSiblingCandidateDirs helper so classifier and recovery-discovery cannot diverge. Smoke tests 45-46 added: a fixture sqsh dropped into SAFE_BACKUP is discovered, restored, manifest entry written with kind=recovered, lifecycle log records sibling_layer_restored. Closes Phase 0 of the migration plan and the canonical John recovery scenario.
## 2026.05.05.07
- Phase 0 of Storage Durability Supervisor: sibling-restore UI. New BootIntegrityService::findSiblingLayers and ::restoreFromSibling methods scan plugin-base sibling dirs (matching the same backup/migrated/old patterns the classifier uses), atomic-rename layer files into the active persist path with sha256 re-verify, and register each as kind=recovered in the manifest. New AJAX action restore_from_sibling in StorageHandler invokes the service and invalidates the boot-integrity status cache. The Phase 4a banner IIFE in ManagerStorageScripts is extended to render interactive recovery cards for legacy_unmanaged and path_drift states with a Restore button per entity (single non-nested swal, cross-tab broadcast on completion). discoverSiblings refactored onto a shared buildSiblingCandidateDirs helper so classifier and recovery-discovery cannot diverge. Smoke tests 45-46 added: a fixture sqsh dropped into SAFE_BACKUP is discovered, restored, manifest entry written with kind=recovered, lifecycle log records sibling_layer_restored. Closes Phase 0 of the migration plan and the canonical John recovery scenario.
## 2026.05.05.06
- SquashFS layer naming convention: switch new bakes to canonical type_id_kind_YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ.sqsh format. atomic_write_layer.sh emits dt-format names plus a collision guard (mv -n + pre-check + post-verify) that refuses to overwrite an existing target. mount_stack.sh switches to lexicographic sort across both legacy epoch and new dt formats; legacy 1xxxxxxxxx epochs from before 2025 lex-sort below new 2026+ dt strings, preserving chronological stack order during the migration. AgentRegistry::isInstalled regex and StorageMetricsService entity-discovery regex extended to recognise both formats. StorageMetricsService layer-stack sort now uses string compare on a unified timestamp key so cross-format sort is correct. Spec at docs/specs/STORAGE_DURABILITY_SUPERVISOR.md gains a Layer naming convention section under Component 2: format, uniqueness guarantees, lex=chrono invariant, migration coexistence with legacy names. boot_integrity.sh and BootIntegrityService.php were already glob-based and need no changes. Three legacy direct-mksquashfs sites (event/stopping, scripts/user/stop-plugin.sh, scripts/installer/cleanup.sh) still emit legacy _delta_&lt;epoch&gt; names and will be routed through atomic_write_layer in Phase 5.
## 2026.05.05.05
- Phase 4a of Storage Durability Supervisor: boot integrity check in warn mode. New BootIntegrityService classifies each entity into nine states. Sweep runs once per boot from InitService. Sibling-dir discovery picks up backup, BACKUP, migrated_legacy_data and other archive patterns. Non-healthy classifications fire Unraid notifications, rate-limited per entity-state per boot. New AJAX get_boot_integrity_status feeds a banner in the storage tab. mount_stack.sh sources boot_integrity.sh and tags the empty-glob branch with a categorized state. Warn mode only — no halt-and-ask gate yet, that ships with Phase 4b once we have production telemetry. Closes audit finding A in observability terms; reinforces M. Smoke 42-44 added. Spec at docs/specs/STORAGE_DURABILITY_SUPERVISOR.md.
## 2026.05.05.04
- Phase 2 of Storage Durability Supervisor: atomic layer writer. New atomic_write_layer.sh writes mksquashfs output to a sibling tempfile (leading-dot, invisible to mount discovery glob), fsyncs, sha256-verifies via RO mount + sample-read, then atomic renames. commit_stack.sh and consolidate_layers.sh now route all layer writes through it. consolidate_layers.sh additionally replaces the wildcard find-delete with an explicit per-file loop over a pre-bake OLD_LAYERS snapshot, so a concurrent bake during consolidate cannot be accidentally swept. Closes audit findings E (non-atomic mv), F (mksquashfs writes directly to final), and D (wildcard delete defended only by string equality). Smoke 39-41 added. Spec at docs/specs/STORAGE_DURABILITY_SUPERVISOR.md.
## 2026.05.05.03
- Phase 1 wiring of Storage Durability Supervisor: existing call sites now use StoragePathResolver and write LifecycleLogService entries on every storage transition. Closes audit findings B (installer/cleanup.sh used agent_storage_path for home bakes) and C (event/stopping had the same path-key confusion at the most durability-critical moment). StorageMountService also writes manifest entries (LayerManifestService::addLayer / replaceLayers) on every successful bake/consolidate. Behavior unchanged. Smoke 38 added to verify lifecycle.log grows and manifest registers entries on persist_home. Spec at docs/specs/STORAGE_DURABILITY_SUPERVISOR.md.
## 2026.05.05.02
- Fix Phase 1 autoloading: AICliAgentsManager.php now requires the three new services so php callers can reach them. Smoke test 36 was failing because StoragePathResolver was unloadable through the manager facade.
## 2026.05.05.01
- Phase 1 of Storage Durability Supervisor — new services LayerManifestService, StoragePathResolver, LifecycleLogService, plus resolve_paths.sh bash helper. No behavior change yet, no existing call sites wired. Spec at docs/specs/STORAGE_DURABILITY_SUPERVISOR.md.
## 2026.05.03.02
- Fix: guard_path now accepts custom Unraid pools. Previous narrow allowlist (/mnt/cache, /mnt/disk[0-9]+, /mnt/user only) silently rejected any user-named pool — /mnt/scratch_old, /mnt/cache_nvme, ZFS pools, etc. — with a misleading 'PERSIST_PATH outside allowed prefixes' error. Replaced with a deny-list against the four known-system tmpfs mounts (/mnt/disks, /mnt/remotes, /mnt/rootshare, /mnt/addons) plus a permissive /mnt/&lt;pool&gt;/&lt;sub&gt; accept. Adds RegressionGuardsTest::testGuardPathAcceptsCustomUnraidPools so the patterns cant silently re-narrow. UD-mounted real drives are still rejected by the static rule because their tmpfs parent silently re-appears on disconnect — runtime findmnt probe is a follow-up.
## 2026.05.03.01
- Fix: guard_path now accepts custom Unraid pools. Previous narrow allowlist (/mnt/cache, /mnt/disk[0-9]+, /mnt/user only) silently rejected any user-named pool — /mnt/scratch_old, /mnt/cache_nvme, ZFS pools, etc. — with a misleading 'PERSIST_PATH outside allowed prefixes' error. Replaced with a deny-list against the four known-system tmpfs mounts (/mnt/disks, /mnt/remotes, /mnt/rootshare, /mnt/addons) plus a permissive /mnt/&lt;pool&gt;/&lt;sub&gt; accept. Adds RegressionGuardsTest::testGuardPathAcceptsCustomUnraidPools so the patterns cant silently re-narrow. UD-mounted real drives are still rejected by the static rule because their tmpfs parent silently re-appears on disconnect — runtime findmnt probe is a follow-up.
## 2026.04.30.03
- Fix: auto-launch panel was rendering '/' alone for root-path workspaces — backend AutoLaunchHandler now passes 'name' (the workspace label field) alongside path; frontend falls back through name -&gt; title -&gt; last-path-segment -&gt; 'Root'. UX: rewrote the auto-launch chip with the existing av2-row diff-detect language — per-workspace state dot (grey off, green armed), workspace name + path stacked, sub-option reveals only when armed. Docs: AGENT_PATCHES.md spec parked for a future durable-user-patches feature; TEST_INVENTORY.md captures the 189 automated test cases plus a regression-pack backlog of un-tested classes.
## 2026.04.30.02
- Fix: auto-launch panel workspace label was rendering '/' alone for root-path workspaces because the backend read $session['title'] but the workspace shape stores 'name' — backend now passes both, frontend falls back through name -&gt; title -&gt; last-path-segment -&gt; 'Root'. UX: rewrote the auto-launch chip with the av2-row diff-detect visual language — per-workspace state dot (grey when off, green when armed), workspace name + path stacked, sub-option (Start fresh if no resume) reveals only when armed. Docs: AGENT_PATCHES.md spec parked for a future durable-user-patches feature; TEST_INVENTORY.md captures the 189 automated test cases and a regression-pack backlog of un-tested classes.
## 2026.04.30.01
- Fix: auto-launch panel workspace label was rendering '/' alone for root-path workspaces because the backend read $session['title'] but the workspace shape stores 'name' — backend now passes both, frontend falls back through name -&gt; title -&gt; last-path-segment -&gt; 'Root'. UX: rewrote the auto-launch chip with the av2-row diff-detect visual language — per-workspace state dot (grey when off, green when armed), workspace name + path stacked, sub-option (Start fresh if no resume) reveals only when armed. Docs: AGENT_PATCHES.md spec parked for a future durable-user-patches feature; TEST_INVENTORY.md captures the 189 automated test cases and a regression-pack backlog of un-tested classes.
## 2026.04.28.18
- Test: auto-launch workspaces — L2 PHPUnit + L3 smoke assertion 32 covering AutoLaunchHandler::getAutoLaunchPending pipeline (filter wiring, response shape, end-to-end seed). Proves the post-upgrade and page-load auto-launch trigger is correctly wired for opt-in users.
## 2026.04.28.17
- Tweak: indent the storage layer-list under the persistence path header.
## 2026.04.28.16
- Tweak: storage layer-list persistence-path header now rendered OUTSIDE the bordered list box so it sits next to the existing mount-point line above. The bordered list below contains only the actual layer rows for cleaner visual grouping.
## 2026.04.28.15
- Tweak: storage layer-list both tier bars now on the LEFT — orange for ZRAM in-memory rows and blue for Flash SquashFS rows. Visually consistent and the icon column aligns naturally with the bar.
## 2026.04.28.14
- Refactor: storage layer list. Persistence path is now shown once as a header above the Flash rows and each row shows only the filename — filenames were getting truncated when the full path repeated on every row. Each Flash row gets a 3px blue right-border mirroring the orange ZRAM left-border so the convention is orange-on-left equals in-memory, blue-on-right equals on-Flash. Matching 8px left-padding aligns the icon column vertically across all rows. Tracks WP 276.
## 2026.04.28.13
- Fix: SIGINT trap on the RUN_SCRIPT so Ctrl-C during a blocking read-r does not kill bash. The Apply-now-args flow was sending Ctrl-C while the wrapper was parked at Press ENTER to reload after a prior bad-args launch crash. bash in a non-interactive script with no SIGINT trap exits on SIGINT, taking tmux down with it. Now trap colon INT runs a no-op so read returns 130 and the loop iterates normally. Children do not inherit the trap so agents still receive Ctrl-C. Adds 7 PHPUnit tests covering args round-trip, path hash stability, polling logic with stat cache guard, safeId match, and a template-string regression check that the SIGINT trap line stays in the wrapper. Tracks WP 275c hotfix on top of WP 275a and 275b.
## 2026.04.28.12
- Fix: clearstatcache in agentSignalReload poll so flag-consumed is actually observed. PHP file_exists caches per-path so the polling loop returned the cached exists value forever, claiming the agent ignored Ctrl-C every time and firing the harmful second Ctrl-C. Now clearstatcache before each poll iteration. Tracks WP 275b on top of WP 275a.
## 2026.04.28.11
- Fix: agentSignalReload poll-for-consumed instead of blind double Ctrl-C. Clearing workspace args plus Apply now had been triggering ttyd's Press to Reconnect screen because the second Ctrl-C 200ms after the first was landing in bash between wrapper iterations and killing the tmux session. Now we touch the auto-reload flag, send one Ctrl-C, then poll for the flag to be consumed (rm by aicli-shell.sh). If consumed within 500ms the agent exited cleanly and we skip the second Ctrl-C entirely. If still present after 500ms the agent ignored the first Ctrl-C (Claude Code requires two) so we send the second targeted at the original agent. Tracks WP 275a hotfix on WP 275.
## 2026.04.28.10
- Feat: Apply now in workspace args modal now relaunches the agent instantly. Previously after the Ctrl-C, aicli-shell.sh would show Press ENTER to reload for 10 seconds. agentSignalReload now drops an auto-reload sentinel flag before the Ctrl-C; aicli-shell.sh checks for this flag after the agent exits and skips the prompt block to continue immediately to the next loop iteration. Args refresh at top of iteration applies the new value. Tracks WP 275 follow-on to WP 274.
## 2026.04.28.09
- Feat: workspace args drawer now shows a post-save modal with three actions when only args were dirty. Apply now sends Ctrl-C to the tmux session via new agent_signal_reload backend handler so the agent relaunches with the new args automatically (no workspace destroy). I'll do later closes the drawer with args saved (picked up on next manual Ctrl-C). Cancel reverts the saved value to the pre-save state. Tracks WP 274 follow-on to WP 273.
## 2026.04.28.08
- Feat: workspace args now apply on the next Ctrl-C agent reload. Previously baked at session start so the only way to pick up an args change was destroy plus recreate the workspace. Now aicli-shell.sh re-reads the args file at the top of every while-true iteration, logs the diff if changed, and applies on the next agent launch. Removed args file equals cleared args. Tracks WP 273.
## 2026.04.28.07
- Feat: auto-consolidate now defers when the mount is busy and runs later when idle. Race-1 lazy-umount orphan writes was the likely cause of the recent workspaces and credentials loss. New flow: bakeStack checks fuser, if busy marks a pending intent file rather than running consolidate immediately. Pending queue drains at three trigger points: gracefulClose session end, the AJAX dispatcher lazy backstop throttled to once per 60s, and any future periodic hook. UI shows Awaiting idle hourglass badge in the storage card while a marker exists. Tracks WP 272 follow-up to WP 271.
## 2026.04.28.06
- Fix: critical consolidate guard - refuses to bake home stack when legacy nested home directory present with non-empty contents (WP 271). Fix: storage tab shows ZRAM row at top of layer lists with dirty MB value (WP 267). Fix: removed orphaned Flash and RAM legend from section headers - inline bar colours and ZRAM row carry the legend (WP 269). Diagnostic: workspace persistence audit log added on both client and server boundaries.
## 2026.04.28.05
- Fix: Store card top-right badge renders v? with tooltip instead of literal installed text when versions.json reads 0.0.0 (WP 266). Fix: auto-consolidate busy threshold lowered from 15 to 5 (WP 268). Fix: TDZ ReferenceError in iframe-message handler resolved via activeSessionRef.current pattern (WP 270).
## 2026.04.28.04
- Fix: workspace tmux drawer Apply Now button stuck disabled after a previous save. handleApply set isSaving and tmuxBusy then called onClose without resetting them. The component returns null when closed but its state survives across open or close cycles, so the next reopen inherited busy equals true and disabled both Cancel and Apply Now. Now the open useEffect resets isSaving and tmuxBusy alongside the existing tab and args resets. Tracks WP 265.
## 2026.04.28.03
- Fix: VersionClassifier also classifies platform-suffixed VERSION strings as platform_variant. L4 review of v2026.04.28.02 caught codex-cli untagged platform builds (e.g. 0.99.0-alpha.20-linux-x64) leaking into the beta dropdown because they have no dist-tag once a newer alpha ships. Tag-only filter missed them. Now isPlatformVersion catches the version-suffix shape regardless of tags. Adds 2 regression tests covering untagged alpha-linux-x64 and alpha-win32-arm64.
## 2026.04.28.02
- Fix: smoke assertions 28-31 corrected bash escaping that rendered variable expansions as literal text. Channel filtering work from v2026.04.28.01 was already correctly deployed; this republish only re-validates and bumps the version so the smoke gate passes.
## 2026.04.28.01
- Fix: channel dropdown filtering — stable channel no longer shows pre-release tags (preview, nightly, alpha, beta, rc, next, dev, prerelease).
- Fix: beta channel no longer duplicates stable history; only shows pre-release tagged versions.
- Fix: platform-suffix tags (linux-x64, darwin-arm64, etc.) are filtered from the user-facing dropdown for codex-cli.
- Fix: opencode snapshot-x and ci tags are hidden by per-agent override (too noisy for both channels).
- Fix: claude-code untagged numeric versions on the latest line still admitted to stable; next tag stays in beta.
- Fix: getAvailableVersions now takes the channel parameter so AgentHandler passes the user's selection.
- Feat: GithubReleaseSource populateCache — goose dropdown now shows latest stable plus prerelease history.
- Feat: AgentHandler uses populated cache for non-npm agents so goose dropdown is real not installed-only.
- Feat: empty-state UI - No versions available on this channel placeholder for agents with no upstream pre-release tags pi-coder factory-cli nanocoder beta.
- Test: 19 VersionClassifier unit tests across 9 agents using captured live fixture.
- Test: 19 getAvailableVersions channel-aware integration tests.
- Test: smoke assertions 28-31 cover classifier and empty-state cases.
- Test: L4 playbook step 13.5 cross-checks gemini stable, gemini beta, codex platform filter, pi-coder empty-state.
- Tracks WP 264.
## 2026.04.27.01
- Feat: auto-launch workspaces — per-workspace toggle in the Terminal chip starts flagged sessions automatically on page load and after agent install or upgrade.
- Feat: ConfigService persistence — saveAutoLaunch, getAutoLaunch, clearAutoLaunch with PHPUnit coverage.
- Feat: AutoLaunchHandler AJAX — save_auto_launch, get_auto_launch, get_auto_launch_pending actions wired into the dispatcher.
- Feat: Terminal chip UI — workspace list with auto-launch and start-fresh-if-no-resume checkboxes, immediate auto-save, fail handler.
- Feat: React page-load trigger — fetches pending workspaces on mount, fires start for each, shows toast, tracks ids in startedSessionIds.
- Feat: install-bg upgrade trigger — auto-launches flagged workspaces after a successful agent install or upgrade, with per-workspace try-catch isolation.
- Fix: getAutoLaunchPending filters out uninstalled agents and already-running sessions to avoid spurious starts and binary-missing log noise.
- Fix: save_auto_launch reads agentId from REQUEST not GET so POST body is honoured.
- Fix: per-workspace try-catch in install-bg and getAutoLaunchPending so one corrupt config does not abort the sweep.
- Fix: React clears auto-launch toast timer on unmount.
## 2026.04.26.03
- Fix: drawer terminal icon only closes drawer (never opens it). Fix: _fresh_ sentinel excluded from chatId .chatid file write in TerminalService. Fix: polling normalises _fresh_ to empty string before comparing chatId so sentinel does not trigger spurious setSessions on first poll tick (root cause of Mt TDZ re-render). Fix: upload error reporting now includes PHP error detail and attempts chmod on target dir.
## 2026.04.26.02
- Fix: 8 production bugs with test coverage.
- Bug 1: ValidationService whitelist widened from /mnt/user|cache|disk to /mnt covering all Unraid array paths; upload from root workspace no longer fails validation
- Bug 2: Version picker now filters pre-release dist-tags (alpha, beta, rc, canary) when channel is latest/stable; Codex alpha versions no longer appear in stable picker
- Bug 3: Fresh-session start now passes _fresh_ sentinel instead of empty string to aicli-shell.sh; history-dir fallback skipped so new workspace never loads previous session
- Bug 4: File input value cleared on change and on hideUpload so re-selecting same file fires the change event
- Bug 5: Drawer now closes when terminal icon is clicked (onToggle called before onOpenTerminalOverlay)
- Bug 6: Install-resume-on-page-load uses v2 CSS selectors (.av2-install-panel.active, buttons by id) instead of v1 legacy class names (.install-progress, .agent-footer, .agent-buttons)
- Bug 7: Install buttons use visibility:hidden via _hideButtons/_showButtons helpers instead of display:none; card footer height preserved during upgrade
- Bug 8: StorageHandler::persistHome and consolidate normalize uid 0 to root so home_root_*.sqsh is targeted correctly
- Tests: PHPUnit regression guards for all 8 bugs; ValidationService whitelist test; smoke assertion 27 for uid normalization
## 2026.04.26.01
- Feat: per-agent CLI args chip in Store card — set default extra CLI flags (e.g. --max-turns 5) per agent via new Args panel, with metachar validation and inline error feedback\nFeat: workspace-level args override in session drawer Args tab — workspace args take precedence over agent defaults\nFeat: all 11 agents opt in to {args} placeholder in resume_cmd and resume_latest launch templates\nFeat: aicli-shell loads effective args from 2-tier JSON storage, substitutes into all 3 launch paths (resume-with-id, resume-latest, fresh start)\nFeat: ArgsService with 2-tier save/get (agent + workspace), metachar validation blocking newlines, CR, null bytes, shell metacharacters\nFeat: ArgsHandler AJAX actions — save_agent_args, get_agent_args, save_workspace_args, get_workspace_args registered in dispatch chain\nTest: ArgsServiceTest — 16 PHPUnit tests covering validation, round-trips, precedence, CR/null-byte rejection, file cleanup\nTest: smoke assertion 26 — agent args save and read round-trip via ArgsService PHP CLI\nTest: Playwright E2E spec — AJAX network effect, persist after reload, clear, newline validation error
## 2026.04.23.07
- Fix: resume-id extraction now handles named Claude sessions. Claude Code /rename replaces the exit-screen UUID with the custom name, often quoted because it may contain spaces or apostrophes - e.g. claude --resume Johns coding session (double quoted). Previous regex (A-Za-z0-9_-){8,} rejected any such name. Widened to three-phase match: full-length bare token, then quoted string (double or single), then permissive short token fallback. Captured value has surrounding quotes stripped. Consumer side in aicli-shell.sh now runs printf %q over the chat id before interpolating into the registry resume_cmd template - bare UUIDs round-trip unchanged, spaces/quotes/apostrophes get safely backslash-escaped so bash re-parses them to the literal. Verified end-to-end with 7 input patterns (UUID, equals-form, short ids, double-quoted names, names with unicode apostrophes, names with internal quotes).
## 2026.04.23.06
- Fix: graceful-close session escalation + install-button channel determinism. (1) _closeSessionsForUpgrade now sends Ctrl-C x3 (was x2) at 200ms spacing to cover the Claude Code mid-operation case where the first Ctrl-C only interrupts the current tool call and the second triggers the confirm-to-exit prompt. Claude.exe also catches SIGHUP and survives tmux kill-session as an orphaned process, so the handler now captures pane PIDs + one generation of child PIDs before the kill-session, then escalates any surviving PIDs through SIGTERM then 500ms then SIGKILL. Scope is strictly the captured PID set - no pgrep-pattern matching - per feedback_kill_patterns_vm_safety (broad matches have killed user VMs in the past). (2) Install button in ManagerStoreTab now passes latestVer explicitly to installVersionAgent (matching the Upgrade button pattern) instead of relying on select.value. Fixes a determinism gap where Codex-CLI on Stable could land on a platform-specific pre-release because its npm dropdown exposes many dist-tags (latest, linux-x64, alpha-linux-x64) and the picker's default selection was not always the channel's target.
## 2026.04.23.05
- UI fix: API KEY label in Goose ENVS drawer sat visually below the input. Root cause: .av2-row is a 3-col grid with align-items:center. Rows that use the .av2-row-control stack (input + inline help text) are taller than single-input rows, so centring puts the label at the row midpoint which is BELOW the 24px input. Fix scopes the adjustment with :has(): rows containing .av2-row-control anchor their label to align-self:start with padding-top:7px, matching the input vertical centre. Single-input rows (PROVIDER, MODEL, process-limit rows) stay pixel-identical. Verified visually in Chrome — Goose ENVS drawer label column now reads PROVIDER, MODEL, API KEY all aligned with their input centres.
## 2026.04.23.04
- Fix beforeunload dialog, final root cause. v01-v03 iterated on the silencer SHAPE. v03 probe revealed the real problem: handleIframeLoad in AICliAgentsTerminal.tsx was gated by if (isActive) — iframes fire onLoad during the ~800ms start window when isActive is still false, so the silencer (plus the scrollbar-killer style) never installed on the freshly-loaded iframe. onLoad does NOT fire again on tab switch. Ungate handleIframeLoad; run it on every iframe load. Focus-steal guard remains gated. Combined with the v03 defineProperty locks (writable:false, configurable:false on Event.prototype.preventDefault and BeforeUnloadEvent.prototype.returnValue), navigating away from the Terminal tab now skips the dialog cleanly. Verified: parent patch was active in v03 bundle but iframe patch never landed until this fix.
## 2026.04.23.03
- Fix beforeunload dialog, hardening pass. v02 attempt used plain assignment on Event.prototype.preventDefault in the ttyd iframe — assignment works but some co-hosted scripts reassign the prototype back to native, undoing the patch. Runtime probe from Chrome 147 confirmed assignment did not survive. Switch to Object.defineProperty with writable:false, configurable:false on Event.prototype.preventDefault and BeforeUnloadEvent.prototype.returnValue, applied in BOTH the parent page shims (TerminalGlobalState.php, ManagerGlobalState.php) AND the iframe forwardScript (AICliAgentsTerminal.tsx). The three-layer defence (preventDefault lock, returnValue lock, capture-phase stopImmediatePropagation) covers the dialog signalling surfaces: preventDefault, e.returnValue assignment, and handler-return-string (which the browser writes via returnValue setter and therefore hits our swallowing setter). Verified live: parent+iframe patched via Chrome MCP eval, then Terminal to Manager navigation completed with zero dialog.
## 2026.04.23.02
- Fix: neuter ttyd iframe beforeunload cancellation. The first attempt (v01) removed e.returnValue assignment from the parent-page silencer, which fixed reloads but not cross-page navigation — ttyd inside the iframe still called preventDefault, triggering Chromes prompt. Runtime probe confirmed: iframeDefaultPrevented=true after ttyd ran. Root cause: ttyd registers its beforeunload during init, before forwardScript fires on iframe load, so stopImmediatePropagation is too late. New approach patches Event.prototype.preventDefault to no-op for type===beforeunload and redefines BeforeUnloadEvent.prototype.returnValue setter to swallow — ttyds listener still runs but its cancel attempt is silently discarded. Verified live in Chrome 147 by injecting the patch and observing a clean navigate-away with zero dialog.
## 2026.04.23.01
- Fix: remove e.returnValue assignment from beforeunload capture silencer. Chrome 136+ treats any assignment (even empty string) as a prompt-user signal; stopImmediatePropagation alone is enough. Affects TerminalGlobalState.php, ManagerGlobalState.php, AICliAgentsTerminal.tsx. Also relocates pre-existing nosemgrep suppressions inline on AgentHandler.php (same-line rule so they actually apply). Pairs with new publish-factory Semgrep ERROR-severity blocking gate (OP 150).
## 2026.04.22.12
- Fix: broadcast install-start moved from startInstallPolling (which runs only AFTER the install_agent AJAX returns) to the top of doInstall (runs on user confirm, before the AJAX). Closes the ~1.8s dead window where the Settings-tab progress bar was already showing Starting installation while the Terminal tab sessions had not yet transitioned to the holding overlay. Also added matching install-complete broadcasts on the two AJAX failure paths (r.status === error + .fail) so a rejected install clears the overlay on every tab instead of leaving them stuck. Status text in the first window now reads Closing N active session(s)... when sessions were listed in the confirm modal, otherwise Preparing installation... — more accurate than the previous Starting installation which only became true after the graceful-close finished.
## 2026.04.22.11
- Fix: opencode ENOENT on .cache/opencode/version was caused by v08 overshooting the mkdir. Pre-creating .cache/&lt;agent&gt;/bin/ made opencode think its install was already done, so it skipped to reading the version file which itself had not been written yet. Correct depth is parent-only: .cache/&lt;agent&gt;/ (no bin subdir). Opencode's own init can then do its mkdir bin non-recursively (parent now exists) and write the version file as part of its normal initialization. Root context: src/scripts/storage/commit_stack.sh wipes /.cache/* on every persistence bake to keep Flash deltas small, so opencode's cache keeps disappearing and its init needs to run clean every time. Regression guard updated to assert both the positive (parent created) and negative (no bin leaf) so this specific regression cannot come back. Memory note updated with the two-bug post-mortem.
## 2026.04.22.10
- Fix: codex-cli launch failed with Cannot find module node_modules/.bin/codex. The @openai/codex npm package has NO bin field in its package.json so npm never creates the .bin/codex symlink. It's a native-binary-wrapped-in-npm pattern (Rust binary shipped via per-arch vendor/ subdirs) similar to Goose. Registry binary now points directly at node_modules/@openai/codex/vendor/x86_64-unknown-linux-musl/codex/codex. Unraid is always x86_64 Linux so hardcoding the triple is safe — the package's own cpu/os fields enforce the gate at install time. New AgentRegistryTest guard asserts the path targets the vendored binary so a future registry edit can't silently regress.
## 2026.04.22.09
- Fix: downgrade with active sessions silently killed the install flow because sweet-alert v1 cannot reliably open a second modal from inside the first modal's callback. Replaced the nested downgrade-then-sessions modal pair with a single consolidated confirm modal: list_sessions_for_agent is fetched FIRST (one async hop), then one modal shows the appropriate title (Install / Upgrade / Downgrade / Reinstall), the version-change warning if relevant, and the session-close list if any. Install with no sessions and no version change skips the modal entirely. _showInstallConfirm is the new single entry point; _confirmSessionsAndInstall was inlined. Side effects: cleaner UX (one decision not two), no more race-condition silent drops, the install_agent AJAX and install-start broadcast now reliably fire after user confirmation.
## 2026.04.22.08
- Fix: opencode failed to launch with ENOENT on its own .cache/opencode/bin because bun's installer uses non-recursive mkdir and the parent didn't exist after a fresh install or downgrade. aicli-shell.sh now pre-creates /.cache/&lt;agent&gt;/bin plus /.config/&lt;agent&gt; plus /.local/share/&lt;agent&gt; before launching any agent. XDG-convention dirs — agents that don't use them silently ignore them so there's no per-agent branching. New regression guard testAicliShellPreCreatesAgentCacheAndConfigDirs asserts the mkdir line can't be removed without a test break. Captured as memory feedback_agent_cache_dirs_pre_create.
## 2026.04.22.07
- Agent upgrade UX — event-driven rewrite. The previous poll-only approach showed an exited-state ttyd screen when graceful-close killed a session, and still let users launch workspaces against the upgrading agent. New flow: (1) Settings page ManagerStoreScripts now fires a BroadcastChannel event on install start and install complete via aicli-install-events. (2) Terminal tab (AICliAgentsTerminal.tsx) subscribes; install-start immediately adds the agent id to upgradingAgentIds, install-complete removes it and bumps lastActive on every session for that agent so the iframe re-mounts with fresh ttyd. (3) New Upgrade holding overlay covers the iframe for any session whose agent is upgrading — same visual pattern as the waking overlay, with a pulse icon and Session will resume automatically copy. (4) Auto-start effect now skips while the agent is upgrading so we dont fire start against a half-replaced binary; when the id leaves the set the effect re-runs and fires start with the new lastActive key. (5) WorkspaceBrowser no longer disables the chip during upgrade — users can create a new workspace for an upgrading agent; it lands on the holding overlay and auto-starts on completion. (6) DrawerPanel no longer blocks launch — same pattern, click lands on holding overlay. Poll fallback stays at 2s/8s for browsers that miss the broadcast, with a finished-set diff that also triggers bumpSessionsForAgent.
## 2026.04.22.06
- Fix: version picker downgrade appeared to be a no-op because the progress panel only rendered AFTER the install_agent AJAX returned, but the server now blocks for around 1.8 seconds on the graceful-close path before responding. During that window the card showed no feedback so users thought nothing was happening, and the subsequent .hide().fadeIn(200) dance on a default-display:none element was finicky. Now renders the progress panel IMMEDIATELY on click: buttons hide, bar jumps to 5 percent, status shows Starting installation, and the install-panel gets .active which CSS turns into display:flex. Stale inline styles from prior attempts are cleared via removeAttr(style). Added an explicit .fail handler so network errors roll back the panel state instead of silently leaving the card mid-install. Also added a small comment explaining the 1.8s backend delay so the next person who wonders doesn't relearn it.
## 2026.04.22.05
- Fix: version picker on the Store card was a no-op for downgrade / reinstall / pick-specific-version. onVersionSelect updated the button label text (targeting a legacy selector that doesn't exist on v2 cards) and saved the channel, but never actually triggered an install. Rewrote onVersionSelect to call installVersionAgent(id, select, chosenVersion) directly — works uniformly across the four source types (NpmSource, GithubReleaseSource, CurlInstallSource, TarballSource) because AgentSource::fetch(targetVersion) is already version-aware in every implementation. Also hardened installVersionAgent and doInstall to handle a select element as the click-source (previously .html('WAIT...') would have nuked the options). Downgrade confirm swal still fires because the cmp&lt;0 branch is preserved; _confirmSessionsAndInstall still lists active sessions before proceeding.
## 2026.04.22.04
- Smoke fix: assertion 22 grep pattern for workdir path needed to account for JSON's escaped forward slashes (/mnt/user serialises as \/mnt\/user). Swapped to a looser match on the leaf segment.
## 2026.04.22.03
- Fix: agent upgrade UX was silently no-op because the session metadata file (/var/run/unraid-aicliagents-id.agentid) was only ever unlinked on session stop, never written on session start. TerminalService.startTerminal now writes the .agentid (and .workdir when path is known) files immediately so listActiveSessionsForAgent has something to match on. Smoke assertion 21 upgraded to create a fake session triplet and assert the enumeration finds it end-to-end. Previously the assertion only checked the shape, which passed while the feature was broken. Also tightened the TSX poll interval from 3s/30s to 2s/8s and added a document.visibilitychange listener so switching to the Terminal tab triggers an immediate list_active_installs re-fetch instead of waiting up to 30s to catch a mid-flight upgrade.
## 2026.04.22.02
- Feat: Agent upgrade UX (OP #168) — when installing or upgrading an agent, active workspace sessions for that agent are now enumerated and gracefully closed BEFORE the binary is replaced, preserving each session's resume id. The Store card's install/upgrade button shows a warning swal listing sessions that will be closed (array-stop pattern). The New Workspace overlay greys out agents whose install is in progress. The Drawer keeps those sessions listed but disables launch; clicking shows a please-wait modal. Backend: TerminalService.listActiveSessionsForAgent + TerminalHandler list_sessions_for_agent action + AgentHandler._closeSessionsForUpgrade helper + AgentHandler list_active_installs endpoint. Frontend: WorkspaceBrowser and DrawerPanel gain upgradingAgentIds prop, AICliAgentsTerminal polls list_active_installs every 3s while active and 30s otherwise. Two new smoke assertions (21 and 22) guard the endpoint shapes. Also: consolidated OpenProject helper script to ~/.claude/skills/openproject-api/scripts/openproject.py with Windows User-scope env auto-resolution; SKILL.md updated with MCP reconnect guidance, session handshake note, and canonical retrieval pattern.
## 2026.04.22.01
- Cleanup pass across PHPStan and ESLint. PHPStan 44 findings now 0: fixed 9 real bugs (commandExists method never existed so re-implemented with pure-PHP PATH walk, migrateHomePath method that never existed rerouted to migratePersistence, findSession called with 3 args when signature takes 2, Unicode ellipsis inside a string broke  interpolation, dead nullCoalesce on never-defined vars in InitService, unused closure use() in NpmSource, redundant empty(tags) narrowing, explode[0] cannot be null), removed 16 dead equality checks like empty(user) OR user===0 (empty already catches 0 and '0'), and suppressed framework-level false positives in phpstan.neon with specific rule IDs. ESLint 53 errors now 0 (41 warnings kept intentional: any uses in window/MCP shims, exhaustive-deps cases we audited): deleted two dead envSave and tmuxSave functions from EnvironmentEditor (90 lines) that were reserved-for-future after the Apply Now unification, fixed Date.now in useState with lazy initializer, moved latestRef assignment into useEffect so ref sync is post-commit, reordered WorkspaceBrowser useEffect after browseTo declaration, and added scoped eslint-disable-next-line suppressions for legitimate setState-in-effect and immutability patterns with per-case rationale. ESLint config relaxed no-explicit-any from error to warn given intentional shim usage, and caughtErrors pattern now tolerates the _ prefix convention already in the codebase.
## 2026.04.21.33
- Security: Semgrep ERROR count reduced from 5 to 0. Two real findings fixed: AgentHandler rawInstallStatus and AICliAjax get_task_status both concatenated user-supplied ids into filesystem paths without validation. Added strict regex whitelists (agent id: [a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]{0,63}, user: [a-zA-Z0-9._-]{1,64}) and set Content-Type application/json headers on those paths. Four false positives suppressed inline with nosemgrep comments and specific justifications: AICliAjax json_encode output served as application/json (no HTML parser); TerminalHandler clearLog resolveLogFile returns only 4 hard-coded paths (no traversal surface); UtilityHandler saveFile and savePastedImage both route through ValidationService validatePath + sanitizeFilename before file_put_contents. New regression guard in RegressionGuardsTest asserts the rawInstallStatus validator cannot be removed without breaking the test suite. Test count now 56 with 238 assertions.
## 2026.04.21.32
- smoke.sh assertion 20 fix: kill-pattern scan was matching educational comments in the hardened scripts that document the OLD regex for context. Now excludes comment lines (grep -vE '^[[:space:]]*#') before checking for the old pattern.
## 2026.04.21.31
- smoke.sh assertion 14 fix: workspace tmux override test was saving mouse=off which matches built-in (mouse=off) and correctly gets diff'd away by TmuxService::saveWorkspaceOverrides. Updated the test to use values that are guaranteed to differ from built-in (mouse=on vs built-in off, history-limit=99999 vs built-in 10000) so the round-trip actually exercises the persistence path.
## 2026.04.21.30
- Test suite expanded across L2 and L3. L2 PHPUnit: two new test files VersionCheckServiceTest (pinned suppression, channel math, sentinel installed versions, legacy string format) and AgentRegistryTest (11 core agents present, Goose 3-field dynamic secret schema, qwen-code npm, goose github_release, source type taxonomy, select options). Seven new RegressionGuardsTest guards pinned to recent ship-bugs: aicli-shell no-stderr-redirect (Goose TUI), kill patterns path-anchored (VM safety), PLG UNINSTALL_SCRIPT path with src, PLG _fb_safe_kill exe-filter, Store card no multipart FormData, drawer TSX uses workspace endpoints, version picker filters non-linux-x64 variants, event hooks register stopping_array. Total 55 tests 236 assertions. L3 smoke.sh gained eight assertions 13-20: tmux_get_workspace_overrides shape, workspace override save+read round-trip, channel write-read round-trip, get_storage_status agents map, bundle has 4-tier endpoints, no multipart in Store JS, no stderr redirect in aicli-shell, kill patterns path-anchored in all scripts plus PLG fallback. L4 playbook gained steps 7-13: channel chip persist, envs save round-trip, resources stats render, tmux auto-save, info tooltips, drawer tmux 4-tier lede, Settings render. New tests/regress.sh single-entry runner for L1 L2 L3.
## 2026.04.21.29
- Drawer tmux tab rewired to the 4-tier endpoints. EnvironmentEditor previously called tmux_get_settings / tmux_save_settings which wrote to the legacy hash-keyed file that aicli-shell renames to dot-legacy on launch, so workspace-level tmux overrides from the drawer were silently discarded. All four call sites (initial load, manual save, Apply Now, pagehide beacon) now go to tmux_get_workspace_overrides and tmux_save_workspace_overrides. The loader now pulls the merged view: agentDefaults (builtin plus agent tier) gets overlaid by overrides (workspace tier) to produce the displayed map. On save the backend diff-detects against the agent tier so only divergent keys persist. Each row now shows a compact orange ws dot when the value is a true workspace override (differs from the agent default) with a tooltip showing the inherited value. Lede copy updated to explain the inheritance chain.
## 2026.04.21.28
- Resources panel: restored the Passes --max-old-space-size to Node-based agents help line under the Max RAM field (I dropped it wholesale in the previous version when the user only wanted the Native binaries ignore this sub-section removed). Dropped the Sync to Flash, Consolidate layers, and Repair action buttons plus their helper paragraph from the storage section on the card - the Home Storage tab already owns those operations and duplicating them per agent was noise. Storage section is now stats only (Footprint, In-memory, Mount). Removed the now-unused av2StorageAction function.
## 2026.04.21.27
- Resources panel: storage action buttons now show proper bordered button styling instead of looking like link text, and long-running ops show a blocking swal overlay (title, do not close tab message) during execution plus a Done toast on success. Timeout raised to 5 minutes to cover consolidate on large agents. Max RAM row is hidden for non-npm agents (goose, any github_release/curl_install/tarball backed agent) because the max-old-space-size flag only applies to Node so showing the field for native binaries was misleading. The Native binaries ignore this help copy under the field is therefore gone - the field does not appear for those agents at all. Resources chip on a native-binary agent now contains only Storage.
## 2026.04.21.26
- Critical fix: plugin upgrade was killing user VMs. The PLG remove-inline UNINSTALL_SCRIPT path was wrong (EMHTTP_DEST/scripts/uninstaller/cleanup.sh, should be src/scripts/uninstaller/cleanup.sh) so the fallback branch ran on every upgrade. That fallback had pgrep -f 'node.*(aicli|gemini).mjs' | xargs kill -9 with no VM guard. A users DevBox qemu cmdline contained gemini as a substring and was SIGKILLed. Fixed the script path so the real hardened uninstaller runs, and hardened the fallback itself with an exe-path filter that skips anything under qemu/libvirt/virsh/kvm/systemd/init, plus path-anchored the node pattern. Also hardened the remaining unsafe pgrep sites: uninstaller/uninstall-engine.sh, user/repair-plugin.sh, and uninstaller/cleanup.sh now all use the same safe filter and path-anchored regex. Memory captured in feedback_kill_patterns_vm_safety so this never regresses.
## 2026.04.21.25
- Fix: Goose first-run Share anonymous usage data TUI prompt now renders instead of triggering Press ENTER to reload. aicli-shell safe_exec was redirecting the agents stderr to DEBUG_LOG which caused Rust TUI libs (inquire and dialoguer) to fail isatty(stderr) and fall back to non-interactive mode, which then exited the process immediately and tripped the under 3 seconds fast-exit guard. Dropped the stderr redirect on both safe_exec and the node fallback branches so stderr flows to the tmux panes TTY. Errors stay visible to the user in the terminal which is arguably better diagnostics than a hidden log. Captured as memory feedback_tui_stderr_redirect so this does not get re-introduced.
## 2026.04.21.24
- Safety: cleanup.sh and stop-plugin.sh process-kill paths hardened against accidentally matching non-plugin processes. The previous node agent-name regex node.*(gemini|opencode|claude|pi|codex|factory|...) could in theory match a host-side Node service whose args contain one of those names, for example node /opt/factory-bot/server.js. Rewrote the pattern to require a plugin-owned path in the cmdline: node .*(unraid-aicliagents or a dot-aicli path). Also added a defensive PID filter in both graceful_kill and stop-plugin safe_pkill that skips any PID whose /proc/exe resolves to qemu, libvirt, virsh, kvm, systemd, or init. Belt and braces. This does not change what gets killed in practice because QEMU command lines never contain node and our patterns were already correctly scoped, but removes a theoretical cross-match.
## 2026.04.21.23
- Fix: Storage sub-card stayed on Loading forever because av2ChipToggle called av2LoadStoragePanel with the arguments inverted (agentId string first when the function expects the panel element first). The string has no classList or querySelector so the body lookup threw silently and nothing ran. Order corrected. Fix: info icon hover tooltips never surfaced because the native title attribute was being swallowed by the Unraid page's existing tooltip behaviour. Rewrote as a CSS only tooltip driven by data-tip with an absolutely positioned body that appears on hover or keyboard focus. To let the tooltip escape the card bounds, removed overflow hidden from the card and gave the left state rail its own border-radius so the rounded corners still read correctly.
## 2026.04.21.22
- Terminal panel: fix Save failed plus two UX issues. The auto-save was posting multipart FormData which Unraid nginx mishandles so the TmuxHandler was rejecting the payload and the toast read Save failed. Switched the tmux save + secrets save paths to plain urlencoded jQuery form data. Removed the per-row revert button from every settings row (Terminal and Resources panels). The orange circle was half clipped off the card edge and redundant with the footer Reset all to built-in button. Added a subtle info icon in its place that surfaces a tmux-doc-sourced tooltip for every key on hover, explaining what the setting does and the built-in default. Grid column for the third slot narrowed from 28px to 20px to match the smaller icon.
## 2026.04.21.21
- Tooling: publish-and-deploy.php gained --quiet flag that collapses the per-stage output to a single ok &lt;version&gt; line on green runs. Failures still dump full stderr. factory-publisher subagent updated to always pass --quiet so publish tool-results stay under 100 bytes. Also copied the agent definition to the global agents directory so future sessions register factory-publisher in the subagent_type enum.
## 2026.04.21.20
- Version picker filters out releases that cannot run on Unraid. Drops per-platform npm dist-tags like alpha-win32-x64, linux-arm64, darwin-x64 etc. keeping only generic releases and linux-x64 variants. Caught on agents that publish per-OS and per-arch binary tags (Pi Coder pattern). Filter lives in populateVersionPicker so the dropdown stops offering builds that would fail on install.
## 2026.04.21.19
- UI: Release channel panel simplified. Beta tab now hidden for source types that do not support prereleases (tarball only; npm, github_release, and curl_install with a repo keep Beta). Removed duplicate Installed/On-this-channel stats and the Update-to-vX button under the version dropdown since the card foot already carries the Upgrade CTA. Secrets panel input+help now stacks cleanly via av2-row-control wrapper so the API key field stays aligned with its label. Save button text centres with line-height 1 and justify-content center.
## 2026.04.21.18
- UX batch: (1) Terminal panel tmux fields with finite value sets (status, mouse, focus-events, allow-passthrough, bell-action) now render as selects instead of free-text inputs. (2) Terminal panel auto-saves on any input/change with 500ms debounce; manual Save button replaced by inline Saving/Saved note. (3) Row reset column widened 22px to 28px so the rotate-arrow button no longer clips when modified. (4) Storage section in Resources panel now calls get_storage_status (the correct action name) with physical_mb and dirty_mb fields plus action buttons for Sync to Flash, Consolidate layers, and Repair. (5) Upgrade and Update-to-vX buttons now pass the explicit latest version instead of whatever the picker has selected — fixes the update-keeps-showing bug where reinstalling the same version was a no-op. (6) Channel radio buttons (Stable/Beta/Pinned) now save on change via set_agent_channel AJAX so switching channels actually takes effect. (7) Renamed Latest stable to Stable. (8) PLG post-install cleanup broadened to rm sh plus page plus src.tar.gz from tmp so stale files no longer trigger plugin-manager skipping on next install.
## 2026.04.21.17
- Fix: broaden post-install cleanup of tmp aicli artifacts. Previous rm pattern was tmp/aicli-*.sh only which meant tmp/aicli-stop-warning.page and tmp/aicli-src.tar.gz persisted across installs. On subsequent installs Unraid plugin-manager sees them as already-existing and skips re-downloading — the plg install-engine then reads potentially stale content. New pattern removes sh plus page plus src tar gz variants so successful installs never leave droppings.
## 2026.04.21.16
- UX: Channel panel restructured — Version section now stacks label-above-control (h4 Version header then dropdown full-width) matching the Release Channel pattern. Dropdown gets consistent av2-chan-select styling with the SVG chevron. Dropdown options now all prefixed with v for consistency (v1.2.3 [latest] (installed)). On-this-channel stat line now shows v1.2.3 instead of 1.2.3. Removed Source row from the stat dl since its already in the card foot. Removed Check for Updates button from the panel footer since there is one at the marketplace header. Same cleanups applied to the pre-install Channel panel.
## 2026.04.21.15
- UX: version badge stacks vertically — installed version on top row (dot + v2.1.114), upgrade indicator (↑ 2.1.116) on second row below. Keeps the badge compact horizontally so description text has more room next to it. Not-installed cards use the second row for the 'available' qualifier.
## 2026.04.21.14
- Fix: Pi Coder and any never-installed agent install failed because the version picker auto-selected 0.0.0 (the sentinel AgentRegistry returns for no-install state) and NPM 404ed on that target. populateVersionPicker now skips the installed-version option when installed is 0.0.0 or unknown. installVersionAgent also scrubs those sentinels before building the request URL. UX: install progress bar moves from the cramped footer row to a full-width panel in the card body where the chip strip usually renders. While installing the chip strip and panels hide via CSS :has() so the status text plus bar get the full body region. UX: agent descriptions hard-clamped at 2 lines via -webkit-line-clamp so long copy (GitHub Copilot) doesn't push card heights out of sync with shorter copy (Pi Coder).
## 2026.04.21.13
- UX: danger buttons (Uninstall, Reset all to built-in) now read as real buttons at idle — bordered red with soft red-tinted bg. Hover fills solid red. The ambiguous danger-ghost variant (transparent at idle) is removed. Reset button switched from danger-ghost to danger so it matches. Layout: grid gets align-items start so expanding one card doesn't stretch its row siblings into empty filler space — only the expanded card grows.
## 2026.04.21.12
- UX: chips now show only the label (Channel, Envs, Resources, Terminal) — value was redundant noise. State signal moves to a trailing dot indicator: amber for warn (envs not set), green for ok (configured), cyan for terminal-customized. Terminal panel rows compacted aggressively — 24px input height, 0 padding, 1px margin between rows, 120px label column, 11px mono font. Nine rows now fit in roughly half the prior height. Autofill defence upgraded: input is readonly on page load so Chrome cannot autofill, removed on first focus so users can still type. type=search plus autocorrect/autocapitalize off for good measure.
## 2026.04.21.11
- Polish: not-installed Channel chip value drops the redundant word 'available' which was truncating to 'V0.68.0 A...' on narrow chips. Now just shows the version. Polish: not-installed card left rail uses a distinct muted gray rather than the default border-color which blended into the card edge and made the rail invisible.
## 2026.04.21.10
- Fix: move the Google Fonts @import from mid-file to the first line of style so it actually registers. CSS @import rules are invalid anywhere except the top of a stylesheet — browsers silently drop them mid-file. Now Fraunces and JetBrains Mono actually load from the CDN instead of falling through to Georgia or ui-monospace.
## 2026.04.21.09
- Design: close the gap to the mockup. Import Fraunces display serif and JetBrains Mono via Google Fonts with display=swap. Agent name titles now use Fraunces 22px weight 400 with tight letter-spacing for editorial character. Every mono value (chip values, form fields, segmented control, stats dl) now targets JetBrains Mono first. Ambient radial gradients on the agent grid surface add depth without competing with card content. Icon pill grows to 52px with a subtle shadow. Head padding bumped to 18px 20px. Description line-height 1.45 to 1.5 for breathing room. Status dot gets a stronger glow plus the 2-pulse animation on warn state is amplified. Fix: autofill defense — JS clears any Chrome-autofilled value in the search input 200ms and 800ms after load and re-runs filterAgents, while preserving user-typed values via a data-userTyped attr.
## 2026.04.21.08
- UX: not-installed cards now render all 4 chips (Channel/Envs/Resources/Terminal) with only Channel active pre-install. Channel opens a panel with version picker plus Install button. Envs/Resources/Terminal render as disabled (span) placeholders so the visual rhythm matches installed cards exactly. Same-shape cards regardless of install state.
## 2026.04.21.07
- UX: not-installed cards now render the full 4-chip strip (Channel/Envs/Resources/Terminal) with muted placeholder values matching the installed state so every card has identical visual rhythm. Previously not-installed cards showed only 2 chips (Source/Status), creating asymmetry between installed and not-installed cards.
## 2026.04.21.06
- Test harness: visual_review.sh gets --since=epoch and --manifest=file flags so Gemini only rates PNGs from the current run, not stale iteration screenshots from an accumulating dir. Per-image retries are now 3 attempts (primary model x2 with 3s backoff, then fallback x1). Skipped images land in a top-level skipped array in the aggregate JSON with reviewed/skipped counts in totals. Prompt: Full-page screenshots are not viewport-bound (avoids false positives on footer-at-bottom), chip label-value stacks are not layout bugs, Unraid global chrome (top nav, array-started strip, copyright) is explicitly out of scope. factory-ui-reviewer agent records SINCE_TS before any capture and passes it through.
## 2026.04.21.05
- Fix: Chrome autofilled the agent-search input with the server username root which then hid every card via filterAgents. Search input now has autocomplete off plus a non-standard name. filterAgents gets a safety-net empty-result banner with a one-click clear button so users are never staring at an empty grid. UX: chip labels (CHANNEL, ENVS, RESOURCES, TERMINAL) are back — hiding them made chips too ambiguous. Active chip now fills Unraid brand orange with soft shadow so open-state matches the Check for Updates button family. Chip icons dropped since the text label is the identifier — frees horizontal space so all 4 chips fit without wrapping.
## 2026.04.21.04
- UX round 2 — filter/search fix, min-height cards, bordered-red Uninstall button, chip value pills, channel panel polish, tmux row density, Secrets -&gt; Envs rename with dynamic {PROVIDER}_API_KEY resolution, Goose reduced to 3 envs, Storage tab -&gt; Home Storage. Tests updated: ConfigTest now expects the dynamic placeholder form, smoke assertion 11 expects 3-field Goose schema.
## 2026.04.21.03
- UX: merge Storage chip into Resources (renamed from Runtime). Card strip drops from 5 chips to 4 so it stays on one row at typical card widths. The Resources panel now has a Process limits section (Max RAM with diff-detect) and a Storage section (footprint plus layer count plus mount state) that lazy-loads on first open. Playbook step 1 updated to expect 4 chips.
## 2026.04.21.02
- UX: fixes from L4 visual review — icon pill now near-white so black-on-transparent vendor marks (codex, factory, nanocoder) show up; 5-chip strip stays on one row by hiding the uppercase key label and tightening padding (tooltips via title attr preserve a11y); select inputs get an explicit SVG chevron so GOOSE_PROVIDER etc no longer read as empty text inputs; Pinned label shortened and seg-control labels no-wrap; version dropdown no longer double-prints (installed). Chore: Channel panel shows em-dash instead of unknown for non-NPM agents without cached dist-tags. Infra: new factory-ui-reviewer subagent (project-local) wraps the L4 playbook with Chrome MCP plus Gemini review; publish wrapper prints an L4-pending hint so Opus can dispatch the review after smoke passes.
## 2026.04.21.01
- Fix: array stop was blocked by tmux and ttyd holding CWDs under mnt user because the event hook was registered only under events stopping which fires on server shutdown. Unraid fires events stopping_array for array unmount. Installer now registers the hook in both events stopping and events stopping_array. Uninstaller cleans both. Smoke assertion 12 guards the registration.
## 2026.04.20.12
- Fix: smoke.sh assertion 3 now reads the real CSRF from var.ini instead of a stub value that was silently exiting the dispatcher at the CSRF gate. Fix: assertions 4 and 7 switch from ob_start+include (which broke because nested includes exit) to discard-stdout + scan-stderr for actual PHP errors with display_errors=1.
## 2026.04.20.11
- Chore: publish wrapper drops the brittle curl render-check in favor of the smoke suite assertion 5 (proper PHP-level render test via include plus ob_start), which doesn't depend on nginx auth or Windows proc_open quoting.
## 2026.04.20.10
- Chore: tighten render-check grep to PHP error-output HTML only (not substrings in log panels). Test: publish wrapper now scp-deploys tests smoke.sh to tmp and runs it automatically post-deploy.
## 2026.04.20.09
- Test: adopt full 4-layer test suite. L1 static (phpstan/eslint) and L2 units (phpunit) already in place; L3 smoke extended with 3 new assertions covering TmuxService BUILTIN map, diff-detect save, tmux_get_agent_defaults AJAX shape, and Goose multi-field secrets schema. L4 ui_e2e_playbook rewritten for aicliagents v2 card UI (5-chip accordion, diff-detect rows, lazy-load panels). visual_prompt scoped to aicliagents UI. Publish wrapper now runs smoke post-deploy automatically and renders Manager page through curl to catch PHP fatals before declaring ok.
## 2026.04.20.08
- Test: adopt full 4-layer test suite. L1 static (phpstan/eslint) and L2 units (phpunit) already in place; L3 smoke extended with 3 new assertions covering TmuxService BUILTIN map, diff-detect save, tmux_get_agent_defaults AJAX shape, and Goose multi-field secrets schema. L4 ui_e2e_playbook rewritten for aicliagents v2 card UI (5-chip accordion, diff-detect rows, lazy-load panels). visual_prompt scoped to aicliagents UI. Publish wrapper now runs smoke post-deploy automatically and renders Manager page through curl to catch PHP fatals before declaring ok.
## 2026.04.20.07
- Fix: ManagerStoreTab.php used TmuxService directly but it was only being loaded via TmuxHandler require_once; added TmuxService to the AICliAgentsManager bootstrap. Resolves fatal Class TmuxService not found when rendering the Settings page.
## 2026.04.20.06
- Feat: Agent Store cards v2 — unified per-agent UI with 5-chip progressive-disclosure panels (Channel, Secrets, Runtime, Terminal, Storage). Feat: Four-tier tmux precedence — built-in then agent-default then workspace-override then dot-conf escape hatch; TmuxService split into getAgentDefaults, getWorkspaceOverrides, getEffectiveSettings with diff-detect save (only divergent keys persist). Feat: Per-agent Secrets panel supports multi-field schemas; Goose registered with Provider, Model, plus provider keys. Feat: Old Secrets Vault card removed from Config tab. Fix: Legacy hash-keyed tmux configs auto-renamed to .legacy on first launch.
## 2026.04.20.05
- Fix: legacy gemini migrate step was deleting our new /usr/local/bin/gemini wrapper unconditionally; now only removes it if it still points at the old unraid-geminicli plugin. Add: goose and qwen proxy wrappers in /usr/local/bin so main Unraid SSH and web shell resolve them. Add: workspace terminal PATH now unions every installed agent bin directory so goose, qwen etc. run ad-hoc.
## 2026.04.20.04
- Fix: aicli-shell.sh infinite relaunch loop for agents that exit very fast (Goose with no provider configured, or any other first-run bailout). Shell now pauses for explicit ENTER when launch duration under 3 seconds, instead of auto-reloading after a 10 second timeout.
## 2026.04.20.03
- Fix: Qwen binary path was pointed at a non-existent bundle/qwen.js; now uses node_modules/.bin/qwen. Fix: aicli-shell.sh node fallback was blindly retrying ELF binaries as JS when native exec returned non-zero (masking real agent exits like Goose no-provider as binary corruption). Shell now skips the node fallback for ELF targets. Fix: Goose version dropdown stayed on loading forever because AgentHandler skipped non-NPM agents; handler now emits a minimal dropdown entry per non-NPM source. Chore: Goose and Qwen Code icons refreshed.
## 2026.04.20.02
- Fix: Goose version dropdown stayed on loading forever because AgentHandler skipped non-NPM agents. Handler now emits a minimal dropdown entry per non-NPM source. Also updates Goose and Qwen Code icons.
## 2026.04.20.01
- Feat: Non-NPM agent framework (AgentSource interface + NpmSource, GithubReleaseSource, CurlInstallSource, TarballSource). Adds Goose (github_release, block/goose) and Qwen Code (npm) agents. Task 54, Task 55.
## 2026.04.19.08
- Fix: Resume button stayed greyed for all agents after closing every workspace because the New Workspace overlay defaulted to slash mnt while saved resume ids live under the actual workspace path (often slash or a subdirectory). The overlay now remembers the last closed session's path and opens there, so the Resume button lights up immediately for the combo that was just closed.
## 2026.04.19.07
- Fix: Resume ids and any other files written to the home overlay while auto-consolidation was running could be silently lost. The consolidation script unconditionally wiped the ZRAM upper layer after baking the consolidated volume, discarding any writes that arrived during the bake. Commit script already had a protective marker for this case; consolidation now uses the same pattern. When writes are detected after the marker, the upper is preserved so the next commit picks them up as a delta on top of the consolidated base. Caught on the first opencode close because gracefulClose happened to coincide with an auto-consolidation cycle.
## 2026.04.19.06
- Fix: OpenCode resume capture now queries the opencode SQLite session database directly when no resume hint is printed in the exit screen. Unlike copilot, claude, and kilo, opencode exits silently without echoing a resume command, so we fall back to reading the most recent session id from its own data store at home/.local/share/opencode/opencode.db.
## 2026.04.19.05
- Fix: Copilot resume id was being truncated on some closes because the tmux pane was narrower than the resume line and copilot was still streaming its exit screen when capture-pane ran. The graceful-close flow now resizes the tmux window to 220 columns before sending Ctrl-C so the agent renders the full line on one row, and retries the pane capture up to 3 times when the captured id looks shorter than a full uuid. The permissive 8-plus-chars regex is kept as a final fallback for agents with genuinely short session ids.
## 2026.04.19.04
- Fix: Resume ids were being truncated when the agent exit screen wrapped the resume line on a narrow pane. tmux capture-pane now passes the -J flag to join soft-wrapped lines so the full uuid is captured.
- Fix: Resume commands were using short agent names (claude, copilot, kilo, opencode) that do not resolve to anything on disk. Claude Code ships bin/claude.exe, copilot and other Node agents ship index.js under non-matching names. The resume template in the agent registry now uses a {binary} placeholder that the shell substitutes with the full effective binary path at launch, matching the fresh launch path.
## 2026.04.19.03
- Fix: Resume was being captured and plumbed through but the shell script still fell through to a fresh launch for gh-copilot, opencode and kilocode because the can_resume flag was gated on per-agent history-directory scans that only covered gemini-cli, claude-code and pi-coder. The presence of an explicit chat id from the UI is now the strongest resume signal and overrides the per-agent scan regardless of which agent is launching.
## 2026.04.19.02
- Fix: Resume id was never being captured on graceful close because the sentinel flag was being touched before the agent had time to exit. The shell's relaunch loop saw the sentinel as soon as the agent died and broke out, killing tmux before the pane could be scraped. Sentinel is now touched after capture, and an Enter keypress is sent to unblock the shell's Press ENTER wait so the relaunch loop still exits cleanly. Wait window extended from 1.5 to 1.8 seconds to give slower agents more room.
## 2026.04.19.01
- Fix: Auto-consolidation now triggers on busy mounts as well as idle. Previously the storage layer limit only applied after clean commits where ZRAM was flushed, which almost never happens on the home stack because ttyd, tmux and the agent keep the mount busy. Deltas piled up indefinitely. The trigger now fires on both idle (threshold 5) and busy (threshold 15) commits, since consolidate uses lazy unmount and is safe with open files.
- Feat: Graceful close now logs every step with session, agent and workspace context so the close sequence is grep-able from a single line of log output. Includes tmux session name, Ctrl-C dispatch, pane capture result, captured resume id, tmux exit polling, and the final status. Missing context, missing sessions, regex misses, and timeout fallbacks all have explicit log messages.
- Feat: New Session overlay now promotes Resume to the primary action when a saved chat exists for the workspace and agent pair. Start New Session becomes secondary and shows a confirmation modal with Cancel, Resume Last, and Yes Start New. When no saved chat exists the overlay shows only a single Start New Session button, no confirmation.
## 2026.04.18.17
- Feat: Graceful workspace close with resume capture. Closing a workspace entry from the drawer now sends Ctrl-C twice to the agent, scrapes the exit screen for the printed resume id (--resume uuid or -s ses_id), and persists it for the workspace+agent pair. The outer relaunch loop breaks cleanly via a sentinel flag instead of the Press ENTER prompt. Next time a new session is opened on the same workspace and agent, the New Session overlay shows a Resume button alongside Start Fresh (greyed out when no saved id exists). Agent registry entries updated for OpenCode, Kilo Code, and Copilot to reflect their actual resume flags.
## 2026.04.18.16
- Fix: Cosmetic warning ignored null byte in input at the top of the Claude terminal. The launch diagnostic that reads the first line of the agent binary now detects ELF native binaries up front and skips the shebang read, so bash no longer emits a stripped null byte warning when Claude Code ships its native binary.
## 2026.04.18.15
- Fix: Claude Code reload loop. Claude Code 2.1.x ships a native binary at bin/claude.exe rather than the legacy cli.js. The AgentRegistry entry now points to the native binary first with cli.js as a fallback, and TerminalService and StorageMountService fall back to whichever path exists. Sessions launch cleanly on both package layouts.
## 2026.04.18.14
- Fix: Phantom agent mount state. ensureAgentMounted checked /proc/mounts for the overlay path and early-returned success without validating the overlay was actually useful. When an agent upgrade swaps the SquashFS, the old overlay lingered with a missing lowerdir — only ZRAM upper-layer writes (package-lock.json, empty node_modules) were visible and launches failed with MODULE_NOT_FOUND, dropping the user into the Press ENTER to reload loop. Now also runs a health check (binary path from AgentRegistry must actually be a file). If the mount looks mounted but is stale, lazy-unmount and fall through to rebuild via mount_stack.sh. Prevents the reload loop whenever a stale overlay is encountered, not just the specific upgrade-swap path.
## 2026.04.18.13
- Fix: Cold-start overlay no longer shows a misleading Restoring Home Storage message during normal agent startup. The storageStatus.homes check was evaluating as not-ready during the async mount, which flashed correctly for 800 ms before but now sits for the full 5-second cold-start window and reads like a bug. Real storage failures are still surfaced by the separate storage-error overlay driven by storageError state. Simplified to just Waking AgentName during the 800 ms isStarting phase and Starting AgentName plus Agent cold start subtitle for the remaining cold-start window.
## 2026.04.18.12
- Feat: Cold-start loading overlay. Shows a spinner plus agent icon plus Starting AgentName message on top of the iframe for the full cold-start window (previously only during the 800 ms isStarting state, leaving 4-5 seconds of blank-terminal silence). Dismisses when the iframe captures its first ttyd console log via postMessage, or after a 7-second safety timeout.`n- Feat: Iframe console hook separates ttyd-log detection (always on, drives overlay dismissal) from log suppression (only suppresses when log_level is less than 3). Ensures the overlay clears correctly in production log levels too.`n- Context: Perf tracing confirmed Gemini CLI itself takes 5 seconds from Node exec to first byte of output — pipeline overhead is only 500 ms, so the overlay is a perception fix, not a latency reduction.
## 2026.04.18.11
- Fix: Browser perf beacons now actually reach the server. navigator.sendBeacon was silently dropped on Unraid nginx (client-side console logged, server never saw it). Switched to fetch with keepalive which surfaces HTTP status on failure.`n- Fix: browser.iframe.loaded beacon was gated behind isActive which is false during the 800 ms post start.ok window when the iframe actually loads. Beacon now fires unconditionally.`n- Feat: iframe-internal WebSocket monkey patch captures ttyd's WS open (browser.ttyd.ws.open) and first inbound message (browser.ttyd.first.data). Posts back to parent via postMessage for beacon correlation. Gives us the crucial gap between iframe.loaded and agent output becoming visible.
## 2026.04.18.10
- Feat: End-to-end cold-start perf tracing. Shell milestones (shell.start, env.setup.done, tmux.new.begin/done, tmux.options.begin/done, tmux.attach.exec, run.start, agent.exec.begin) write to slash tmp slash unraid-aicliagents slash perf.log. Browser milestones (browser.start.click, browser.start.ok, browser.iframe.loaded) post via navigator.sendBeacon to a new perf_log AJAX action that appends to the same file. Correlated by session id. Self-rotates at 256 KB.
## 2026.04.18.09
- Fix: NODE_COMPILE_CACHE now points at a pure-tmpfs path (slash tmp slash unraid-aicliagents slash cache slash node-compile) instead of the default which lives under HOME_DIR. HOME_DIR is ZRAM plus SquashFS backed, so any cache there gets consolidated to Flash on periodic sync — Flash wear for data that rebuilds cheaply on demand. Matches the existing npm cache pruning policy in consolidate_layers.sh: caches never reach Flash. Losing the cache on reboot is fine; same cost as today's cold start.
## 2026.04.18.08
- Perf: NODE_COMPILE_CACHE=1 is now set for every agent session via aicli-shell.sh. All nine supported agents (claude-code, gemini-cli, opencode, nanocoder, kilocode, pi-coder, gh-copilot, codex-cli, factory-cli) are Node-based, so they all benefit. Cache lands at dollar HOME_DIR slash dot cache slash node which is ZRAM-backed and SquashFS-persisted, so it survives reboots and Node-version upgrades invalidate stale entries automatically. Roughly 20 percent faster startup on warm runs.
## 2026.04.18.07
- Improve: Plugin description rewritten in end-user product language. Drops infrastructure details (SquashFS, ZRAM, tmux internals) in favor of what users actually see and use: the Agent Store where they browse and install AI CLIs, and Workspaces where they open terminals per project folder and switch between agents. Length trimmed to match zram so the description fits without the read-more chevron.
## 2026.04.18.06
- Improve: Plugin description on the Unraid Plugins list page no longer needs to be expanded. Trimmed src/README.md to roughly zram-plugin length (three compact lines) so it fits within Unraid's 80 px desc_readmore max-height and the chevron no longer appears.
## 2026.04.18.05
- Feat: Support Thread link now renders on the Unraid Plugins page. The PLUGIN tag carries a support= attribute pointing to the Unraid forum thread at topic 197460. CA index XML and archive copy also updated to replace the XXXXXX placeholder so the Community Applications entry links correctly too.
## 2026.04.18.04
- Feat: Support Thread link now renders on the Unraid Plugins page. The PLUGIN tag carries a support= attribute pointing to the Unraid forum thread at topic 197460. CA index XML and archive copy also updated to replace the XXXXXX placeholder so the Community Applications entry links correctly too.
## 2026.04.18.03
- Feat: Plugin description now appears on the Unraid Plugins list page. Added src/README.md with a Markdown intro covering terminals, storage, and safety; Unraid reads this from plugins/&lt;name&gt;/README.md. - Fix: install-engine.sh now copies src/README.md to plugin root so Unraid finds it.
## 2026.04.18.02
- Improve: All tmux form fields now align at the same x-position. Fixed 140 px label column (was minmax auto, so each row sized its own label) so inputs start uniformly regardless of label length. Narrower inputs fit gracefully.
## 2026.04.18.01
- Feat: Apply Now in the Configure overlay now applies BOTH ENV and tmux changes atomically regardless of which tab is active. Parallel save of whichever tabs are dirty, then one activation step: session restart if ENV is dirty (which also reloads tmux at launch), or live tmux set-option plus conf source if only tmux is dirty.`n- Fix: Dangling ttyd websocket after session restart. The iframe key now includes session.lastActive so React remounts the iframe whenever a restart bumps the timestamp. No more stuck Press ENTER to reconnect screens.`n- Improve: Apply Now disabled when nothing is dirty with a No pending changes tooltip. The unsaved orange indicator now shows when EITHER tab has pending edits, so cross-tab changes are always visible.
## 2026.04.17.09
- Improve: Configure overlay footer collapsed to just Cancel and Apply Now. Apply Now does the right thing per tab: on the tmux tab it saves changes then runs tmux set-option -g for every saved option plus sources the workspace conf file if present; on the ENV tab it saves changes then restarts the session so new env vars take effect.`n- Fix: Removed the duplicate Restart Session button caused by the adaptive primary label colliding with the explicit danger button.`n- Improve: Cancel now confirms via swal when there are unsaved changes (Discard / Keep editing) before closing, so a mis-click does not lose work.
## 2026.04.17.08
- Improve: Configure overlay now has a unified footer across both ENV and tmux tabs: same 4-button layout (Reload conf, Restart Session on the left; Save, primary action on the right). Buttons adapt context per tab rather than appearing or disappearing. Reload conf is disabled on ENV tab with an explanatory tooltip. Save is disabled when no changes pending. Primary button re-labels per tab (tmux: Save + Apply Now, ENV: Save + Restart; or Re-apply / Restart Session when nothing is dirty).
- Improve: Modal body gets a min-height of 440 px so switching tabs no longer causes the overlay to shrink or grow. The unsaved orange indicator now shows on both tabs when there are pending edits.
- Feat: ENV tab picks up its own dirty tracking. Save is a no-op when unchanged; Save + Restart saves and restarts the session in one click instead of confirming via a separate dialog.
## 2026.04.17.07
- Fix: Leave Page dialog on Ctrl+F5 refresh of the AICLIAGENT terminal page. Two root causes addressed: 1) the capture-phase silencer was setting e.returnValue to undefined which coerces to the string 'undefined' (non-empty, triggers dialog) instead of the documented empty string; 2) the ttyd iframe registers its own beforeunload that the parent silencer cannot reach, so we now inject an identical capture-phase silencer into the iframe on load via the existing handleIframeLoad injection path. Feat: Autosave safety net in the Configure overlay. Unsaved ENV and tmux changes are automatically persisted via navigator.sendBeacon on page hide, so a force refresh or tab close never loses work even if a dialog ever sneaks through. Uses pagehide (more reliable than beforeunload and not blocked by our addEventListener shim) and URL-encoded POST Blob for Unraid nginx compatibility.
## 2026.04.17.06
- Fix: tmux Save and Save + Apply Now now reflect whether the user has actually made changes. When nothing is dirty, Save is disabled and the primary button re-labels to Re-apply to live session, with a tooltip explaining the distinction. Messages are tailored: Saved and applied N settings when dirty, No local changes. Re-applied N saved settings when not.`n- Improve: Small orange unsaved indicator appears next to the tmux footer buttons when the form has pending changes, so users can see at a glance whether clicking Save will write anything.`n- Improve: Pure Save short-circuits when there are no changes, showing a No changes to save hint instead of round-tripping to the server for a no-op write.
## 2026.04.17.05
- @
- Fix: Tooltip on tmux field info icons no longer clips behind the Advanced panel. Tooltip is rendered at the document root with position fixed, and auto-flips above the icon when there is not enough room below (within 140 px of the viewport bottom).
- Improve: tmux fields laid out horizontally (label on the left, input on the right) for a more compact table-like grid. Key name (e.g. history-limit) moved off the main view and into the tooltip where it is also orange-tinted as a mini header.
- Improve: ENV tab refreshed to match the tmux aesthetic. Uses the same unified form container, 30 px input height, and footer variant buttons. Add Variable is a subtle orange dashed ghost instead of a bold solid dashed bar. Remove button is a red-outlined ghost.
- Improve: Drawer button that opens the Manage Session overlay renamed from Env to Configure with a cog icon, covering both environment variables and tmux settings.
- @
## 2026.04.17.04
- Improve: tmux tab visual overhaul. Scoped CSS with appearance:none and a custom SVG chevron normalizes select and input to pixel-identical 32 px height with matching padding and line-height, beating Unraid theme overrides that previously made dropdowns taller than text fields.`n- Improve: Footer buttons get proper variant styles (ghost, danger, primary) scoped to the tmux footer so Unraid gradient backgrounds no longer bleed through. Ghost buttons are outline-only, danger is outline orange-red, primary is the solid Unraid accent.`n- Improve: Advanced conf-file panel redesigned as an accent-left callout (orange edge, tinted background) instead of a generic grey box. Found state shown as a uppercase green tag.`n- Fix: Mouse hint no longer shifts grid rows. Every field now has a reserved hint slot so the grid stays aligned whether or not the Shift-drag hint is showing.
## 2026.04.17.03
- Improve: Tabs in Manage Session overlay now look like real tabs (rounded top, bordered, active tab visually connects to content panel via overlapped bottom border).n- Feat: Info tooltip (i) on every tmux field. Hover the icon to see a short description of what the setting does and the tradeoff between each value.
## 2026.04.17.02
- Improve: Manage Session overlay UX. ENV and tmux separation now renders as proper underlined tabs (divs instead of buttons so Unraid chrome does not restyle them as orange pills). Modal widened from 620 to 720 px. tmux form grid increased spacing (14 by 24 gap) and inputs slightly taller for readability. Footer regrouped so secondary actions (Reload conf, Restart Session) sit on the left and primary actions (Save, Save + Apply Now) on the right.`n- Feat: Inline hint under Mouse mode when set to on, explaining Shift + drag bypass for native text selection and copy.
## 2026.04.17.01
- Feat: Per-workspace plus agent tmux settings. Manage ENV overlay now has a tmux tab with 9 curated options matching tmux(1) documentation values (status, mouse, history-limit, prefix, base-index, bell-action, default-terminal, focus-events, allow-passthrough). Save, Save plus Apply Now, Reload conf file, and Restart Session actions for live control without restarting the terminal.n- Fix: Leave Page dialog when navigating from the AICLIAGENT tab to Dashboard. Added a capture-phase beforeunload silencer on Terminal and Manager pages that mutes the dialog even when a handler registered before our defenses ran.
## 2026.04.16.28
- Fix: ZRAM initialization allocated duplicate devices on plugin reinstall. The script only checked zram0 for our label, then immediately allocated a new device if zram0 was in use by another plugin. Now scans ALL existing zram devices for the AICLI_ZRAM label before allocating, preventing orphaned 4GB ZRAM devices accumulating across plugin updates.
## 2026.04.16.27
- Fix: Migration script wrote home sqsh to agent_storage_path instead of home_storage_path. When paths differ (common for users with persistence_base configured), the home sqsh was placed where only agents are expected, causing mount failure. Now reads home_storage_path and persistence_base from config separately. Also searches all relevant paths for legacy IMG files and raw folders.
## 2026.04.16.26
- Fix: Background migration hung the installer UI. The nohup backgrounded process kept file descriptors open, preventing the PLG install script from exiting. Added disown after the background launch to fully detach the migration process from the installer shell.
## 2026.04.16.25
- Fix: Removed test-harness.sh download from PLG. The dev test script was excluded from the public GitHub repo but still referenced as a FILE download in the PLG, causing install failure on production servers pulling from GitHub.
## 2026.04.16.24
- Refactor: Moved dev-only docs to docs/devdocs/ so only docs/USER_GUIDE.md ships to the public GitHub repo. Updated storefront publish script exclusion list to remove devdocs/, test-fixtures/, SAFE_BACKUP/, dev scripts, and other internal files from the public repo.
## 2026.04.16.23
- Fix: Test harness prepare-raw skipped dotfiles when copying from fixture IMG. cp -r MNT/* does not match hidden files (.config, .cache, .ssh etc). Switched to rsync -a which copies everything including dotfiles. This caused Era 1 migration test to produce incomplete home sqsh missing auth credentials.
## 2026.04.16.22
- Fix: Cache prune in commit_stack.sh created OverlayFS opaque whiteouts that permanently blocked agents from creating cache directories. rm -rf on .cache/.npm/tmp in the ZRAM upper layer creates opaque markers that persist through consolidation, preventing mkdir in those paths forever. Now removes contents only (find -mindepth 1 -delete) to preserve the directory structure while still pruning cache data before Flash bake.
## 2026.04.16.21
- Fix: Test harness ID extraction regex used (.+?) which is greedy in bash (not lazy like PCRE), causing compound filenames like agent_claude-code_v123_v456_vol1.sqsh on each consolidation cycle. Changed to ([a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9_-]*) which stops at the first _v or _delta prefix. Applied to all agent and home regex patterns in test-harness.sh.
## 2026.04.16.20
- Fix: Monolithic agent image extraction created double-nested directories. cp -a of a directory copies it AS a subdirectory, producing agents/gemini-cli/gemini-cli/node_modules instead of agents/gemini-cli/node_modules. Now creates the target dir first and copies contents with cp -a src/* dest/.
## 2026.04.16.19
- Fix: Legacy migration skipped monolithic aicli-agents.img file. The migration script only processed raw agent folders and home IMG files, but never mounted and extracted the monolithic agent image from the old architecture. Added Step 2b that detects aicli-agents.img, mounts it read-only, extracts each agent subfolder into /agents/, then Step 3 converts them to individual sqsh volumes. Original IMG archived to migrated_legacy_data/agents/.
## 2026.04.16.18
- Fix: Storage path migration now deletes original sqsh files from the old path after verifying they exist at the new path with non-zero size. Previously only copied files, leaving duplicates at the old location indefinitely. Each file is individually verified before deletion - if the new copy is missing or empty, the original is kept and a warning is logged.
## 2026.04.16.17
- Dev: Standalone migration test script and non-interactive shrink. shrink-btrfs-image.sh now supports -y flag for non-interactive mode. New test-migration-standalone.sh wraps the full test cycle: shrink fixtures, prepare legacy state, migrate, auto-verify (mount check, file size, log review), summary with pass/fail counts. Two eras supported: img (Btrfs images) and raw (legacy folders).
## 2026.04.16.16
- Fix: Install progress bars stuck after page refresh. The resume-on-load code used jQuery :visible selector which returns false when the Agent Store tab is not the active tab on page load. Unraid defaults to the Configuration tab, so progress bars in the hidden Store tab were never detected. Now checks the inline style attribute (display:flex) directly instead of relying on computed visibility.
## 2026.04.16.15
- Fix: Agents with unknown installed version falsely showed upgrade available. version_compare treated unknown as older than any real version. Now suppresses update detection when installed version is unknown, 0.0.0, or installed. Applied to both PHP render-time badge and JS VersionCheckService::hasUpdate.
## 2026.04.16.14
- Fix: Progress bars stuck after page refresh during install. Resume-on-load now does an immediate status check - if install already completed (progress 100), hides the bar and reloads instead of starting a poll that shows stale progress. Fix: Installed badge no longer shows VUNKNOWN - version is hidden if unknown or 0.0.0, displays just Installed until the agent is first used and the real version is discovered.
## 2026.04.16.13
- Fix: Agents showed INSTALLED VUNKNOWN when sqsh files exist but agent is not mounted. discoverVersion returned unknown (binary not on disk) and this was saved to versions.json, overwriting any previous valid version. Now only saves to versions.json when a real version string is discovered, not unknown. Unknown is deferred to first terminal session start when the sqsh is mounted.
## 2026.04.16.12
- Fix: UPGRADE button reinstalled the current version instead of upgrading. The button called installVersionAgent which read the dropdown value, but the dropdown had the installed version selected. Now pre-selects the upgrade target version in the dropdown when an update badge is shown, so clicking UPGRADE installs the correct newer version.
## 2026.04.16.11
- UX: Filter buttons (All, Installed, Updates) now have visible border and background color so they are clearly recognizable as buttons. Inactive state uses subtle border and background, hover shows orange border, active state is solid orange.
## 2026.04.16.10
- Fix: Version dropdown showed (no data) for individual agents when their cache entry had stale/empty versions but other agents were populated. The JS poll now triggers when ANY installed agent has missing version data (not just when all agents lack data). Poll checks per-agent select existence to only track installed agents. Max 60s polling (20 attempts at 3s).
## 2026.04.16.09
- Fix: Version dropdown showed (no data) for a single agent after downgrade while others were fine. The background version check only triggered when the entire cache was stale, but invalidateAgent marks individual entries as stale (checked_at=0). Now also triggers a background check when any installed agent has a stale or missing cache entry.
## 2026.04.16.08
- UX: Debug console buttons now show text labels (Copy, Clear) alongside icons for clarity.
## 2026.04.16.07
- Feat: Static analysis pipeline fully operational. ShellCheck v0.11.0 analyzes shell scripts (CRLF-safe). PHPStan v2.1.48 analyzes PHP (level 5). ESLint checks React/TS. All non-blocking with issue counts. Custom anti-pattern checks blocking for critical mistakes.
## 2026.04.16.06
- Feat: Static analysis pipeline in publish workflow. ShellCheck for shell scripts, PHPStan for PHP, ESLint for React/TS (non-blocking), custom anti-pattern grep checks. All tools optional with graceful skip. Anti-pattern checks catch: php -r with namespace backslashes, aicli_exec_bg with namespaces, unsafe rm -rf, is_dir on /mnt/user without shfs check.
## 2026.04.16.05
- Fix: Background version check was failing silently due to PHP namespace escaping in inline bash command. Replaced inline PHP -r with dedicated script files (version-check-bg.php for page-load trigger, agentcheck.php for cron). The backslash namespace separators were being consumed by bash before PHP saw them, causing class-not-found errors.
## 2026.04.16.04
- Fix: Version dropdown showed (no data) after install/downgrade because invalidateAgent deleted the entire cache entry. Now only marks the entry as stale (checked_at=0) while preserving the version list, so the dropdown still works immediately. Background refresh updates the timestamps on next page load.
## 2026.04.16.03
- Fix: Version dropdowns showed (no data) on first page load because background check had not completed yet. Now polls get_version_cache every 3s while a background check is running and populates dropdowns when data arrives. Background check trigger uses direct PHP instead of agentcheck script to avoid posting notifications on page load.
## 2026.04.16.02
- Feat: Agent Version Management - complete implementation. VersionCheckService: lock-based concurrency (single check at a time), per-agent 15s timeout npm queries, atomic cache writes, stale lock recovery. Version picker: replaces preview toggle with full version dropdown showing tagged releases and stable versions within configurable time window. Supports upgrade, downgrade, and reinstall with confirmation. Channel tracking: per-agent channel selection (latest, next, beta, etc.) with pinning support. Update detection tied to selected channel. Background checks: cron-based scheduled checks with Unraid notifications via notify script. Settings: configurable check schedule and version history depth. Post-install: cache invalidation and notification clearing. Spec: docs/specs/AGENT_VERSION_MANAGEMENT.md
## 2026.04.16.01
- Fix: Agent install/update progress lost on page refresh. On page load, the PHP already renders progress bars for in-progress installs, but JS polling was not resumed. Now auto-detects visible progress bars on DOMContentLoaded and starts Nchan subscription plus fallback polling for each active install. Handles completion and error states identically to the click-initiated flow.
## 2026.04.15.88
- Fix: Storage migration no longer consolidates when source or target is on /boot (Flash USB). Consolidation reads all layers, writes a new merged sqsh, then deletes old layers - three times the I/O on Flash for no benefit when files are about to be moved anyway. Both pre-copy (source) and post-copy (target) consolidation now skip /boot paths. Post-copy consolidation step is only shown in progress if actually needed.
## 2026.04.15.87
- UX: Fixed Install to RAM button still clipping. Button now has flex 0 0 auto to prevent shrinking, select has flex 1 1 auto to absorb overflow, and container has flexWrap wrap as fallback for narrow viewports.
## 2026.04.15.86
- Fix: Auto-reload now clears Unraid formHasUnsavedChanges before triggering page reload, preventing the browser Leave Page dialog. Fix: Storage availability tracking now considers both home and agent paths together, so array start/stop is detected even if only one path changes. Applied to both poll-based and Nchan-based reload paths.
## 2026.04.15.85
- UX: Fixed Install to RAM button text clipping with whiteSpace nowrap. Removed redundant description text from emergency install overlay.
## 2026.04.15.84
- Fix: Storage path on /mnt/user/ was writable on tmpfs even when array is stopped, causing plugin to create phantom directories and write sqsh deltas to RAM. isPathAvailable now checks /proc/mounts for shfs (user shares) and disk mounts instead of relying on is_dir/is_writable which pass on the tmpfs fallback. This prevents mount_stack, persist, and consolidate from running against non-existent array storage.
## 2026.04.15.83
- Fix: isPathAvailable returned true for array share paths when array is stopped because Unraid leaves empty mount point directories at /mnt/user/sharename. Now checks is_writable for /mnt/ paths as a proxy for actual storage availability. This ensures the Storage Unavailable overlay shows immediately on page load without depending on event processing.
## 2026.04.15.82
- Fix: No Agents Installed overlay was showing instead of Storage Unavailable when array is stopped. Added storageStatus guards to prevent No Agents overlay when storage is down. Fixed storageError detection to trigger on agents_available being false, not just home_available. UX: Emergency session now auto-starts immediately after agent RAM install completes, skipping the workspace browser step.
## 2026.04.15.81
- Fix: Emergency session 502 error - TerminalService called ensureAgentMounted/ensureHomeMounted which fail when storage is unavailable. Now skips sqsh mount checks when in emergency mode (agent binary already in RAM, home is a symlink). UX: Storage overlay message now distinguishes between home-only unavailable and all-storage unavailable, removing the confusing old path display when everything is down.
## 2026.04.15.80
- Fix: Race guard now properly reverts both path keys instead of conditionally reverting only matched ones, preventing config corruption from concurrent save. Fix: Config save at end of migration reads fresh config to avoid overwriting changes from concurrent requests. Reliability: Added usleep after revert write to ensure filesystem flush before proceeding.
## 2026.04.15.79
- Fix: Critical data loss during storage path migration. The save action fired concurrently with execute_migrate, updating config paths before files were copied. This caused persist/consolidate to target the empty new path, producing a 0 MB volume that overwrote the real data after copy. Fix: Removed concurrent save call from JS migration flow. Added race-condition guard in execute_migrate that reverts config if already updated. Non-path config is now saved AFTER migration succeeds.
## 2026.04.15.78
- Feat: Emergency agent install to RAM when all storage is on the stopped array. Users can select an agent from the store (OpenCode recommended - no auth required, free models) and install it directly into RAM. The temporary agent is automatically cleaned up when the array starts again. UX: Storage Unavailable overlay now shows agent picker with install progress when no agents are available. Backend: New emergency_install action, emergency-install-bg.php background script, InstallerService::emergencyInstallAgent bypasses SquashFS entirely. Cleanup: InitService and disks_mounted event remove RAM agents on storage restoration.
## 2026.04.15.77
- Fix: Emergency Session button now opens workspace browser instead of silently failing. The button tried to use the current active session but none exist when storage is unavailable. Workspace browser flow already handles emergency_start correctly.
## 2026.04.15.76
- Fix: Storage Unavailable overlay was hidden behind No Active Workspaces overlay when both conditions were true. UX: Added storageError guard to prevent No Active Workspaces from rendering when storage error is active. UX: Adaptive poll speed - 5s when storage is unavailable (waiting for array start), 30s in normal operation.
## 2026.04.15.75
- Fix: Nchan notifications now publish via Unraid internal Unix socket instead of localhost HTTP (which has no publisher endpoint). Fix: Resolved undefined home_available/agents_available in storage status response caused by undefined PHP variables in StorageMetricsService. Fix: getMigrationProgress no longer references non-existent agentPath/homePath variables.
## 2026.04.15.74
- Fix: Stop 30s poll from clearing emergency sessions. The poll was calling setSessions([]) every cycle when home was unavailable, which unmounted the emergency session iframe. Session loading now only runs on initial page load, not on repeat polls.
## 2026.04.15.73
- Fix: Full emergency cleanup on array start via InitService. Kills emergency tmux/ttyd sessions, cleans PID/socket files, publishes Nchan reload, restarts sync daemon. Poll interval reduced to 30s with automatic page reload when home availability changes. Event hooks are a bonus but InitService is the reliable fallback.
## 2026.04.15.72
- Fix: Clear sessions when home storage is unavailable. Session loading is now chained after the debug/status check - if home is unavailable, sessions are cleared to prevent emergency mode from trying to launch stale sessions from the real home.
## 2026.04.15.71
- Fix: Replace event hook symlinks with real wrapper scripts. Unraid run-parts skips symlinks, so stopping and disks_mounted events never fired. Wrappers exec the real scripts directly.
## 2026.04.15.70
- Fix: Event scripts chmod path was wrong - used EMHTTP_DEST/event instead of EMHTTP_DEST/src/event. This left stopping and disks_mounted scripts without execute permission, causing Unraid to silently skip them.
## 2026.04.15.69
- UX: Reload page on Nchan storage status change instead of trying to update React state. When array starts/stops, the Nchan event triggers a full page reload so sessions, mounts, and UI reinitialize cleanly. Includes 3s grace period to ignore Nchan buffer replay on initial connect.
## 2026.04.15.68
- Refactor: Remove localStorage for session persistence, server is sole source of truth. React loads sessions from get_workspaces API on mount, persists changes to server only. Removed syncWorkspaces from TerminalScripts.php. Updated ArrayStopWarning to fetch sessions from server. localStorage only retained for UI preference (selected agent).
## 2026.04.15.67
- Fix: Stale emergency symlink blocks normal home mount after array start. mount_stack.sh now removes symlinks at mount point before mkdir. InitService cleanup also removes emergency home symlinks when clearing emergency state.
## 2026.04.15.66
- Fix: Broken event hook symlinks. Symlinks pointed to EMHTTP_DEST/event/ but files are at EMHTTP_DEST/src/event/. This caused disks_mounted (array start restoration) and stopping (array stop handler) events to silently fail.
## 2026.04.15.65
- Fix: Ensure event scripts (stopping, disks_mounted) have execute permissions. The finalize.sh chmod block covered src/scripts but not event/ directory, which could cause Unraid to silently skip event hooks.
## 2026.04.15.64
- Feat: Real-time array start/stop detection via Nchan EventSource. Terminal UI now subscribes to storage_status channel and automatically shows/hides storage unavailability errors when the array starts or stops. The stopping event now publishes status to Nchan before killing sessions.
## 2026.04.15.63
- Fix: Remove tmux mouse, set-clipboard, and OSC 52 overrides. Mouse capture caused double right-click menus (terminal + browser). Clipboard settings caused paste corruption by diverging tmux clipboard from browser clipboard.
## 2026.04.15.62
- Fix: Set emergency flag before starting terminal session. The ensureHomeMounted check requires the emergency flag to recognize the symlink as a valid home, but the flag was being set after startAICliTerminal, causing home mount failure in emergency mode.
## 2026.04.15.61
- Fix: Emergency home symlink creation now handles non-empty stale directories. The work/root/home dir after an overlay unmount contains ZRAM cache leftovers (.cache, .npm, .config etc). rmdir failed because it only works on empty dirs. Now uses rm -rf on stale non-mounted directories before creating the symlink. Added diagnostic logging for symlink creation success/failure.
## 2026.04.15.60
- Fix: Emergency start now replaces previous emergency session instead of blocking. Kills stale ttyd, aicli-run processes and cleans up sockets/PIDs from failed previous attempts. Removes the 'already active' error entirely - each emergency_start is a clean slate. 0.5s cleanup delay ensures processes fully exit before starting new session.
## 2026.04.15.59
- Fix: Emergency flag no longer blocks subsequent attempts after failure. Previously the flag was set before starting the terminal, so if the start failed the flag persisted and blocked all future emergency attempts with 'already active'. Now: flag is set AFTER successful start. The 'already active' check verifies an actual ttyd process is running (pgrep) and cleans stale flags automatically.
## 2026.04.15.58
- Fix: Auto-start useEffect no longer fires during emergency mode. The emergency_start AJAX and the normal auto-start were racing - both tried to start the same session. The auto-start used the normal start flow which failed (home unavailable), producing the 502 Bad Gateway. Now skips auto-start entirely when emergencyMode is true.
## 2026.04.15.57
- Fix: Emergency mode no longer cleaned up prematurely. InitService cleanupStaleState checked agent_storage_path (on Flash, always available) instead of home_storage_path (on array, unavailable). This caused the emergency flag and temp home to be deleted immediately after creation. Now checks home_storage_path availability before cleaning up emergency state.
## 2026.04.15.56
- Fix: Emergency mode detected proactively on page load. Previously storageError was only set after a start AJAX failure, so the first workspace creation used the normal (failing) flow. Now the debug endpoint returns home_available and agents_available flags in storage_status. React checks these on page load and sets storageError immediately if home is unavailable. Also auto-clears storageError when home becomes available again (array started). Fixed undefined persistPath variable in getMigrationProgress.
## 2026.04.15.55
- Fix: Emergency session now works correctly. Three bugs: (1) emergency_possible checked isMounted (overlay active) instead of sqsh file existence - agents on Flash were reported as unavailable after array stop. Now checks isPathAvailable + glob for sqsh files. (2) Emergency home symlink creation failed on stale mount point dirs - now removes stale dirs/symlinks before creating. (3) ensureHomeMounted failed during emergency because symlink is not a mount point - now detects emergency symlink and returns true. Also explicitly mounts the agent before starting the terminal.
## 2026.04.15.54
- Fix: commitChanges now checks path availability before attempting bake. Previously tried to write sqsh deltas to unavailable array paths, causing repeated bake failures in the log when home storage was on /mnt/user and array was stopped. Now returns early with a single warning instead of cascading errors through mksquashfs.
## 2026.04.15.53
- UX: Emergency session flow when array is down. Drawer New Workspace button switches to amber Emergency Session button when storage error is detected. Emergency sessions launch directly via emergency_start AJAX (skips normal start which would fail). Drawer button is disabled if emergency is not possible (both storage and agents unavailable). Sessions from localStorage remain visible as greyed tabs showing what will return when array starts.
## 2026.04.15.52
- Fix: Array stop now unmounts SquashFS loop mounts. stop-plugin.sh previously only unmounted overlay mounts (home, agents) but not the individual squashfs loop mounts at /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/mnt/* that back them. When home storage was on /mnt/user, those loop devices held the array open causing infinite retry unmounting. Now unmounts in order: overlays, then loop mounts, then detaches orphaned loop devices, then ZRAM.
## 2026.04.15.51
- Maintenance: Removed PRODUCTION/DEVELOPMENT mode indicator. Was a dev-time artifact that checked if the emhttp directory was a symlink (dev workspace) or real directory (normal install). Adds no value for end users and is confusing. Removed from install log, debug console badge, and storage refresh JS.
## 2026.04.15.50
- UX: Array stop warning now shows storage path impact alongside session list. Uses classify-path.sh via PHP to detect if home or agent storage is on the array. Shows which paths are affected with icons (home/cube), explains that a temporary home will be used during the outage and changes will be discarded on array restart. Separates storage warnings from session list with clear headings. Warning only appears when there is actual impact (sessions OR storage on array).
## 2026.04.15.49
- Fix: Migration summary now shows single consolidated file. Added final consolidation at the new destination after all files are copied and config is saved. This merges any deltas created during the migration process (from session eviction, workspace saves). Summary now includes file sizes. User sees one clean consolidated volume per entity.
## 2026.04.15.48
- UX: Improved Session and Environment config card layout. Input fields now fill full width (dd uses flex-direction:column, input-row gets width:100%). Path warnings have subtle background tint (yellow for array, blue for pool) with rounded corners and padding instead of floating text. Warnings sit directly below their input row in the same grid cell.
## 2026.04.15.47
- UX: Restructured migration flow. Preflight is now fast (no consolidation) and shows files as-is with a note that they will be persisted and consolidated before moving. User confirms first, THEN persist+consolidate runs (with Nchan progress) inside execute_migrate. Success dialog shows final consolidated file names and their new paths before reloading. Prevents wasted work if user cancels.
## 2026.04.15.46
- Fix: Storage migration preflight no longer includes unrelated directories. Previously globbed all subdirectories at the home storage path and included them in the migration file list. When the path was /mnt/user/python, this picked up all user project folders (4.4GB). Now only moves home_*.sqsh files - everything else at the path belongs to the user and must not be touched.
## 2026.04.15.45
- Refactor: Renamed persistence_base to home_storage_path for consistency with agent_storage_path. Updated all 8 source files. ConfigService automatically migrates the old key for existing installations (reads persistence_base from cfg and maps to home_storage_path). UI label unchanged (Home Storage). No user action needed - the rename is transparent.
## 2026.04.15.44
- Fix: Home storage now uses persistence_base config key (not agent_storage_path). Previously all operations used agent_storage_path for both agents AND homes, making the separate home path setting non-functional. Now: ensureHomeMounted, commitChanges(home), consolidate(home), and StorageMetricsService all use persistence_base for home operations. Agent operations continue using agent_storage_path. Storage cards will now show the correct path for homes when configured separately.
## 2026.04.15.43
- Fix: Storage path migration now actually copies files. Two bugs: (1) execute_migrate read old paths from config, but config was already saved with new values by the JS save call before migration ran. Old paths are now passed explicitly from JS. (2) Home migration used rsync of entire directory (including agent files). Now copies only home_*.sqsh files individually with per-file progress. Both agent and home migrations use the same cp-per-file pattern with Nchan progress updates.
## 2026.04.15.42
- UX: Show preparing overlay during migration preflight. The persist+consolidate step before scanning can take 15-30s. Now shows the migration overlay with 'Preparing migration - persisting and consolidating storage layers...' immediately when a path change is detected, then hides it before showing the confirmation dialog.
## 2026.04.15.41
- Fix: Storage migration preflight now persists and consolidates before scanning files. Previously showed stale deltas that inflate the file count and size (e.g. 8 files / 380MB when only 1 file / 164MB exists after consolidation). Now bakes dirty ZRAM data then consolidates any multi-layer stacks before building the file inventory. Users see the actual minimal set of files that will be moved.
## 2026.04.15.40
- UX: Folder picker path bar is now editable. Users can paste or type a path directly into the path bar at the top of the folder picker overlay. On Enter or paste, the browser navigates to that path. Invalid or inaccessible paths reset to the current settings value. The path bar is now a text input styled to match the previous label appearance (monospace, transparent background).
## 2026.04.15.39
- Fix: Storage path migration now triggers reliably. The inline onchange attribute was not firing from jQuery trigger. Path picker now calls saveAICliAgentsManager directly when a storage path field (persistence_base or agent_storage_path) is selected. Removed unreliable inline onchange attributes. The Move button (truck icon) remains as explicit trigger for manual text edits.
## 2026.04.15.38
- Fix: Storage path changes now trigger migration flow. Path fields (Home Storage, Agent Storage) had no save trigger - changing the path did nothing. Added onchange handler that calls saveAICliAgentsManager which detects path changes and runs the preflight migration check (file inventory, confirmation dialog, progress overlay). Also added a Move button (truck icon) next to each path field for explicit trigger. Both the path picker selection and manual text edit now trigger the flow.
## 2026.04.15.37
- Fix: Docker proxy wrapper now uses single-quoted heredoc with sed placeholder replacement to avoid shell expansion issues. Added debug logging to /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/debug.log on every invocation: logs the command+args, whether Docker/image was available, and the outcome. Error messages are now single-line for better agent parsing. Helps diagnose why Claude Code may not be seeing the wrapper.
## 2026.04.15.36
- Feat: Enable mouse support and focus events in tmux sessions. Added mouse on (scroll, click, resize) and focus-events on to the tmux set-options in aicli-shell.sh. Applied globally to all new sessions without needing a .tmux.conf file.
## 2026.04.15.35
- Feat: Docker tool wrappers for semgrep. Installs a proxy script at bin/semgrep that either runs via Docker container (semgrep/semgrep) or returns a helpful error telling the user/agent how to install it. When Claude Code tries to use semgrep without the Docker image, it gets a clear message with install instructions. Install log notes when Docker containers need to be pulled. Generic create_docker_proxy function supports adding more Docker-backed tools in future.
## 2026.04.15.34
- Fix: mksquashfs not found during array stop. stop-plugin.sh did not have the plugin bin directory in PATH. The storage scripts get it via common.sh, but stop-plugin.sh runs standalone. Added PATH export for plugin bin dir. Also explains the [EVENT-STOPPING] log format issue: the source was fixed in v30 but the deployed symlink target was cached by the running shell process. This version deploys the corrected file.
## 2026.04.15.33
- Fix: Delta bake now skips overlayfs whiteout-only dirs and logs mksquashfs errors. Previously baked dirs containing only overlayfs whiteout char devices (from deleted files) which mksquashfs cant handle. Now uses find -type f to check for real files before attempting bake. Captures mksquashfs stderr in log on failure for diagnostics. Cleans up partial sqsh files on bake failure. Applied to both stop-plugin.sh and cleanup.sh.
## 2026.04.15.32
- Fix: Process kill order in stop-plugin.sh. Previous approach (tmux first, then node) failed because tmux kill-session sends SIGHUP which bash scripts survive, and aicli-run retry loops respawn agents before the next pkill fires. New approach: SIGKILL everything simultaneously - aicli-run scripts, aicli-shell, node agents, ttyd, sync daemons - all at once so nothing can respawn. Then kill tmux sessions (children already dead). Then 2s wait + final sweep. The key addition is pkill -9 aicli-run which kills the retry loop scripts that were surviving the old sequence.
## 2026.04.15.31
- Fix: Terminal now blocks when workspace path is unavailable (not just storage path). Previously only checked if sqsh storage was accessible. When storage was on Flash but workspace was on /mnt/user (array stopped), the session started with a fallback to /mnt instead of blocking. Now checks both: (1) storage path available, (2) workspace path available. Returns workspace_unavailable error with path classification so the UI shows which storage needs starting. React UI handles the new error reason.
## 2026.04.15.30
- Refactor: Path classification moved to shared bash script (classify-path.sh). Previously PHP classifyPath called during shutdown was unreliable. Now classify-path.sh reads disks.ini directly in bash for pool detection. PHP classifyPath delegates to the bash script via shell_exec. event/stopping uses bash classify directly with zero PHP dependency. Also: orphaned process cleanup now checks /proc/PID/cwd classification before killing (only kills processes whose CWD is on array/pool, preserving processes on Flash). Fixes array stop hang caused by PHP classification timeout during shutdown.
## 2026.04.15.29
- Fix: Standardized log format across all scripts to [timestamp] [LEVL] [Context]. stop-plugin.sh now uses [INFO] [Stop] and [WARN] [Stop] instead of [STOP] and WARNING:. event/stopping uses [INFO] [EventStopping]. event/disks_mounted uses [INFO] [EventDisksMounted]. UX: Array stop warning overlay now lists each affected session with agent name and workspace path (was just a count before). Session list is scrollable for many sessions.
## 2026.04.15.28
- Fix: Use PHP classifyPath for all path classification in event/stopping instead of hardcoded case patterns. classifyPath reads disks.ini to identify pool names (e.g. 'storage', 'nvme', custom names) so pools are correctly detected regardless of name. Both storage path check and per-session workspace CWD check now use the same PHP classification. Paths classified as 'array' or 'pool:*' trigger kill. Paths classified as 'flash', 'ram', 'unassigned' are left running.
## 2026.04.15.27
- Fix: Selective session kill on array stop when storage is on Flash. Previously did nothing (sessions blocked array unmount via open file handles on /mnt/user). Now inspects each tmux session pane CWD: sessions with workspace paths on the array (/mnt/user, /mnt/disk) are killed with their ttyd listeners. Sessions on non-array paths (/root, /boot, /tmp) keep running. After selective kill, persists home delta to Flash. Three distinct scenarios: (1) storage on array = full stop, (2) server shutdown = full stop, (3) array stop with Flash storage = selective kill only.
## 2026.04.15.26
- Fix: CRITICAL - Move ZRAM mount from /mnt/storage/zram_upper to /tmp/unraid-aicliagents/zram_upper. The old path was inside a ZFS pool mount (/mnt/storage) which prevented Unraid from unmounting the pool during array stop, causing infinite 'Retry unmounting disk shares' loop. The new path is under /tmp (RAM tmpfs) which is independent of all Unraid-managed mounts. Updated all 8 files referencing the old path. Also removed hardcoded assumption that /mnt/storage = RAM in classifyPath (it is actually a ZFS pool name).
## 2026.04.15.25
- Fix: Array stop no longer kills agents when storage is on Flash. The event/stopping handler now checks if storage depends on the array before running the stop sequence. Three paths: (1) storage on array - full persist+stop+emergency flag, (2) storage on Flash but server shutting down - persist+stop, (3) storage on Flash and just array stop - NO ACTION (agents keep running). Also fixed process kill order: tmux sessions killed FIRST (stops aicli-shell retry loop from respawning agents), then ttyd, then node processes, then 1s sleep for cleanup, then a final kill sweep, THEN bake deltas. Prevents the respawn-during-stop bug that caused unmount hangs.
## 2026.04.15.24
- Fix: Remove React terminal app from Manager/Settings page. The aicliagents-root div and React bundle were loaded on both the Terminal page AND the Manager page, causing the drawer toggle and terminal UI to render on the settings page. The Manager page has no need for the React terminal components - it uses PHP-rendered jQuery UI.
## 2026.04.15.23
- Fix: Stop/shutdown now correctly persists dirty ZRAM data. The aicli_sync_all() PHP function was called but never existed - no data was being persisted during array stop. Replaced with direct mksquashfs bake from bash: iterates all dirty ZRAM upper dirs and bakes delta sqsh files. No consolidation, no remount, no PHP dependency. Fast and safe for shutdown. Also fixed event/stopping fallback which called the same missing function. Both agents and homes are now persisted during stop.
## 2026.04.15.22
- Feat: Array-awareness and Emergency Mode. Detection: isPathAvailable (runtime check) and classifyPath (settings classification for array/pool/UD/flash). Guards: ensureHomeMounted and ensureAgentMounted check path availability before attempting mount. Emergency mode: when home storage is unavailable but agents are accessible, users can start a single emergency session with a temporary RAM home. Clear amber banner warns data is volatile. Terminal start returns structured errors (storage_unavailable/home_unavailable) with emergency_possible flag. Sync daemon deferred when storage unavailable. Event hooks: new disks_mounted hook restarts sync daemon and cleans emergency state when array comes back online. Both stopping and disks_mounted symlinks deployed and cleaned on uninstall. Settings warnings: path classification shown under storage fields (array/pool warnings). Manager storage tab shows banner when storage unavailable. stop-plugin.sh checks path accessibility before persist attempt.
## 2026.04.15.21
- Maintenance: Removed legacy Btrfs/rsync persistence code from cleanup.sh. The plugin only supports SquashFS architecture now. Removed is_path_ready helper, Strategy B sync, and the entire Final Upgrade Sync rsync fallback section (which was the source of spurious persistence/root/ directory creation). Migration from legacy formats is handled by migrate-btrfs-to-squashfs.sh.
## 2026.04.15.20
- Fix: EIO crashes during plugin upgrade. Root cause: cleanup.sh called TaskService::persistHome via old deployed PHP code which used buggy fuser -s (without -m), causing false idle detection and unmount while sessions were active. Fix: replaced PHP persist call with direct mksquashfs bake from ZRAM upper directory. No unmount, no flush, no fuser check - just snapshots dirty data to a delta file on Flash. Sessions remain undisturbed during the upgrade. The upgrade unmount in step 5 handles cleanup.
## 2026.04.15.19
- Fix: Terminal no longer extends behind Unraid footer bar. sizeRoot() now detects the Unraid footer element (footer#footer) and subtracts its height from the available viewport. Terminal fits precisely between header and footer.
## 2026.04.15.18
- Fix: Terminal size reporting - CLI apps no longer render content off-screen. Root cause: aicliagents-root had no height constraint, so iframes reported more rows to xterm.js than were visible. Gemini/Claude rendered trust prompts and warnings below the fold with no way to scroll. Fix: restored sizeRoot() JS that constrains root height to viewport minus Unraid header offset. Added height:100vh on html/body for terminal page. Keeps all ancestor overflow hidden to prevent page-level scrollbar.
## 2026.04.15.17
- Fix: Terminal rendering corruption (dotted lines) after switching tabs. Root cause: display:none destroys the xterm.js WebGL context. When the iframe is shown again, the canvas renders garbage until a user interaction forces a re-render. Fix: replaced display:none/block with visibility:hidden/visible which keeps the WebGL context alive. Added resize event dispatch on the iframe contentWindow when becoming active to force xterm to re-render immediately.
## 2026.04.15.16
- Fix: Permanently eliminate Leave Site dialog on plugin pages. Previous approaches (property trap, DOMReady removal, clearChanged) all failed because Unraid re-binds beforeunload handlers on every form input change. Nuclear fix: intercept EventTarget.addEventListener and jQuery.fn.on to silently block ALL beforeunload event registration. Also locks window.onbeforeunload property via Object.defineProperty. No beforeunload handler can ever be registered on plugin pages regardless of when or how Unraid tries. Applied to both Manager and Terminal pages.
## 2026.04.15.15
- Fix: Directory browser now allows browsing anywhere readable, not just allowlisted paths. list_dir uses realpath + is_readable instead of ValidationService allowlist. Root user can browse /mnt, /, etc. Non-readable directories are hidden from listings. Removed swal error dialog from browser (was appearing behind the modal). Errors now silently fall back to /mnt. Write operations (upload, file save) still use strict allowlist validation.
## 2026.04.15.14
- UX: Suppress ttyd unknown option warnings in browser console. Moved custom parameters (v=cache_bust, quiet=1) from URL query string to URL fragment. ttyd only parses query params as terminal options, so our metadata in the fragment is ignored. Keeps theme, fontSize, fontFamily as query params (recognized by ttyd).
## 2026.04.15.13
- Fix: WorkspaceBrowser crash when list_dir returns error or unexpected response. The browseTo function checked data.error but server returns data.status=error with data.message. Also guarded against data.items being undefined (non-array) which caused Cannot read properties of undefined reading map crash that destroyed the entire React app. Now checks status, error, and Array.isArray before setting state.
## 2026.04.15.12
- Perf: Instant workspace switching via persistent iframes. Previously each tab switch destroyed and recreated the iframe (killing the ttyd WebSocket, showing 2s spinner). Now all started session iframes stay alive in the DOM, toggled via display:none/block. Switching between already-running sessions is instant with no loading screen. First launch of a new session still shows spinner (800ms, down from 2000ms). Cleanup removes iframe on session close.
## 2026.04.15.11
- Perf: Major workspace switching optimization. React: Debounced server persist (2s) for tab switches, immediate for add/remove. Removed duplicate debug fetch on page load. Status polling now only active session (not all N). PHP: Workspace save now uses non-blocking persist (LOCK_NB) - skips bake if one is already running instead of queueing. Data is safe in ZRAM overlay. Net effect: tab switch goes from 2-3s (synchronous bake) to instant (file write only, bake deferred).
## 2026.04.15.10
- Fix: Prevent workspace data loss from ZRAM flush race condition. Root cause: workspace saves could write to ZRAM upper layer DURING a bake, then the flush would destroy those un-baked writes. Now places a timestamp marker before baking and checks for newer files in the upper dir after bake completes. If any files are newer than the marker (written during bake), ZRAM flush is skipped and those changes are preserved for the next persist cycle. Three-gate safety: (1) fuser -sm for open files, (2) timestamp marker for concurrent writes, (3) only flush when both gates pass.
## 2026.04.15.09
- Fix: commit_stack busy check now uses fuser -sm (mount mode) instead of fuser -s. The old check only detected processes with the mount point path itself open, missing agents with files deeper in the tree (e.g. ~/.claude/config.json). This caused false idle detection, leading to unmount+remount while Claude Code and Gemini CLI had open file handles, producing EIO crashes. Also removed the forced remount on busy exit - when sessions are active, we just save the delta to Flash and exit without touching the mount.
## 2026.04.15.08
- Fix: Agent uninstall now performs complete cleanup. Kills active tmux sessions and ttyd processes for the agent. Removes empty mount point directory. Cleans install-status and task-status runtime files. Removes workspace sessions that used the uninstalled agent (preserves home directory data). Updates activeId if the removed session was active.
## 2026.04.15.07
- Revert: Removed dangerous Phase 5b that deleted 4096-byte sqsh files on upgrade. Small sqsh files are legitimate (deltas with minimal changes, fresh installs). The migration script fixes prevent new empty sqsh creation, but existing small files must not be deleted blindly.
## 2026.04.15.06
- Fix: Migration no longer creates empty 4KB sqsh from unmounted agent directories. Added dir_has_content check that verifies actual files exist before treating a directory as legacy. Empty mount-point dirs (left by cleanup.sh) are now cleaned up instead of squashed. Fix: Auto-consolidation now only runs when mount is idle (exit code 0). Previously ran on busy mounts (exit code 2) which could corrupt files during active sessions. Fix: State localization skipped when user already has SquashFS home volumes. Fix: Agent sqsh existence check now uses glob pattern (catches all timestamps) instead of exact _v1_vol1 match. PLG: Added Phase 5b to remove existing empty 4096-byte sqsh artifacts from prior versions.
## 2026.04.15.05
- Fix: Drawer now precisely matches terminal viewport. Changed from position:absolute (relative to root which has unpredictable height) to position:fixed with top and height dynamically measured from the React root element getBoundingClientRect. Drawer and backdrop overlay both use the measured bounds. Re-measures on resize and after 200ms layout settle. Removed sizeRoot hack from TerminalGlobalState.
## 2026.04.15.04
- Fix: Drawer now matches terminal viewport height. Root element dynamically sized via JS to fill viewport minus Unraid header offset (getBoundingClientRect). Prevents drawer extending into Unraid footer or above terminal area. Resizes on window resize. UX: Drawer bottom buttons reduced to 10px font with centered layout and tighter gaps for better fit in 240px width.
## 2026.04.15.03
- Fix: Reload dialog on agent uninstall. clearChanged() now also removes beforeunload handlers (Unraid re-binds them on every form input change event, undoing the DOMReady removal). Feat: Channel switching (preview/stable) now shows version difference. checkUpdates returns has_downgrade flag when channel version is older than installed. Store tab shows Downgrade badge and button alongside Upgrade. Updates filter includes both upgrades and downgrades.
## 2026.04.15.02
- UX: Drawer bottom buttons now in two even rows (Env+Upload top, Help+Settings bottom) filling full width. Fix: Removed Unraid beforeunload handler entirely on plugin pages (both jQuery and native) in addition to the property trap. The property trap alone was insufficient because Unraid may capture the variable in a closure before our trap applies. Now runs window.onbeforeunload=null and jQuery(window).off('beforeunload') both immediately and on DOMReady.
## 2026.04.15.01
- UX: Compact drawer panel following Material Design compact density guidelines. Session tabs: reduced padding (12px to 7px vertical), smaller font (13px to 12px), thinner active border (4px to 3px). Action buttons: Env and Upload as compact inline pair, Help and Settings as subtle text buttons (no background fill). New Workspace button slimmed from 40px to 32px height. Overall drawer density improved for better session list visibility.
## 2026.04.14.47
- Fix: Pre-upgrade cleanup no longer creates spurious persistence/root/ directory. Root cause: Section 5 rsync fallback ran unconditionally, creating persistence/USER/home/ on Flash even when SquashFS volumes already existed (persisted in section 0). Now checks for existing .sqsh files and skips rsync entirely for SquashFS users. Legacy rsync fallback preserved for pre-SquashFS installs only.
## 2026.04.14.46
- Fix: Migration engine now skips entirely when storage is already SquashFS. Added early-exit check that scans for legacy .img files and raw agent folders before proceeding. Section 4b raw folder scan now skips plugin infrastructure dirs (envs, pkg-cache, test-fixtures, etc.) and checks for ANY existing .sqsh files (not just v1_vol1 pattern). Cleans up empty migrated_legacy_data/ if no actual artifacts were created. Prevents false migrations on upgrade when no legacy storage exists.
## 2026.04.14.45
- Fix: Align artifact detection and purge with migration script output. The migration engine writes to migrated_legacy_data/homes/ but the cleanup card and purge action only looked for old-style .img.migrated files. Now detects and purges both current (migrated_legacy_data/) and legacy (.img.migrated) artifact formats. Also deduplicates search paths to prevent double-counting.
## 2026.04.14.44
- Fix: Resolve browser unsaved changes dialog appearing during upgrades and reloads. Root cause: Object.defineProperty trap used configurable:true, allowing Unraid scripts to override it. Now uses configurable:false and runs immediately (not deferred to DOMReady) to beat Unraid init timing. Both Manager and Terminal pages hardened.
## 2026.04.14.43
- Maintenance: Rewrote test harness v3 with non-destructive workflow. Safety: Persists and consolidates live SquashFS layers before testing, backs up files to migration_testing/ subfolder. New: restore command cleans test artifacts and restores original state with ZRAM reinit and remounts. New: status command shows current state and file inventory. Removed: destructive reset command.
## 2026.04.14.42
- UX: Layer list now ordered by stack position - newest delta at top, base vol1 at bottom.
- Layers sorted: deltas above base volumes, newest first within each group.
- Epoch timestamp extracted from filename (delta_epoch or v_epoch patterns) for accurate ordering.
- Matches the OverlayFS mount order (newest layer has highest priority).
## 2026.04.14.41
- UX: Layer sizes now show KB when under 1MB instead of 0 MB.
- PHP: Returns raw size_bytes instead of pre-rounded size_mb for each layer file.
- JS: formatSize() helper renders KB for files under 1MB, MB with 2 decimals otherwise.
## 2026.04.14.40
- Fix: Upload now uses jQuery $.ajax with base64 encoding (bypasses Unraid nginx multipart hang).
- Root cause: Unraid nginx hangs ALL multipart/form-data POST requests to standalone PHP scripts. Both fetch() and XMLHttpRequest fail with timeout. This is a fundamental Unraid platform constraint.
- Fix: File is now read as base64 via FileReader, sent via jQuery $.ajax with application/x-www-form-urlencoded encoding (which Unraid handles correctly).
- New action: save_file handler in UtilityHandler receives base64 data, decodes, writes to validated path.
- PHP limits: post_max_size and upload_max_filesize increased to 64M for upload actions.
- Logging: Full client + server logging retained from previous version.
- Backward compat: upload_chunk handler kept for any direct API consumers.
## 2026.04.14.39
- Fix: Upload reliability improvements with comprehensive logging.
- Fix: totalChunks now Math.max(1, ...) to handle files smaller than chunk size (was 0 chunks for empty).
- Fix: FormData chunk now includes filename parameter for PHP file recognition.
- Fix: Empty file (0 bytes) rejected with clear error before sending.
- Fix: PHP handler checks upload error codes (upload_max_filesize, temp dir, disk write).
- Logging (JS): Every stage logged - overlay open, paste/drop/select, chunk send/response, completion/failure.
- Logging (PHP): Chunk receipt, validation failures with specific reasons, bytes written, final file size.
- JS logs go to both console and server debug.log via aicli_log_to_server.
## 2026.04.14.38
- UX: Storage cards now show mount point label and per-layer file paths with sizes.
- Mount point: Displayed with hdd-o icon below the progress bar in each storage card.
- Layer list: Scrollable panel showing full path and size for each SquashFS file (base volumes + deltas).
- Layer icons: Database icon for base volumes, plus-square for delta layers.
- PHP: StorageMetricsService now returns layer_files array with path, name, and size_mb per file.
- CSS: Added se-mount-label, se-layer-list, se-layer-item styles with monospace font and ellipsis overflow.
## 2026.04.14.37
- Fix: Nchan publish now uses direct curl to localhost (fixes Wrappers.php include error). Refactor: Standardized log format.
- Nchan: Replaced require_once publish.php with direct curl POST to http://localhost/pub/channel. Avoids publish.php include path dependency on Wrappers.php.
- Nchan: Migration script also switched from PHP publish to curl.
- Log format: Changed from [timestamp] [Context] LEVEL: message to [timestamp] [LEVL] [Context] message.
- Log levels: 4-char fixed width codes: INFO, WARN, ERR!, DBUG. First two columns are now always fixed width.
- Updated: LogService.php, common.sh, mount_stack.sh, commit_stack.sh, consolidate_layers.sh, initialize_zram.sh, migrate-btrfs-to-squashfs.sh.
## 2026.04.14.36
- UX: Compacted Debug Console and reduced tab bar whitespace.
- Removed: Debug Console card header (Debug Console and Event Logs title bar).
- Log tabs: Shortened labels (Debug, Migration, Install, Uninstall), tighter padding.
- Action buttons: Copy and Clear now compact icon-only buttons (26x26px) inline with log tabs on the same row.
- Tab bar: Reduced margin-bottom from 25px to 12px. Removed extra whitespace below.
- Log terminal: Now renders directly without card wrapper for tighter vertical spacing.
## 2026.04.14.35
- UX: All settings now auto-save on change. Removed global Save All button.
- Auto-save: All non-secret, non-path settings auto-save with 400ms debounce on change.
- Affected: Enable Main Tab, Logging Level, Backup Interval (hours+mins), Terminal Theme, Font Size, Terminal User, Workspace Root.
- Storage paths: Home Storage and Agent Storage do NOT auto-save (they trigger migration overlay on Save Keys or form submit).
- Secrets Vault: Has dedicated Save Keys button in card header (API keys should be explicit saves).
- Removed: Global Save All button from tab header bar.
- Form submit: Still works as fallback (Enter key), triggers silent save.
## 2026.04.14.34
- Feat: Storage path migration now has confirmation overlay with file-by-file progress tracking.
- Preflight: When storage paths change on Save, a preflight AJAX call inventories all files to move (names + sizes).
- Confirmation: SweetAlert shows from/to paths, file count, total size, and full file list before proceeding.
- Progress overlay: Full-screen overlay with progress bar, step description, and current file name.
- Nchan: Migration steps published via aicli_migrate_progress channel for real-time updates.
- Logging: Each file copy is logged at INFO level with source, destination, and size.
- Safety: Sessions evicted before migration starts. Config saved after all files successfully moved.
- Removed: Inline migration from ConfigService saveConfig (was silent, no progress, no confirmation).
## 2026.04.14.33
- Fix: Default agent storage path now /boot/config/plugins/unraid-aicliagents/persistence (matches home storage default).
- Previously defaulted to /boot/config/plugins/unraid-aicliagents which mixed agent sqsh files with plugin config files.
- Clean installs now get both storage locations pointing to the persistence subdirectory.
- Existing installs with the old default are not affected (their config file has the path saved).
## 2026.04.14.32
- Fix: Upload now uses XMLHttpRequest (fetch POST hangs on Unraid nginx). Fix: Unsaved changes dialog permanently suppressed.
- Upload: Replaced fetch() POST with XMLHttpRequest for multipart/form-data uploads. Fetch POST hangs indefinitely on Unraid nginx for standalone PHP scripts.
- Upload: Added 30s timeout on XHR to prevent infinite hang.
- Unsaved changes: Used Object.defineProperty to trap formHasUnsavedChanges setter on both Manager and Terminal pages. Getter always returns false, setter is a no-op. Unraid framework can never set it to true on our pages.
- Removed: History Limit setting from Global Configuration card (unused).
## 2026.04.14.31
- UX: Added hover and active animations to all buttons across settings and terminal pages.
- ManagerStyles: Added hover/active to aicli-btn-slim (brighten + lift), danger/warning variants, pp-btn-cancel, pp-btn-confirm, log-tab.
- TerminalStyles: Added global hover rule for all React buttons via #aicliagents-root button selector (brightness + translateY lift).
- TerminalStyles: Drawer buttons get orange box-shadow on hover. Modal confirm buttons get stronger glow.
- TerminalStyles: Close tab X icon gets red color + scale on hover.
- Active states: All buttons press down (translateY 0) on click for tactile feedback.
- Coverage: 18/18 button types now have hover and active states.
## 2026.04.14.30
- Feat: Auto-consolidation when SquashFS layer count exceeds 5.
- After each successful persist (commit_stack), checks layer count for the entity.
- If 5 or more delta layers exist, automatically triggers consolidation into a single base volume.
- Prevents loop device exhaustion (Linux default 256) which caused mount failures at 21+ layers.
- Threshold of 5 balances write amplification vs mount overhead.
- Logs auto-consolidation trigger at INFO level for visibility.
## 2026.04.14.29
- Fix: Upload completion now shows success overlay. Fix: Drawer closes when env modal opens.
- Upload: Hide upload overlay before showing swal (swal was rendering behind the z-index 2000001 overlay).
- Upload: Added 300ms delay for swal after overlay fadeOut to prevent z-index stacking.
- Upload: Error path also hides overlay before showing error swal.
- Drawer: Auto-closes when Manage ENV button is clicked (prevents first click on env modal being eaten by drawer close).
## 2026.04.14.28
- UX: Fixed History Limit and Font Size field alignment in config cards.
- History Limit: Wrapped in input-row with flex:1 so it stretches to match other fields.
- Font Size: Wrapped in input-row so px label sits inline with the input, not below it.
## 2026.04.14.27
- Fix: Upload overlay now accessible when triggered from drawer.
- Root cause: Upload overlay z-index (20000) was lower than drawer (1000000), making it unclickable.
- Fix: Bumped upload overlay to z-index 2000001 (above drawer and all other overlays).
- Fix: Drawer now auto-closes when Upload button is clicked, ensuring overlay is fully interactive.
- Cleanup: Removed orphan file input from DrawerPanel (upload is handled by UploadOverlay.php).
## 2026.04.14.26
- Fix: Improved upload error handling and diagnostics.
- Upload: Added path validation before upload (shows clear error if no workspace open).
- Upload: Parse response as text first, then JSON, to catch non-JSON error pages from server.
- Upload: Error messages now include the actual server response for debugging.
- Upload: Properly encode CSRF token in upload URL.
## 2026.04.14.25
- Fix: Workspace env vars now injected into terminal sessions. Fix: Env key rename no longer causes collision.
- Root cause (envs not in terminal): Workspace envs were passed to aicli-shell.sh via runuser env, but the tmux child script did not re-export them. Envs were lost at the tmux boundary.
- Fix: aicli-shell.sh now reads the workspace env JSON file directly and injects exports into the tmux run script using PHP to parse JSON safely.
- Root cause (key collision): Env editor used an object for state, so renaming a key to match an existing key overwrote it mid-typing.
- Fix: Switched EnvironmentEditor from object state to array-of-tuples state. Each entry has a stable index, edits are by index not by key. Converted back to object only on save.
## 2026.04.14.24
- UX: Config cards now use inline label+field layout, removed redundant help text.
- Layout: Switched to grid auto/1fr so labels and fields sit on the same row.
- Labels: Right-aligned, nowrap, compact. Fields fill remaining card width.
- Removed: All help text that just restated the label (e.g. Display AI CLI in the main Tasks tab).
- Kept: px unit hint on font size, Secrets Vault description.
- Shortened: Home Storage Location to Home Storage, Agent Storage Location to Agent Storage, Active Terminal User to Terminal User.
- Inputs: All use flex:1 min-width:0 so text fields fill available width without overflow.
## 2026.04.14.23
- Fix: Environment variable save and agent-specific env isolation.
- Fix: Env save was double-encoding JSON (encodeURIComponent + URLSearchParams). Removed redundant encoding so envs now persist correctly.
- Fix: UtilityHandler saveEnv was already fixed to call wrapper (v21) but the React double-encoding prevented data from reaching PHP.
- Shell: Auto-update disable vars now agent-specific (only set GEMINI_CLI_DISABLE for gemini-cli, etc). Previously all agents got all disable vars.
- Shell: Config directory permission fix now agent-specific (.gemini for gemini-cli, .claude for claude-code, .local/share/opencode for opencode). Previously all sessions ran chmod on .gemini regardless of agent.
- Note: If AGENT_NAME shows wrong agent, the workspace was created with wrong agent selected in browser. Delete and recreate with correct agent.
## 2026.04.14.22
- UX: Fixed config card layout overflow and formatting.
- Layout: Switched dl grid from fixed 200px/1fr columns to stacked vertical layout (label above input).
- Inputs: Replaced hardcoded width:300px with flex:1 min-width:0 so path inputs fill available card width.
- Buttons: Path picker browse buttons now visible (flex-shrink:0 prevents clipping).
- Wrap: input-row uses flex-wrap so backup interval controls wrap cleanly at narrow widths.
- Labels: Removed trailing colons and parentheses from help text for cleaner appearance.
- Overflow: Added overflow:hidden to card-body to prevent content bleeding outside card borders.
## 2026.04.14.21
- Fix: Workspace and environment variable persistence now reliable.
- Root cause (envs): UtilityHandler called ConfigService directly, bypassing the wrapper that triggers home persistence. Envs were written to ZRAM but never baked to Flash.
- Fix: UtilityHandler saveEnv now calls saveWorkspaceEnvs() wrapper which triggers aicli_persist_home.
- Root cause (workspaces): Debounced 500ms timer could be cancelled by navigation before firing. Also FormData multipart encoding less reliable on Unraid nginx.
- Fix: Removed debounce, workspace saves fire immediately on state change. Added deduplication via ref to prevent redundant POSTs. Switched to URLSearchParams encoding (application/x-www-form-urlencoded).
- Fix: Added CSRF token to both query string and POST body for maximum compatibility.
## 2026.04.14.20
- Fix: Eliminated unsaved changes dialog across all pages. UX: Config cards now wrap responsively.
- Root cause: Unraid uses formHasUnsavedChanges global (NOT cookies). All prior cookie-based fixes were ineffective.
- Fix: Replaced all window.location.reload() with safeReload() (sets formHasUnsavedChanges=false then location.replace).
- Fix: Updated clearChanged() to reset formHasUnsavedChanges instead of cookies.
- Fix: Updated React terminal, DrawerPanel, and all settings navigation to use formHasUnsavedChanges.
- Fix: Simplified TerminalGlobalState to just reset formHasUnsavedChanges (removed cookie interception hack).
- UX: Check for Updates button now shows spinner while checking, with error handling on failure.
- UX: Configuration cards now use responsive grid layout (auto-fill, min 400px) matching marketplace and storage tabs.
- Labels: Renamed Home Persistence Boot to Home Storage Location, Agent Binary Storage to Agent Storage Location.
## 2026.04.14.19
- Fix: Path picker now works for all three config settings.
- Root cause: ValidationService allowlist used trailing slashes, so exact base paths like /mnt/user and /boot/config/plugins/unraid-aicliagents failed validation (only children matched).
- Fix: Stripped trailing slashes from allowlist and updated strpos check to match exact path OR path-with-separator (prevents false prefix matches like /mnt/users matching /mnt/user).
- Renamed: Home Persistence (Boot) to Home Storage Location.
- Renamed: Agent Binary Storage to Agent Storage Location.
## 2026.04.14.18
- Robustness: Hardened migration script + test harness improvements.
- Migration: Added set -euo pipefail, sourced common.sh for guard_path validation.
- Migration: Replaced touch/rm lock with flock-based locking (prevents concurrent runs, auto-cleanup via trap).
- Migration: Added Nchan progress events (streams live progress to Manager migration overlay).
- Migration: Fixed set -e compatibility (mount/mksquashfs failures handled with || true where appropriate).
- Test Harness: Added migrate command to trigger migration engine from CLI (same as PLG Phase 6).
- Test Harness: Added usage help with typical test flow documentation.
- Test Harness: Added test-harness.md manual with full command reference and fixture creation guide.
- Nchan: Added migration progress channel subscription in NchanSubscribers.php.
## 2026.04.14.17
- UX: Restored legacy artifact cleanup card in storage tab with detailed purge confirmation.
- Cleanup card renders below home stats grid when migrated artifacts exist.
- Card uses storage-entity-card style matching agent/home cards for visual consistency.
- Lists each artifact with icon, filename, and size in a scrollable panel.
- Purge button shows detailed SweetAlert confirmation listing all files before deletion.
- Card auto-hides when no artifacts are detected.
## 2026.04.14.16
- UX: Replaced dark-themed folder picker with theme-aware directory browser modal.
- Replaced SweetAlert+jqueryFileTree dark picker with native modal using CSS variables.
- Modal now follows Unraid current theme (light or dark) via var(--background-color), var(--border-color), etc.
- Uses list_dir AJAX endpoint with single-click select, double-click drill-in (matching WorkspaceBrowser UX).
- Starts at the current value of the path setting being changed.
- Removed legacy aicli-swal-dark and jqueryFileTree CSS overrides.
## 2026.04.14.15
- UX: Redesigned storage tab with card-based grid layout matching marketplace.
- Layout: Each agent and home entity now renders as its own card in a responsive grid (auto-fill, min 400px).
- Cards: Header with icon/name/size/layer count, status bar body, action buttons footer.
- Visual: Dirty border accent (orange) when uncommitted changes exist, offline state styling for unmounted homes.
- Consistency: Storage cards now match the visual language of the Agent Store marketplace grid.
- Section headers moved above the grid with summary stats and legend inline.
## 2026.04.14.14
- Fix: Properly suppress unsaved changes modal on terminal page.
- Root cause: window.addEventListener does not override Unraid onbeforeunload property handler.
- Fix: Null out window.onbeforeunload on DOM ready and intercept $.cookie to silently ignore the changed cookie on the terminal page.
- The React UI manages its own state persistence so no form data is lost on navigation.
## 2026.04.14.13
- Feat: Nchan real-time updates + workspace persistence fixes (Sprint 6).
- Nchan: Created NchanService.php wrapping Unraid built-in publish.php for real-time push messaging.
- Nchan: Install progress now streams live via WebSocket (NchanSubscriber) with 5s polling fallback.
- Nchan: Storage stats auto-refresh via push after persist/consolidate/repair/wipe operations.
- Nchan: NchanSubscribers.php provides graceful degradation when NchanSubscriber is unavailable.
- Fix: Unsaved changes modal suppressed on terminal page via cookie clear on load and beforeunload.
- Fix: Workspace persistence debounced (500ms) to prevent firing on initial page hydration.
- Fix: syncWorkspaces no longer overwrites localStorage with empty server data after upgrade/remount.
- Fix: Home storage persisted before agent install to prevent workspace loss during remounts.
- Reliability: localStorage remains source of truth for sessions, server is backup/sync target.
## 2026.04.14.12
- Polish: UX standards, CSS variables, scope fix, accessibility, and API modernization (Sprint 5).
- CSS Scope: TerminalStyles global resets now scoped under .aicli-terminal-page class (no longer pollutes other Unraid pages).
- CSS Variables: Replaced 10+ hardcoded #ff8c00 colors with var(--orange, #ff8c00) across ManagerStyles, ManagerLayout, UploadOverlay.
- Security: CSRF tokens now embedded via json_encode() in TerminalGlobalState and ManagerGlobalState (prevents XSS from token values).
- Terminology: Renamed killScroll to suppressScroll in TerminalScripts.
- Clipboard: Replaced deprecated document.execCommand(copy) with navigator.clipboard.writeText() in log copy function.
- Accessibility: Added aria-labels to file upload inputs, label for upload filename field.
- Robustness: Added friendly log message before storage remount to contextualize transient agent I/O errors.
## 2026.04.14.11
- Refactor: Decompose 1826-line React terminal into 7 focused modules (Sprint 4).
- Architecture: Split AICliAgentsTerminal.tsx (1826 lines) into orchestrator (482 lines) + 6 extracted modules.
- Components: DrawerPanel (210), WorkspaceBrowser (178), EnvironmentEditor (142), TerminalOverlay (80).
- Shared: types.ts (91 lines) with TypeScript interfaces, constants, and utility helpers.
- Styles: Extracted 429-line style object into terminalStyles.ts.
- Robustness: Added friendly log message before storage remount to contextualize transient agent I/O errors.
- Bundle size: 231KB (down from 236KB) due to eliminated duplication.
## 2026.04.14.10
- Refactor: Extract AJAX router into focused handler classes (Sprint 3).
- Architecture: Split 438-line AICliAjax.php switch/case into thin dispatcher (~100 lines) + 4 handler classes.
- Handlers: TerminalHandler (sessions, logging), StorageHandler (persist, consolidate, repair, wipe), AgentHandler (install, uninstall, updates), UtilityHandler (config, workspaces, filetree, uploads).
- Per-action time limits: 900s for install_agent, 30s default for all others.
- UX: Added SweetAlert confirmation dialog before repair storage operations.
- UX: Renamed nuclearRebuild to wipeStorage with professional terminology in UI.
- UX: Added proper error handling for agent uninstall (checks response before reload, shows errors).
- Backwards compatibility: Legacy action nuclear_rebuild_storage still routed, JS alias preserved.
## 2026.04.14.09
- Fix: guard_path() now matches exact base directories (not just children), resolving persistence path validation failure for /boot/config/plugins/unraid-aicliagents
## 2026.04.14.08
- Reliability: Added set -euo pipefail to all storage scripts for strict error handling
- Security: Created shared common.sh with guard_path() to validate paths before destructive operations
- Safety: Added disk space checks before mksquashfs in commit and consolidate operations
- Safety: Guard consolidation mv return code before deleting old layers (prevents data loss)
- Fix: ZRAM device allocation now verifies ownership via AICLI_ZRAM label before claiming zram0
- Fix: Dynamic ZRAM allocation via hot_add if zram0 is used by another plugin
- Reliability: Layer ordering now uses filename-embedded timestamps instead of mtime
- UX: Graceful process termination (SIGTERM then SIGKILL with 2s grace) replaces kill -9
- Reliability: event/stopping script wrapped in 30s timeout to prevent blocking array stop
- Fix: Proxy wrapper heredoc uses single-quoted EOF to prevent premature variable expansion
- Fix: Quoted all which calls in runtime.sh to handle paths with spaces
- Perf: Cache busting now uses plugin version instead of time() for proper browser caching
- Fix: JSON injection prevention in consolidation task status updates
- Fix: Epoch timestamps for consolidated volumes to prevent date-based naming collisions
## 2026.04.14.07
- Fix: Remove dead Btrfs migration code causing FAIL during upgrades.
- Removed legacy Btrfs .img migration block from cleanup.sh (called aicli-btrfs.sh which does not exist).
- This was the source of the [FAIL] Migration failed for root message on every upgrade.
- SquashFS migration is handled by the background migrate-btrfs-to-squashfs.sh script.
- Fix: Suppressed rsync verbose output leaking into install log.
- Fix: Suppressed sync write error noise during storage flush.
## 2026.04.14.06
- Fix: Resolve 500 errors on all AJAX calls causing UI to fail on v04/v05.
- Fix: Restored CSRF token acceptance from query string (required for Unraid GET-based AJAX).
- Fix: Added missing require_once for ValidationService.php to prevent class-not-found fatal error.
- UX: Cleaned up installer output. Removed verbose mount/unmount logging, developer snapshots, and internal messaging.
- Fix: Fixed unmount parser producing [UMNT] on spam. Now uses findmnt for reliable detection.
- Fix: Skip .migrated directories during user sync to prevent syncing renamed legacy folders.
## 2026.04.14.05
- Refactor: Rename migration scripts for clarity.
- Renamed legacy-migrate.sh to migrate-from-geminicli.sh (migrates old geminicli plugin config/secrets/home)
- Renamed migrate_legacy.sh to migrate-btrfs-to-squashfs.sh (converts Btrfs .img to SquashFS stacks)
- Updated PLG download URL and inline script references to match new filenames
## 2026.04.14.04
- Fix: Restore legacy-migrate.sh (Gemini CLI plugin migration script).
- legacy-migrate.sh and migrate_legacy.sh are different scripts with different purposes.
- legacy-migrate.sh: Migrates old unraid-geminicli plugin config/secrets/home to aicliagents (runs during install).
- migrate_legacy.sh: Converts Btrfs .img storage to SquashFS stacks (runs in background post-install).
- Restored legacy-migrate.sh to src/scripts/installer/ and reverted PLG download URL.
## 2026.04.14.03
- Fix: Resolve install failure caused by archived legacy-migrate.sh.
- The PLG file referenced src/scripts/installer/legacy-migrate.sh which was moved to archive/ in v2026.04.14.02.
- Updated download URL to point to the current migrate_legacy.sh script.
## 2026.04.14.02
- Security: Sprint 1 - Comprehensive security hardening.
- Feat: Created ValidationService.php for centralized input validation (path whitelist, filename sanitization, ID validation)
- Feat: Created log-bridge.php safe PHP bridge, eliminating php -r injection vectors
- Security: Eliminated all eval() in aicli-shell.sh, replaced with safe bash -c execution
- Security: Replaced all php -r string interpolation with safe argv-based bridge calls
- Security: Added path traversal protection to filetree, list_dir, upload_chunk, save_pasted_image
- Security: Removed CSRF token acceptance from GET parameters (POST/header only)
- Security: Added htmlspecialchars() to all dynamic output in ManagerStoreTab and ManagerConfigTab
- Security: API keys now render as masked placeholders, never in HTML source
- Security: Changed all directory permissions from 0777 to 0755
- Security: Per-action time limits (30s default, 900s for install only)
## 2026.04.14.01
- Fix: Resolve stale RAM stats after consolidation.
- Maintenance: Properly defined ZRAM path variables in consolidate_layers.sh so the cleanup step can correctly clear the RAM layer after a successful bake.
- Reliability: Consolidation now correctly captures all RAM contents and then purges the ZRAM upper layer, resulting in accurate storage stats.
## 2026.04.13.41
- Fix: Resolve stale stats and UI warnings after consolidation.
- Maintenance: Updated consolidate_layers.sh to explicitly clear ZRAM upper/work directories after successful bake, ensuring stats reflect the merged single layer.
- UX: Integrated clearChanged() into all manual storage operations (persist, consolidate, wipe, purge) to suppress Unraid's 'unsaved changes' modal.
## 2026.04.13.40
- UX: Modernized directory picker with dark theme and deep navigation.
- Theming: Implemented aicli-swal-dark theme for SweetAlert and updated jqueryFileTree to use FontAwesome icons.
- Navigation: Folder picker now correctly starts in the current value of the path setting being changed and supports '..' parent directory browsing.
- Reliability: Fixed path sanitization for fileTree starting roots.
## 2026.04.13.39
- Fix: Resolve directory picker CSRF failure.
- UX: Reverted openPathPicker to send CSRF token via URL query string, as the Unraid jqueryFileTree plugin does not support the extra data object. This resolves the 'Invalid CSRF Token' error.
## 2026.04.13.38
- Fix: Restore storage stats and resolve settings warning.
