- sh.
- Fix: Ensure runtime script syntax is valid after nested logic refactor.
## 2026.04.10.22
- Fix: Resolve bash syntax error in runtime
- sh causing silent installer skips.
- Fix: Correctly structure squashfs-tools installation logic to handle existing binaries and system-wide tools.
- Fix: Ensure all tool installation phases log clear success or failure markers.
## 2026.04.10.21
- Fix: Harden runtime tool installation with strict error checking and binary verification.
- Fix: Ensure installer exits with failure if tool extraction or download fails, preventing false-positive success logs.
- Fix: Standardize logging of tool installation phases for better transparency.
## 2026.04.10.20
- Refactor: Remove UI-blocking wait loop from background migration script to ensure the plugin remains usable during tool downloads.
- Fix: Update migration error message to guide users towards re-installation if tools are missing.
## 2026.04.10.19
- Fix: Resolve SquashFS migration race condition by implementing a wait loop for mksquashfs.
- Fix: Add backup Slackware mirror for squashfs-tools download to improve reliability.
## 2026.04.10.18
- Fix: Restore granular task progress bars for storage consolidation and maintenance.
- Fix: Restore 'Repair' (stack remount) and 'Wipe' (nuclear rebuild) maintenance buttons.
- Fix: Restore standalone background sync daemon for periodic SquashFS commits of user homes.
- Fix: Implement immediate SquashFS commit after agent installation to ensure ZRAM changes are persisted to flash.
- Fix: Implement automatic
- sqsh file migration when agent_storage_path is changed in settings.
- Refactor: Update TaskService and InstallerService to use SquashFS commit/consolidate logic instead of legacy Btrfs scripts.
- Refactor: Remove obsolete btrfs_delta_service
- sh from plugin manifest and cleanup sections.
## 2026.04.10.17
- Fix: Restore runtime tool checks and stabilize installer logs.
- Reorganized modular installer engine into 5 distinct phases.
- Restored missing call to aicli-runtime
- sh to ensure tool verification (Node, tmux, fd, rg, squashfs) is logged.
- Standardized step numbering and progress reporting for a professional installation experience.
## 2026.04.10.16
